  <Name>k__BackingField: Isaiah
  fancyName: 
  nickname: isa
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 255596ce6b91ac640b392e20dd4f8a9e, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Rebellion of God\u2019s People"
      title: "Rebellion of God\u2019s People"
      number: 1
      content: '  The vision of [the prophet] Isaiah the son of Amoz concerning [the
        kingdom of] Judah and [its capital] Jerusalem, which he saw [as revealed
        by God] during the reigns of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of
        Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Hear, O heavens, and listen, O earth;For the Lord has spoken:\u201CI
        have reared and brought up sons,But they have rebelled against Me and have
        broken away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The ox [instinctively] knows its owner,And the donkey its master\u2019s
        feeding trough,But Israel does not know [Me as Lord],My people do not understand.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Ah, sinful nation,A people loaded down with wickedness [with sin,
        with injustice, with wrongdoing],Offspring of evildoers,Sons who behave corruptly!They
        have abandoned (rejected) the Lord,They have despised the Holy One of Israel
        [provoking Him to anger],They have turned away from Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Why should you be stricken and punished again [since no change results
        from it]?You [only] continue to rebel.The whole head is sickAnd the whole
        heart is faint and sick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "From the sole of the foot even to the headThere is nothing healthy
        in the nation\u2019s body,Only bruises, welts, and raw wounds,Not pressed
        out or bandaged,Nor softened with oil [as a remedy].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Your land lies desolate [because of your disobedience],Your cities
        are burned with fire,Your fields\u2014strangers are devouring them in your
        very presence;It is desolate, as overthrown by strangers.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem) is left like a [deserted] shelter
        in a vineyard,Like a watchman\u2019s hut in a cucumber field, like a besieged
        city [isolated, surrounded by devastation].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: God Has Had Enough'
      title: God Has Had Enough
      number: 9
      content: 'If the Lord of hostsHad not left us a few survivors,We would be like
        Sodom,We would be like Gomorrah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Hear the word of the Lord [rulers of Jerusalem],You rulers of [another]
        Sodom,Listen to the law and instruction of our God,You people of [another]
        Gomorrah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CWhat are your multiplied sacrifices to Me [without your repentance]?\u201DSays
        the Lord.\u201CI have had enough of [your] burnt offerings of ramsAnd the
        fat of well-fed cattle [without your obedience];And I take no pleasure in
        the blood of bulls or lambs or goats [offered without repentance].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'When you come to appear before Me,Who requires this of you, this
        trampling of My [temple] courts [by your sinful feet]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Do not bring worthless offerings again,[Your] incense is repulsive
        to Me;[Your] New Moon and Sabbath [observances], the calling of assemblies\u2014I
        cannot endure wickedness [your sin, your injustice, your wrongdoing] and
        [the squalor of] the festive assembly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I hate [the hypocrisy of] your New Moon festivals and your appointed
        feasts.They have become a burden to Me;I am weary of bearing them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So when you spread out your hands [in prayer, pleading for My help],I
        will hide My eyes from you;Yes, even though you offer many prayers,I will
        not be listening.Your hands are full of blood!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CWash yourselves, make yourselves clean;Get your evil deeds
        out of My sight.Stop doing evil,  "
      comments: []
    - name: "17: \u201CLet Us Reason\u201D"
      title: "\u201CLet Us Reason\u201D"
      number: 17
      content: 'Learn to do good.Seek justice,Rebuke the ruthless,Defend the fatherless,Plead
        for the [rights of the] widow [in court].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CCome now, and let us reason together,\u201DSays the Lord.\u201CThough
        your sins are like scarlet,They shall be as white as snow;Though they are
        red like crimson,They shall be like wool.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'If you are willing and obedient,You shall eat the best of the land;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Zion Corrupted, to Be Redeemed'
      title: Zion Corrupted, to Be Redeemed
      number: 20
      content: "But if you refuse and rebel,You shall be devoured by the sword.\u201DFor
        the mouth of the Lord has spoken.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'How the faithful city has become a prostitute [idolatrous, despicable],She
        who was full of justice!Right standing with God once lodged in her,But now
        murderers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Your silver has turned to lead,Your wine is diluted with water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Your rulers are rebelsAnd companions of thieves;Everyone loves bribesAnd
        chases after gifts.They do not defend the fatherless,Nor does the widow\u2019s
        cause come before them [instead they delay or turn a deaf ear].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore the Lord God of hosts,The Mighty One of Israel, declares:\u201CAh,
        I will be freed of My adversariesAnd avenge Myself on My enemies.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And I will turn My hand against you,And will [thoroughly] purge away
        your dross as with lyeAnd remove all your tin (impurity).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then I will restore your judges as at the first,And your counselors
        as at the beginning;Afterward you will be called the city of righteousness,The
        faithful city.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Zion will be redeemed with justiceAnd her repentant ones with righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But rebels and sinners will be crushed and destroyed together,And
        those who abandon (turn away from) the Lord will be consumed (perish).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'For you will be ashamed [of the degradation] of the oaks in which
        you took [idolatrous] pleasure,And you will be ashamed of the gardens [of
        passion] which you have chosen [for pagan worship].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'For you will be like an oak whose leaf withers and diesAnd like a
        garden that has no water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: The strong man will become tinder,And his work a spark.So both will
        burn togetherAnd there will be none to quench them.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Universal Reign"
      title: "God\u2019s Universal Reign"
      number: 1
      content: '  The word [from God] which Isaiah son of Amoz saw [in a vision]
        concerning [the nation of] Judah and [its capital city] Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Now it will come to pass thatIn the last daysThe mountain of the
        house of the LordWill be [firmly] established as the highest of the mountains,And
        will be exalted above the hills;And all the nations will stream to it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And many peoples shall come and say,\u201CCome, let us go up to the
        mountain of the Lord,To the house (temple) of the God of Jacob;That He may
        teach us His waysAnd that we may walk in His paths.\u201DFor the law will
        go out from ZionAnd the word of the Lord from Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And He will judge between the nations,And will mediate [disputes]
        for many peoples;And they will beat their swords into plowshares and their
        spears into pruning hooks.Nation will not lift up the sword against nation,And
        never again will they learn war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'O house of Jacob, come, let us walk in the light of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Most certainly [Lord] You have abandoned your people, the house of
        Jacob,Because they are filled with influences from the east,And they are
        soothsayers [who foretell] like the Philistines;Also they strike bargains
        with the children of foreigners (pagans).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Their land has also been filled with silver and goldAnd there is
        no end to their treasures;Their land has also been filled with horsesAnd
        there is no end to their chariots.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their land has also been filled with idols;They worship the work
        of their hands,That which their own fingers have made.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So the common man has been humbled [before idols]And the man of importance
        has been degraded,Therefore do not forgive them [O Lord].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Go among the rocks and hide in the dustFrom the terror of the Lord
        and from the splendor of His majesty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: A Day of Reckoning Coming'
      title: A Day of Reckoning Coming
      number: 11
      content: 'The proud look of man will be degradedAnd the arrogance of men will
        be humbled,And the Lord alone will be exalted in that day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the Lord of hosts will have a day of reckoningAgainst all who
        are proud and arrogantAnd against all who are lifted up,That they may be
        degraded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the wrath of God will be against all the cedars of Lebanon [west
        of the Jordan] that are high and lifted up,Against all the oaks of Bashan
        [east of the Jordan],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Against all the high mountains,Against all the hills that are lifted
        up,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Against every high tower,Against every fortified wall,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Against all the ships of TarshishAnd against all the beautiful craft.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the pride of man will be humbledAnd the arrogance of men will
        be degraded;The Lord alone shall be exalted in that day,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And the idols will completely vanish (be abolished).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'They [the stricken, deprived of all in which they had trusted] will
        go into the caves of the rocksAnd into the holes of the ground [fleeing]From
        the terror and dread of the LordAnd from the splendor of His majesty,When
        He arises to terrify the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In that day men will throw away to the moles and to the batsTheir
        idols of silver and their idols of gold,Which they made for themselves [as
        objects] to worship,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'To go into the caverns of the rocks and into the clefts of the [ragged]
        cliffs [as they flee]From the terror and dread of the Lord and the splendor
        of His majesty,When He arises to terrify the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Stop regarding man, whose breath [of life] is in his nostrils [for
        so little time];For why should he be esteemed?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Will Remove the Leaders'
      title: God Will Remove the Leaders
      number: 1
      content: '  Listen carefully, the Lord God of hosts is removing from Jerusalem
        and from JudahBoth supply and support, the whole supply of breadAnd the whole
        supply of water;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The brave man and the warrior [He is also removing],The judge and
        the prophet,The diviner and the elder,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The captain of fifty and the man of honor,The counselor and the expert
        artisan,And the skillful enchanter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And I will make mere boys their princes,And capricious (impulsive,
        unpredictable) children will rule over them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And the people will be oppressed,Each one by another, and each one
        by his neighbor;The boy will be arrogant and insolent toward the elderAnd
        the vulgar (common) toward the honorable [person of rank].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "When a man takes hold of his brother in the house of his father,
        saying,\u201CYou have a robe, you shall be our judge and ruler,And this pile
        of ruins will be under your control,\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "He will protest on that day, saying,\u201CI will not be a governor;For
        in my house there is neither bread nor clothing;You should not make me a
        judge and ruler of the people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For Jerusalem has stumbled and Judah has fallen,Because their words
        and their actions are against the Lord,To rebel against His glorious presence
        and defiantly provoke Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Their partiality testifies against them,They display their sin like
        Sodom;They do not even hide it.Woe (judgment is coming) to them!For they
        have brought evil on themselves [as a reward].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Say to the righteous that it will go well with them,For they will
        eat the fruit of their [righteous] actions.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to the wicked! It shall go badly with him,For
        what his hand has done shall be done to him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: God Will Judge'
      title: God Will Judge
      number: 12
      content: 'O My people! Children are their oppressors,And women rule over them.O
        My people! Your leaders lead you astrayAnd confuse (destroy, swallow up)
        the direction of your paths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The Lord rises to contend,And stands to judge the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The Lord enters into judgment with the elders of His people and their
        princes,\u201CFor it is you who have devoured the vineyard [with your oppression,
        you have robbed the people and ruined the country];The plunder of the poor
        is in your houses.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Judah\u2019s Women Denounced"
      title: "Judah\u2019s Women Denounced"
      number: 15
      content: "What do you mean by crushing My peopleAnd grinding the face of the
        poor?\u201DDeclares the Lord God of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Moreover, the Lord said, \u201CBecause the daughters of Zion are
        proudAnd walk with outstretched necks and seductive (flirtatious, alluring)
        eyes,And trip along with mincing steps and an affected gaitAnd walk with
        jingling anklets on their feet,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore the Lord will afflict the crown of the head of the daughters
        of Zion with scabs [making them bald],And the Lord will expose their foreheads
        (send them into captivity).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day the Lord will take away the beauty of their anklets,
        [braided] caps, crescent [head] ornaments, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'dangling earrings, bracelets, and the hanging veils and scarves, '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'head wraps (turbans), [short, jingling] ankle chains, sashes, perfume
        boxes, amulets (charms), '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'signet [finger] rings, nose rings, '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'festival robes, outer tunics, shawls, handbags, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'hand mirrors, [fine linen] undergarments, headbands, and veils [covering
        the entire body].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Now it will come to pass that instead of the sweet fragrance of spices
        there will be [the stench of] rottenness;Instead of a belt, a rope;Instead
        of well-set hair, baldness;Instead of fine clothes, a robe of sackcloth;And
        branding [of captives by the scorching heat] instead of beauty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Your men will fall by the swordAnd your mighty men in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Jerusalem\u2019s gates will lament (cry out in grief) and mourn
        [as those who wail for the dead];And she, being ruined and desolate, will
        sit upon the ground."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Remnant Prepared'
      title: A Remnant Prepared
      number: 1
      content: "  And in that day seven women will take hold of one man, saying,
        \u201CWe will eat our own food and wear [and provide] our own clothes; only
        let us be called by your name; take away our shame [of being unmarried].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'In that day the Branch of the Lord will be splendid and glorious,
        and the fruit of the land will be excellent and lovely to those of Israel
        who have survived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "It will come to pass that he who is left in Zion and remains in Jerusalem
        will be called holy (set apart for God)\u2014everyone who is recorded for
        [eternal] life in Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'When the Lord has washed away the [moral] filth of the daughters
        of Zion and has cleansed the bloodstains of Jerusalem from her midst, by
        the spirit of judgment and by the spirit of burning, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'then the Lord will create over the entire site of Mount Zion and
        over her assemblies, a cloud by day, smoke, and the brightness of a flaming
        fire by night; for over all the glory and brilliance will be a canopy [a
        defense, a covering of His divine love and protection]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: And there will be a pavilion for shade from the heat by day, and a
        refuge and a shelter from the storm and the rain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Parable of the Vineyard'
      title: Parable of the Vineyard
      number: 1
      content: '  Now let me sing for my greatly Beloved [Lord]A song of my Beloved
        about His vineyard (His chosen people).My greatly Beloved had a vineyard
        on a very fertile slope (the promised land, Canaan).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He dug it all around and cleared away its stones,And planted it with
        the choicest vine (the people of Judah).And He built a tower in the center
        of it;And also hewed out a wine vat in it.Then He expected it to produce
        [the choicest] grapes,But it produced only worthless ones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CAnd now, says the Lord, O inhabitants of Jerusalem and men
        of Judah,Judge between Me and My vineyard (My people).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'What more could have been done for My vineyard that I have not done
        in it?When I expected it to produce good grapes, why did it yield worthless
        ones?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So now let me tell you what I am going to do to My vineyard:I will
        take away its thorn-hedge, and it will be burned up;I will break down its
        stone wall and it will be trampled down [by enemies].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will turn it into a wasteland;It will not be pruned or cultivated,But
        briars and thorns will come up.I will also command the clouds not to rain
        on it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Woes for the Wicked'
      title: Woes for the Wicked
      number: 7
      content: 'For the vineyard of the Lord of hosts is the house (nation) of IsraelAnd
        the men of Judah are His delightful planting [which He loves].So He looked
        for justice, but in fact, [He saw] bloodshed and lawlessness;[He looked]
        for righteousness, but in fact, [He heard] a cry of distress and oppression.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to those who join house to house and join
        field to field [to increase their holdings by depriving others],Until there
        is no more room [for others],So that you have to live alone in the midst
        of the land!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "In my ears the Lord of hosts said, \u201CBe assured that many houses
        will become desolate,  Even great and beautiful ones will be unoccupied.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For ten acres of vineyard will yield [only] one bath of wine,And
        a homer (six bushels) of seed will produce [only] one ephah of grain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to those who rise early in the morning to
        pursue intoxicating drink,Who stay up late in the night till wine inflames
        them!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They have lyre and harp, tambourine and flute, and wine at their
        feasts;But they do not regard nor even pay attention to the deeds of the
        Lord,Nor do they consider the work of His hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore My people go into exile because they lack knowledge [of
        God];And their honorable men are famished,And their common people are parched
        with thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore Sheol (the realm of the dead) has increased its appetite
        and opened its mouth beyond measure;And Jerusalem\u2019s splendor, her multitude,
        her [boisterous] uproar and her [drunken] revelers descend into it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So the common man will be bowed down and the man of importance degraded,And
        the eyes of the proud (arrogant) will be degraded.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'But the Lord of hosts will be exalted in justice,And God, the Holy
        One, will show Himself holy in righteousness [through His righteous judgments].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Then the lambs will graze [among the ruins] as in their own pasture,And
        strangers will eat in the desolate places of the [exiled] wealthy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to those who drag along wickedness with
        cords of falsehood,And sin as if with cart ropes [towing their own punishment];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Who say, \u201CLet Him move speedily, let Him expedite His work [His
        promised vengeance], so that we may see it;And let the purpose of the Holy
        One of Israel approachAnd come to pass, so that we may know it!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to those who call evil good, and good evil;Who
        substitute darkness for light and light for darkness;Who substitute bitter
        for sweet and sweet for bitter!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to those who are wise in their own eyesAnd
        clever and shrewd in their own sight!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Woe (judgment is coming) to those who are heroes at drinking wineAnd
        men of strength in mixing intoxicating drinks,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Who justify the wicked and acquit the guilty for a bribe,And take
        away the rights of those who are in the right!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Therefore, as the tongue of fire consumes the stubble [from straw]And
        the dry grass collapses into the flame,So their root will become like rot
        and their blossom blow away like fine dust;Because they have rejected the
        law of the Lord of hostsAnd despised and discarded the word of the Holy One
        of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Therefore the anger of the Lord has burned against His people,And
        He has stretched out His hand against them and has struck them down.And the
        mountains trembled, and their dead bodies lay like rubbish in the middle
        of the streets.In spite of all this God\u2019s anger is not turned away,But
        His hand is still stretched out [in judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He will lift up a flag to [call] the distant nations [to bring His
        judgment on Judah],And will whistle for them from the ends of the earth;And
        indeed, they will come with great speed swiftly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'No one among them is weary or stumbles,No one slumbers or sleeps;Nor
        is the belt at their waist undone [as if unprepared for action],Nor is the
        strap of their sandal broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Their arrows are sharp and all their bows are strung and bent;Their
        horses\u2019 hoofs seem like flint and their chariot wheels like a whirlwind.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Their roaring is like a lioness, they roar like young lions;They
        growl and seize their preyAnd carry it off and there is no one to save it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: And in that day they will roar against them (Judah) like the roaring
        of the sea.And if one looks to the land, in fact, there is darkness and distress;Even
        the light will be darkened by its clouds.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Isaiah\u2019s Vision"
      title: "Isaiah\u2019s Vision"
      number: 1
      content: '  In the year that King Uzziah died, I saw [in a vision] the Lord
        sitting on a throne, high and exalted, with the train of His royal robe filling
        the [most holy part of the] temple. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Above Him seraphim (heavenly beings) stood; each one had six wings:
        with two wings he covered his face, with two wings he covered his feet, and
        with two wings he flew. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And one called out to another, saying,\u201CHoly, Holy, Holy is the
        Lord of hosts;The whole earth is filled with His glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the foundations of the thresholds trembled at the voice of him
        who called out, and the temple was filling with smoke. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then I said,\u201CWoe is me! For I am ruined,Because I am a man of
        [ceremonially] unclean lips,And I live among a people of unclean lips;For
        my eyes have seen the King, the Lord of hosts.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then one of the seraphim flew to me with a burning coal in his hand,
        which he had taken from the altar with tongs. '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Isaiah\u2019s Commission"
      title: "Isaiah\u2019s Commission"
      number: 7
      content: "He touched my mouth with it and said, \u201CListen carefully, this
        has touched your lips; your wickedness [your sin, your injustice, your wrongdoing]
        is taken away and your sin atoned for and forgiven.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then I heard the voice of the Lord, saying, \u201CWhom shall I send,
        and who will go for Us?\u201D Then I said, \u201CHere am I. Send me!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And He said, \u201CGo, and tell this people:\u2018Keep on listening,
        but do not understand;Keep on looking, but do not comprehend.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Make the heart of this people insensitive,Their ears dull,And their
        eyes dim,Otherwise they might see with their eyes,Hear with their ears,Understand
        with their hearts,And return and be healed.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then I said, \u201CLord, how long?\u201D And He answered,\u201CUntil
        cities are devastated and without inhabitant,And houses are without peopleAnd
        the land is utterly desolate,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The Lord has removed [His] people far away,And there are many deserted
        places in the midst of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And though a tenth [of the people] remain in the land,It will again
        be subject to destruction [consumed and burned],Like a massive terebinth
        tree or like an oakWhose stump remains when it is chopped down.The holy seed
        [the elect remnant] is its stump [the substance of Israel].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: War against Jerusalem'
      title: War against Jerusalem
      number: 1
      content: '  Now it came to pass in the days of Ahaz the son of Jotham, the
        son of Uzziah, king of Judah, that Rezin king of Aram (Syria) and Pekah the
        son of Remaliah, king of Israel, went up to Jerusalem to wage war against
        it, but they could not conquer it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "When the house of David (Judah) was told, \u201CAram is allied with
        Ephraim (Israel),\u201D the hearts of Ahaz and his people trembled as the
        trees of the forest tremble in the wind.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then the Lord said to Isaiah, \u201CGo out to meet Ahaz [king of
        Judah], you and your son Shear-jashub, at the end of the aqueduct of the
        Upper Pool, on the highway to the Fuller\u2019s Field; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "and say to him, \u2018Take care and be calm, do not fear and be weak-hearted
        because of these two stumps of smoldering logs, on account of the fierce
        anger of [King] Rezin and Aram and of the son of Remaliah (Pekah, usurper
        of the throne of Israel). "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Because Aram, along with Ephraim (Israel) and the son of Remaliah,
        have planned evil against you (Judah), saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CLet us go up against Judah and terrorize it; and let us breach
        its wall and tear it apart [each of us taking a portion] and set up the son
        of Tabeel over it as its [puppet] king,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "for this is what the Lord God says, \u201CIt shall not stand nor
        shall it happen. "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the head (capital) of Aram is Damascus and the head of Damascus
        is [King] Rezin (now within sixty-five years Ephraim will be broken to pieces
        and will no longer be a people). '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Child Immanuel'
      title: The Child Immanuel
      number: 9
      content: "And the head (capital) of Ephraim is Samaria, and the head of Samaria
        is Remaliah\u2019s son [King Pekah]. If you will not believe [and trust in
        God and His message], be assured that you will not be established.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then the Lord spoke again to [King] Ahaz, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAsk a sign for yourself from the Lord your God [one that will
        convince you that God has spoken and will keep His word]; make your request
        as deep as Sheol or as high as heaven.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But Ahaz said, \u201CI will not ask, nor will I test the Lord!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CHear then, O house of David! Is it too small
        a thing for you to try the patience of men, but will you try the patience
        of my God as well? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the Lord Himself will give you a sign: Listen carefully,
        the virgin will conceive and give birth to a son, and she will call his name
        Immanuel (God with us). '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He will eat curds and honey when he knows enough to refuse evil and
        choose good. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Trials to Come for Judah'
      title: Trials to Come for Judah
      number: 16
      content: 'For before the child will know enough to refuse evil and choose good,
        the land (Canaan) whose two kings you dread will be deserted [both Ephraim
        and Aram].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The Lord will bring on you, on your people, and on your father\u2019s
        house such days as have not come since the day that Ephraim (the ten northern
        tribes) separated from Judah\u2014[He will call for] the king of Assyria.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day the Lord will whistle for the fly that is in the mouth
        of the rivers and canals of Egypt and for the bee that is in the land of
        Assyria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These [armies, like flies and bees] will all come and settle on the
        steep and rugged ravines and in the clefts of the rocks, and on all the thorn
        bushes and in all the watering places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'In that day [when foreign armies swarm the land] the Lord will shave
        with a razor, hired from the regions beyond the Euphrates (that is, with
        the king of Assyria), [that razor will shave] the head and the hair of the
        legs; and it will also remove the beard [leaving Judah stripped, shamed and
        scorned].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Now in that day [because of the poverty caused by the invaders] a
        man will keep alive only a young milk cow and two sheep; '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'and because of the abundance of milk produced he will eat curds,
        for everyone that is left in the land will eat [only] curds and [wild] honey.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And it will come to pass in that day, in every place where there
        used to be a thousand vines, worth a thousand silver shekels, there will
        be briars and thorns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'People will come there [to hunt] with arrows and with bows because
        all the land will be briars and thorns. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: As for all the hills which used to be cultivated with the pick and
        the hoe, you will no longer go there for fear of briars and thorns; but they
        will become a place where oxen are pastured and where sheep tread.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Damascus and Samaria Fall'
      title: Damascus and Samaria Fall
      number: 1
      content: "  Then the Lord said to me, \u201CTake for yourself a large tablet
        [for public display] and write on it in ordinary characters: Belonging to
        Maher-shalal-hash-baz. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And I will get faithful witnesses to attest [to this prophecy] for
        me, Uriah the priest and Zechariah the son of Jeberechiah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "So I approached [my wife] the prophetess, and she conceived and gave
        birth to a son. Then the Lord said to me, \u201CName him Maher-shalal-hash-baz
        [to remind the people of the prophecy]; "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "for before the boy knows how to say, \u2018My father\u2019 or \u2018My
        mother,\u2019 the riches of Damascus (Aram\u2019s capital) and the spoil
        of Samaria (Israel\u2019s capital) will be carried away by the king of Assyria.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Again the Lord spoke to me, saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CBecause these people (Judah) have refused the gently flowing
        waters of ShiloahAnd rejoice in Rezin [the king of Aram] and Remaliah\u2019s
        son [Pekah the king of Israel],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Now therefore, listen carefully, the Lord is about to bring on them
        the waters of the [Euphrates] River, strong and abundant\u2014The king of
        Assyria and all his glory;And it will rise over all its channels and canals
        and go far beyond its banks.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: A Believing Remnant'
      title: A Believing Remnant
      number: 8
      content: 'Then it will sweep on into Judah; it will overflow and pass through
        [the hills],Reaching even to the neck [of which Jerusalem is the head],And
        its outstretched wings (the armies of Assyria) will fill the width of Your
        land, O Immanuel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CBe broken [in pieces], O peoples, and be shattered!Listen,
        all you [our enemies from the] far countries.Prepare yourselves [for war],
        and be shattered;Prepare yourselves [for war], and be shattered.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Take counsel together [against Judah], but it will come to nothing;Speak
        the word, but it will not stand,For God is with us (Immanuel).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'For in this way the Lord spoke to me with His strong hand [upon me]
        and instructed me not to walk in the way of this people [behaving as they
        do], saying,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CYou are not to say, \u2018It is a conspiracy!\u2019In regard
        to all that this people call a conspiracy,And you are not to fear what they
        fear nor be in dread of it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'It is the Lord of hosts whom you are to regard as holy and awesome.He
        shall be your [source of] fear,He shall be your [source of] dread [not man].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then He shall be a sanctuary [a sacred, indestructible shelter for
        those who fear and trust Him];But to both the houses of Israel [both the
        northern and southern kingdoms\u2014Israel and Judah, He will be] a stone
        on which to stumble and a rock on which to trip,A trap and a snare for the
        inhabitants of Jerusalem.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Many [among them] will stumble over them;Then they will fall and
        be broken,They will even be snared and trapped.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Bind up the testimony, seal the law and the teaching among my (Isaiah\u2019s)
        disciples. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And I will wait for the Lord who is hiding His face from the house
        of Jacob; and I will look eagerly for Him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Listen carefully, I and the children whom the Lord has given me are
        for signs and wonders [that will occur] in Israel from the Lord of hosts,
        who dwells on Mount Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "When the people [instead of trusting God] say to you, \u201CConsult
        the mediums [who try to talk to the dead] and the soothsayers who chirp and
        whisper and mutter,\u201D should not a people consult their God? Should they
        consult the dead on behalf of the living? "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: '[Direct those people] to the law and to the testimony! If their teachings
        are not in accord with this word, it is because they have no dawn. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They [who consult mediums and soothsayers] will pass through the
        land deeply distressed and hungry, and when they are hungry, they will become
        enraged and will curse their king and their God as they look upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then they will look to the earth, they will see only distress and
        darkness, the gloom of anguish; and they will be driven away into darkness
        and overwhelming night.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Birth and Reign of the Prince of Peace'
      title: Birth and Reign of the Prince of Peace
      number: 1
      content: '  But there will be no more gloom for her who was in anguish [for
        with judgment comes the promise of salvation]. In earlier times He treated
        the land of Zebulun and the land of Naphtali with contempt, but later on
        He will make them honored [by the presence of the Messiah], by the way of
        the sea, on the other side of Jordan, Galilee of the Gentiles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The people who walk in [spiritual] darkness  Will see a great Light;Those
        who live in the dark land,The Light will shine on them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You [O God] will increase the nation,You will multiply their joy;They
        will rejoice before YouLike the joy and jubilation of the harvest,As men
        rejoice when they divide the spoil [of victory].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For You will break the yoke of Israel\u2019s burden and the staff
        (goad) on their shoulders,The rod of their oppressor, as at the battle of
        Midian.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "For every boot of the marching warrior in the battle tumult,And [every
        soldier\u2019s] garment rolled in blood, will be used for burning, fuel for
        the fire.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For to us a Child shall be born, to us a Son shall be given;And the
        government shall be upon His shoulder,And His name shall be called Wonderful
        Counselor, Mighty God,Everlasting Father, Prince of Peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: God\u2019s Anger with Israel\u2019s Arrogance"
      title: "God\u2019s Anger with Israel\u2019s Arrogance"
      number: 7
      content: 'There shall be no end to the increase of His government and of peace,[He
        shall rule] on the throne of David and over his kingdom,To establish it and
        to uphold it with justice and righteousnessFrom that time forward and forevermore.The
        zeal of the Lord of hosts will accomplish this.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The Lord sends a word (message) against Jacob,And it falls on Israel
        [the ten northern tribes, the kingdom of Ephraim].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And all the people know it,  That is,  Ephraim and the inhabitants
        of Samaria [its capital],Who say in pride and arrogance of heart:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CThe bricks have fallen down,But we will rebuild [all the better]
        with ashlar (hewed stones);The sycamores have been cut down,But we will replace
        them with [expensive] cedars.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore the Lord raises against Ephraim adversaries from Rezin
        [king of Aram]And spurs their enemies on,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The Arameans on the east and the Philistines on the west;And they
        devour Israel with gaping jaws.In spite of all this, God\u2019s anger does
        not turn awayBut His hand is still stretched out [in judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Yet the people do not turn back [in repentance] to Him who struck
        them,Nor do they seek the Lord of hosts [as their most essential need].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore the Lord cuts off head and tail [the highest and the lowest]
        from Israel,  Both [the high] palm branch and [the low] bulrush in one day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The elderly and honorable man, he is the head;And the prophet who
        teaches lies, he is the tail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For those who lead this people are causing them to go astray;And
        those who are led [astray] by them are swallowed up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Therefore the Lord does not rejoice over their young men,Nor does
        He have compassion on their fatherless or their widows;For every one of them
        is godless and an evildoer,And every mouth is speaking foolishness.In spite
        of all this, God\u2019s anger does not turn awayBut His hand is still stretched
        out [in judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For wickedness burns like a fire;It consumes briars and thorns,It
        even sets the forest thickets ablaze;And it swirls upward in a column of
        smoke.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'By the wrath of the Lord of hosts the land is burned up,And the people
        are like fuel for the fire;No man spares his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'They slice off [in discord] what is on the right hand but are still
        hungry,And they eat what is on the left hand but they are not satisfied;Each
        eats the flesh of his own arm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "[The tribe of] Manasseh devours [the tribe of his brother] Ephraim,
        and Ephraim Manasseh,And together they are against Judah (the southern kingdom,
        the house of David).In spite of all this, God\u2019s anger does not turn
        awayBut His hand is still stretched out [in judgment]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Assyria Is God\u2019s Instrument"
      title: "Assyria Is God\u2019s Instrument"
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to those [judges] who issue evil statutes,And
        to those [magistrates] who constantly record unjust and oppressive decisions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So as to deprive the needy of justiceAnd rob the poor of My people
        of rightful claims,So that widows may be their spoilAnd that they may plunder
        the fatherless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Now what will you do in the day of [God\u2019s] punishment,And in
        the storm of devastation which will come from far away?To whom will you flee
        for help?And where will you leave your wealth [for safekeeping]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nothing remains but to crouch among the captivesOr fall [dead] among
        the slain [on the battlefield].In spite of all this, God\u2019s anger does
        not turn away,But His hand is still stretched out [in judgment].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Woe to Assyria, the rod of My anger [against Israel],The staff in
        whose hand is My indignation and fury [against Israel\u2019s disobedience]!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I send Assyria against a godless nationAnd commission it against
        the people of My wrathTo take the spoil and to seize the plunder,And to trample
        them down like mud in the streets.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Yet it is not Assyria\u2019s intention [to do My will],Nor does it
        plan so in its heart,But instead it is its purpose to destroyAnd to cut off
        many nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For Assyria says, \u201CAre not my princes all kings?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Is not Calno [conquered] like Carchemish [on the Euphrates]?Is not
        Hamath [subdued] like Arpad [her neighbor]?Is not Samaria [in Israel] like
        Damascus [in Aram]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'As my hand has reached to the kingdoms of the idols,Whose carved
        images were greater and more feared than those of Jerusalem and Samaria,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Shall I not do to Jerusalem and her imagesJust as I have done to
        Samaria and her idols?\u201D [declares Assyria].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So when the Lord has completed all His work [of judgment] on Mount
        Zion and on Jerusalem, He will say, \u201CI will punish the fruit [the thoughts,
        the declarations, and the actions] of the arrogant heart of the king of Assyria
        and the haughtiness of his pride.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For the Assyrian king has said,\u201CI have done this by the power
        of my [own] hand and by my wisdom,For I have understanding and skill.I have
        removed the boundaries of the peoplesAnd have plundered their treasures;Like
        a bull I have brought down those who sat on thrones.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "My hand has found the wealth of the people like a nest,And as one
        gathers eggs that are abandoned, so I have gathered all the earth;And there
        was not one that flapped its wing, or that opened its beak and chirped.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Is the axe able to lift itself over the one who chops with it?Is
        the saw able to magnify itself over the one who wields it?  That would be
        like a club moving those who lift it,Or like a staff raising him who is not
        [made of] wood [like itself]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Therefore the Lord, the God of hosts, will send a wasting disease
        among the stout warriors of Assyria;And under his glory a fire will be kindled
        like a burning flame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And the Light of Israel will become a fire and His Holy One a flame,And
        it will burn and devour Assyria\u2019s thorns and briars in a single day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "The Lord will consume the glory of Assyria\u2019s forest and of its
        fruitful garden, both soul and body,And it will be as when a sick man wastes
        away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: A Remnant Will Return'
      title: A Remnant Will Return
      number: 19
      content: "And the remaining trees of Assyria\u2019s forest will be so few in
        numberThat a child could write them down.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now in that day the remnant of Israel, and those of the house of
        Jacob who have escaped, will never again rely on the one who struck them,
        but will truly rely on the Lord, the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'A remnant will return, a remnant of Jacob, to the mighty God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For though your people, O Israel, may be as the sand of the sea, 
        Only a remnant within them will return;The destruction is determined [it
        is decided and destined for completion], overflowing with justice (righteous
        punishment).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For the Lord, the God of hosts, will execute a complete destruction,
        one that is decreed, in the midst of all the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Therefore, the Lord God of hosts says this, \u201CO My people who
        dwell in Zion, do not be afraid of the Assyrian who strikes you with a rod
        and lifts up his staff against you, as [the king of] Egypt did. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For yet a very little while and My indignation [against you] will
        be fulfilled and My anger will be directed toward the destruction of the
        Assyrian.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The Lord of hosts will brandish a whip against them like the slaughter
        of Midian at the rock of Oreb; and His staff will be over the [Red] Sea and
        He will lift it up the way He did in [the flight from] Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So it will be in that day, that the burden of the Assyrian will be
        removed from your shoulders and his yoke from your neck. The yoke will be
        broken because of the fat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The Assyrian has come against Aiath [in Judah],He has passed through
        Migron [with his army];At Michmash he stored his equipment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "They have gone through the pass, saying,\u201CGeba will be our lodging
        place for the night.\u201DRamah trembles, and Gibeah [the city] of Saul has
        fled.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Cry aloud with your voice [in consternation], O Daughter of Gallim!Pay
        attention, Laishah! Answer her, Anathoth!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Madmenah has fled;The inhabitants of Gebim have fled [with their
        belongings] to safety.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'Yet today the Assyrian will halt at Nob [the city of priests];He
        shakes his fist at the mountain of the Daughter of Zion, at the hill of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'Listen carefully, the Lord, the God of hosts, will lop off the [beautiful]
        boughs with terrifying force;The tall in stature will be cut downAnd the
        lofty will be abased and humiliated.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He will cut down the thickets of the forest with an iron axe,And Lebanon
        (the Assyrian) will fall by the Mighty One.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Righteous Reign of the Branch'
      title: Righteous Reign of the Branch
      number: 1
      content: "  Then a Shoot (the Messiah) will spring from the stock of Jesse
        [David\u2019s father],And a Branch from his roots will bear fruit.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the Spirit of the Lord will rest on Him\u2014The Spirit of wisdom
        and understanding,The Spirit of counsel and strength,The Spirit of knowledge
        and of the [reverential and obedient] fear of the Lord\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And He will delight in the fear of the Lord,And He will not judge
        by what His eyes see,Nor make decisions by what His ears hear;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But with righteousness and justice He will judge the poor,And decide
        with fairness for the downtrodden of the earth;And He shall strike the earth
        with the rod of His mouth,And with the breath of His lips He shall slay the
        wicked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And righteousness will be the belt around His loins,And faithfulness
        the belt around His waist.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the wolf will dwell with the lamb,And the leopard will lie down
        with the young goat,And the calf and the young lion and the fatted steer
        together;And a little child will lead them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the cow and the bear will graze [together],Their young will lie
        down together,And the lion shall eat straw like the ox.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the nursing child will [safely] play over the hole of the cobra,And
        the weaned child will put his hand on the viper\u2019s den [and not be hurt].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They will not hurt or destroy in all My holy mountain,For the earth
        will be full of the knowledge of the LordAs the waters cover the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: The Restored Remnant'
      title: The Restored Remnant
      number: 10
      content: 'Then in that dayThe nations will make supplications to the Root of
        JesseWho will stand as a signal for the peoples;And His resting place will
        be glorious.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then it will happen on that day that the LordWill again acquire with
        His hand a second timeThe remnant of His people, who will remain,From Assyria,
        from [Lower] Egypt, from Pathros, from Cush (Ethiopia), from Elam [in Persia],
        from Shinar [Babylonia], from Hamath [in Aram],And from the coastlands bordering
        the [Mediterranean] Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And He will lift up a signal for the nationsAnd assemble the outcasts
        of Israel,And will gather the dispersed of JudahFrom the four corners of
        the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Then the jealousy of Ephraim will depart,And those who harass Judah
        will be cut off;Ephraim will not be jealous of Judah,And Judah will not harass
        Ephraim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ephraim and Judah will [unite and] swoop down on the slopes of the
        Philistines toward the west;Together they will plunder the sons (Arabs) of
        the east.They will possess Edom and Moab,And the sons of Ammon will be subject
        to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And the Lord will utterly destroyThe tongue of the Sea of Egypt;And
        with His scorching windHe will wave His hand over the River;He will strike
        and divide it into seven channelsAnd make [it possible for] people [to] walk
        over in sandals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: And there will be a highway from AssyriaFor the remnant of His people
        who will be left,Just as there was for IsraelIn the day when they came up
        out of the land of Egypt.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Thanksgiving Expressed'
      title: Thanksgiving Expressed
      number: 1
      content: "  And on that day you will say,\u201CI will give thanks to You, O
        Lord;For though You were angry with me,Your anger has turned away,And You
        comfort me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Behold, God, my salvation!I will trust and not be afraid,For the
        Lord God is my strength and song;Yes, He has become my salvation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore with joy you will draw waterFrom the springs of salvation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And in that day you will say,\u201CGive thanks to the Lord, call
        on His name [in prayer].Make His deeds known among the peoples [of the earth];Proclaim
        [to them] that His name is exalted!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Sing praises to the Lord, for He has done excellent and glorious
        things;Let this be known throughout the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: Rejoice and shout for joy, O inhabitant of Zion,For great in your
        midst is the Holy One of Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecies about Babylon'
      title: Prophecies about Babylon
      number: 1
      content: '  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Babylon which Isaiah the son of Amoz saw [in a prophetic vision]:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Lift up a signal banner on the bare mountain,Summon them [the Medes
        and Persians] with a loud voice,Wave the [beckoning] hand so that they may
        enter the doorways of the [Babylonian] nobles.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I [the Lord] have commanded My consecrated ones,I have even called
        My great warriors,My proudly exulting ones [the Medes and the Persians who
        triumph for My honor]\u2014To execute My anger.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'A sound of tumult on the mountains,Like that of many people!A sound
        of the uproar of the kingdoms,Of nations gathered together!The Lord of hosts
        is mustering an army for battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: Judgment on the Day of the Lord'
      title: Judgment on the Day of the Lord
      number: 5
      content: "They are coming from a distant country,From the end of heaven [the
        farthest horizon]\u2014The Lord and the weapons of His indignation\u2014To
        destroy the whole land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Wail, for the day of the Lord is at hand!It will come as destruction
        from the Almighty (All Sufficient One\u2014Invincible God)!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Therefore all hands will fall limp,And every man\u2019s heart will
        melt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'They [of Babylon] will be shocked and terrified,Pains and anguish
        will grip them;They will be in pain like a woman in childbirth.They will
        stare aghast and horrified at one another,Their faces aflame [from the effects
        of the unprecedented warfare].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Listen carefully, the day of the Lord is coming,Cruel, with wrath
        and raging anger,To make the land a horror [of devastation];And He shall
        exterminate its sinners from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the stars of heaven and their constellationsWill not flash with
        their light;The sun will be dark when it rises,And the moon will not shed
        its light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In this way I will punish the world for its evilAnd the wicked for
        their wickedness [their sin, their injustice, their wrongdoing];I will also
        put an end to the arrogance of the proudAnd will abase the arrogance of the
        tyrant.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will make mortal man more rare than fine gold,And mankind [scarcer]
        than the pure gold of Ophir.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore I will make the heavens tremble;And the earth will be shaken
        from its placeAt the wrath of the Lord of hostsIn the day of His burning
        anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And like the hunted gazelle,Or like sheep that no man gathers,Each
        [foreign resident] will turn [and go back] to his own people,And each one
        flee to his own land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Anyone who is found will be pierced through,And anyone who is captured
        will fall by the sword.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Babylon Will Fall to the Medes'
      title: Babylon Will Fall to the Medes
      number: 16
      content: 'Their children also will be smashed to piecesBefore their eyes;Their
        houses will be lootedAnd their wives ravished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Listen carefully, I will put the Medes [in motion] against them,Who
        have no regard for silver and do not delight in gold [and therefore cannot
        be bribed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their bows will cut down the young men [of Babylon];They will take
        no pity on the fruit of the womb,Their eyes will not look with compassion
        on the children.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Babylon, the glory of kingdoms, the beauty of the Chaldeans\u2019
        pride,Will be like Sodom and Gomorrah when God overthrew them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Babylon will never be inhabited or lived in from generation to generation;Nor
        will the Arab pitch his tent there,Nor will the shepherds let their sheep
        lie down there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But desert creatures will lie down there,And their houses will be
        full of owls;Ostriches also will live there, and wild goats will dance there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "  Hyenas will howl in their castles,And jackals in their luxurious
        palaces.Babylon\u2019s time has nearly come,And her days will not be prolonged."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Taunt"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Taunt"
      number: 1
      content: '  For the Lord will have compassion on Jacob (the captives in Babylon)
        and will again choose Israel, and will settle them in their own land. Foreigners
        (Gentiles) will join them [as proselytes] and will attach themselves to the
        house of Jacob (Israel). '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The peoples will take them along and bring them to their own place
        (Judea), and the house of Israel will possess them as an inheritance in the
        land of the Lord as male and female servants; and they will take captive
        those whose captives they have been, and they will rule over their [former]
        oppressors.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it will be in the day when the Lord gives you rest from your
        pain and turmoil and from the harsh service in which you have been enslaved, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "that you will take up this taunt against the king of Babylon, and
        say,\u201CHow the oppressor has ceased [his insolence],  And how the fury
        has ceased!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord has broken the staff of the wicked,The scepter of the [tyrant]
        rulers  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Which used to strike the peoples in anger with incessant blows,Which
        subdued and ruled the nations in wrath with unrelenting persecution.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The whole earth is at rest and is quiet;They break into shouts of
        joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Even the cypress trees rejoice over you [kings of Babylon], even
        the cedars of Lebanon, saying,\u2018Since you were laid low, no woodcutter
        comes up against us.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  Sheol below is excited about you to meet you when you come [you
        tyrant of Babylon];It stirs up the spirits of the dead [to greet you], all
        the leaders of the earth;It raises all the kings of the nations from their
        thrones [in astonishment at your fall].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "All of them will respond [tauntingly] and say to you,\u2018You have
        become as weak as we are.You have become like us.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Your pomp and magnificence have been brought down to Sheol,Along
        with the music of your harps;The maggots [which prey on the dead] are spread
        out under you [as a bed]And worms are your covering [Babylonian rulers].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'How you have fallen from heaven,O star of the morning [light-bringer],
        son of the dawn!You have been cut down to the ground,You who have weakened
        the nations [king of Babylon]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "But you said in your heart,\u2018I will ascend to heaven;I will raise
        my throne above the stars of God;I will sit on the mount of assemblyIn the
        remote parts of the north.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "I will ascend above the heights of the clouds;I will make myself
        like the Most High.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'But [in fact] you will be brought down to Sheol,To the remote recesses
        of the pit (the region of the dead).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Those who see you will gaze at you,They will consider you, saying,\u2018Is
        this the man who made the earth tremble,Who shook kingdoms,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Who made the world like a wildernessAnd overthrew its cities,Who
        did not permit his prisoners to return home?\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'All the kings of the nations, all of them lie [dead] in glorious
        array,Each one in his own sepulcher.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But you [king of Babylon] have been cast out of your tomb (denied
        burial)Like a rejected branch,Clothed with the slain who are pierced by the
        sword,Who go down to the stones of the pit [into which carcasses are thrown],Like
        a dead body trampled [underfoot].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You will not be united with them in burial,Because you have destroyed
        your land,You have slain your people.May the descendants of evildoers never
        be named!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Prepare a slaughtering place for his sonsBecause of the wickedness
        [the sin, the injustice, the wrongdoing] of their fathers.They must not rise
        and take possession of the earth,And fill the face of the world with cities.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CI will rise up against them,\u201D says the Lord of hosts,
        \u201Cand will cut off from Babylon name and survivors, and son and grandson,\u201D
        declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: Judgment on Assyria'
      title: Judgment on Assyria
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CI will also make Babylon a possession of the hedgehog and of
        swamps of water, and I will sweep it away with the broom of destruction,\u201D
        declares the Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "The Lord of hosts has sworn [an oath], saying, \u201CJust as I have
        intended, so it has certainly happened, and just as I have planned, so it
        will stand\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "to break the Assyrian in My land, and on My mountains I will trample
        him underfoot. Then the Assyrian\u2019s yoke will be removed from them (the
        people of Judah) and his burden removed from their shoulder. "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'This is the plan [of God] decided for the whole earth [regarded as
        conquered and put under tribute by Assyria]; and this is the hand [of God]
        that is stretched out over all the nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Judgment on Philistia'
      title: Judgment on Philistia
      number: 27
      content: "For the Lord of hosts has decided and planned, and who can annul
        it? His hand is stretched out, and who can turn it back?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'In the year that King Ahaz [of Judah] died this [mournful, inspired]
        oracle (a burden to be carried) came:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CDo not rejoice, O Philistia, any of you,Because the rod [of
        Judah] that struck you is broken;For out of the serpent\u2019s root will
        come a viper [King Hezekiah of Judah],And its offspring will be a flying
        serpent.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The firstborn of the helpless [of Judah] will feed [on My meadows],And
        the needy will lie down in safety;But I will kill your root with famine,And
        your survivors will be put to death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Howl, O gate; cry, O city!Melt away, O Philistia, all of you;For
        smoke comes out of the north,And there is no straggler in his ranks and no
        one stands detached [in Hezekiah\u2019s battalions].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "Then what answer will one give the messengers of the [Philistine]
        nation?That the Lord has founded Zion,And the afflicted of His people will
        seek and find refuge in it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on Moab'
      title: Judgment on Moab
      number: 1
      content: '  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Moab:Because in a night Ar of Moab is devastated and ruined;Because in a
        night Kir of Moab is devastated and ruined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "They have gone up to the temple and to Dibon, to the high places
        to weep.Moab wails over Nebo and over Medeba;Everyone\u2019s head is shaved,
        and every beard is cut off [in mourning].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'In their streets they have wrapped themselves with sackcloth;On their
        [flat] housetops and in their open squaresEveryone is wailing, dissolved
        in tears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Heshbon and Elealeh [cities claimed by Moab] cry out;Their voice
        is heard as far as Jahaz.Therefore the armed men of Moab cry out;Moab\u2019s
        soul trembles within him.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My heart cries out for Moab;His fugitives are [fleeing] as far as
        Zoar and Eglath-shelishiyah.For they go up the ascent of Luhith weeping;For
        on the road to Horonaim they raise a cry of distress over their destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the waters of Nimrim are desolate.Indeed the grass is withered,
        the new growth dies;There is no green thing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore the abundance which they have acquired and stored awayThey
        carry off over the Brook of the Willows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the cry of distress has echoed around the territory of Moab;The
        wailing goes as far as Eglaim and the mournful cry to Beer-elim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "For the waters of Dimon are full of blood;Yet I will bring even more
        woes on Dimon\u2014A lion upon those of Moab who escape and upon the remnant
        of the land."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Prophecy of Moab\u2019s Devastation"
      title: "Prophecy of Moab\u2019s Devastation"
      number: 1
      content: '  Send lambs to the ruler of the land [you Moabites],From Sela [that
        is, Petra in Edom] through the wilderness to the mountain of the Daughter
        of Zion (Jerusalem).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For like wandering birds or scattered nestlings,The daughters of
        Moab will be at the fords of the [river] Arnon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "[Say to the ruler] \u201CGive us advice, make a decision [for Moab,
        king of Judah];Cast your shadow [over us] like night in the midst of noon;Hide
        the outcasts, do not betray the fugitive [to his pursuer].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Let our outcasts of Moab live among you;Be a [sheltered] hiding place
        to them from the destroyer.\u201DFor the extortioner has come to an end,
        destruction has ceased,Oppressors [who trample men] have completely disappeared
        from the land,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'A throne will be established in lovingkindness,And One will sit on
        it in faithfulness in the tent (dynasty, family) of David;Judging and seeking
        justiceAnd being prompt to do righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "We have heard of the pride of Moab, an excessive pride\u2014Even
        of his arrogance, his conceit, his rage,His untruthful boasting.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Therefore Moab will wail for Moab; everyone will wail.You will mourn
        for the raisin cakes of Kir-hareseth,As those who are utterly stricken and
        discouraged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For the fields of Heshbon have languished and withered, and the vines
        of Sibmah as well;The lords of the nations have trampled down [Moab\u2019s]
        choice vine branches,Which reached as far as Jazer and wandered into the
        wilderness;Its tendrils stretched out, they passed over [the shores of] the
        [Dead] Sea.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore I (Isaiah) will weep bitterly for Jazer, for the vines
        of Sibmah.I will drench you with my tears, O Heshbon and Elealeh;For the
        war-cry [of the enemy] has fallen on your summer fruits and your harvest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Gladness and joy are taken away from the fruitful field;In the vineyards
        there will be no singing or joyful sound;No treader treads out wine in the
        presses,For I (God) put an end to the joyful shouting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore my heart sounds like a harp [in mournful compassion] for
        Moab,And my inner being mourns for Kir-hareseth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'So it will come to pass when Moab presents himself,When he wearies
        himself [worshiping] on his high place [of idolatry]And comes to his sanctuary
        [of Chemosh, god of Moab] to pray,That he will not prevail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "This is the word which the Lord spoke earlier concerning Moab [when
        Moab\u2019s pride and resistance to God were first known]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But now the Lord speaks, saying, \u201CWithin three years, as the
        years of a hired man [who will not serve longer than the agreed time], the
        glory of Moab will be degraded along with all the great population, and the
        remnant [that survives] will be very small and of no account.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy about Damascus'
      title: Prophecy about Damascus
      number: 1
      content: "  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Damascus [capital of Aram (Syria), and Israel\u2019s defense against Assyria].\u201CListen
        carefully, Damascus will cease to be a cityAnd will become a fallen ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The cities of Aroer [east of the Jordan] are deserted;They will be
        [only a refuge] for flocks to lie down in,And there will be no one to make
        them afraid.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The fortified city will disappear from Ephraim,And the kingdom from
        DamascusAnd the remnant of Aram (Syria);They will be like the [departed]
        glory of [her ally] the children of Israel,\u201DDeclares the Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CNow in that day the [former] glory of Jacob [Israel\u2014his
        might, his population, his prosperity] will fade,And the fatness of his flesh
        will become lean.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And it will be like the reaper gathering the standing grain,As his
        arm harvests the ears of grain;Yes, it will be like one gleaning ears of
        grainIn the [fertile] Valley of Rephaim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Yet gleanings will be left in the land [of Israel] like the shaking
        of the olive tree,Two or three olives on the topmost branch,Four or five
        on the [outermost] branches of the fruitful tree,\u201DDeclares the Lord,
        the God of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'In that day man will have regard for his Maker,And his eyes will
        regard the Holy One of Israel [with awe-inspired reverence].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And he will not have regard for the [idolatrous] altars, the work
        of his hands,Nor will he look to that which his fingers have made,Neither
        the Asherim (symbols of the goddess Asherah) nor the incense altars.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In that day the strong cities of Aram and Israel will be like deserted
        places in the forest,Or like branches which they abandoned before the children
        of Israel;And the land will be a desolation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Because you [Judah] have forgotten the God of your salvationAnd have
        not remembered the Rock of your Stronghold\u2014Therefore you plant lovely
        plantsAnd set the grounds with vine slips of a strange god,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In the day that you plant it you carefully fence it in,And in the
        morning you bring your seed to blossom;Yet [promising as it is] the harvest
        will be a heap [of ruins that passes away]In the day of sickness and incurable
        pain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Oh, the uproar of many peoplesWho roar like the roaring of the seas,And
        the noise of nationsWho roar like the rumbling of mighty waters!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The nations roar on like the roaring of many waters,But God will
        rebuke them and they will flee far away,And be chased like chaff on the mountains
        before the wind,Or like whirling dust before the storm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: At evening time, now look, sudden terror!Before morning the Assyrians
        are no more.This is the portion (fate) of those who plunder us,And the lot
        of those who pillage us.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Message to Ethiopia'
      title: Message to Ethiopia
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to the land of whirring wingsWhich is
        beyond the rivers of Cush (Ethiopia),  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Which sends ambassadors by the sea,Even in vessels of papyrus on
        the surface of the waters.Go, swift messengers, to a nation [of people] tall
        and smooth (clean shaven),To a people feared far and wide,A powerful and
        oppressive nationWhose land the rivers divide.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All you inhabitants of the world, you who dwell on the earth,When
        a banner is raised on the mountains, you will see it!When a trumpet is blown,
        you will hear it!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For this is what the Lord has said to me,\u201CI will be quiet and
        I will look on from My dwelling place,Like shimmering heat above the sunshine,Like
        a cloud of dew in the heat of harvest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For before the harvest, when the blossom is overAnd the flower becomes
        a ripening grape,He will cut off the sprigs [without buds] with pruning knives,And
        [He will] remove and cut away the spreading branches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'They (warriors) will be left together for the mountain birds of prey,And
        for the beasts of the earth;And the birds of prey will [spend the] summer
        feeding on them,And all the beasts of the earth will spend harvest time on
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "At that time a gift of homage will be brought to the Lord of hostsFrom
        a people tall and smooth (clean shaven),From a people feared far and wide,A
        powerful and oppressive nation,Whose land the rivers divide\u2014To the place
        [of worship] of the name of the Lord of hosts, to Mount Zion [in Jerusalem]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Message to Egypt'
      title: Message to Egypt
      number: 1
      content: '  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Egypt:Listen carefully, the Lord is riding on a swift cloud and is about
        to come to Egypt;The idols of Egypt will tremble at His presence,And the
        heart of the Egyptians will melt within them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSo I will provoke Egyptians against Egyptians;And they will
        fight, each one against his brother and each one against his neighbor,City
        against city, kingdom against kingdom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the spirit of the Egyptians will become exhausted within them
        and emptied out;And I will confuse their strategy,So that they will consult
        the idols and the spirits of the dead,And mediums and soothsayers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And I will hand over the Egyptians to a hard and cruel master,And
        a mighty king will rule over them,\u201D declares the Lord God of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The waters from the sea will dry up,And the river will be parched
        and dry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The canals will become foul-smelling,The streams of Egypt will thin
        out and dry up,The reeds and the rushes will rot away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The meadows by the Nile, by the edge of the Nile,And all the sown
        fields of the NileWill become dry, be blown away, and be no more.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The fishermen will lament (cry out in grief),And all those who cast
        a hook into the Nile will mourn,And those who spread nets upon the waters
        will languish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Moreover, those who make linen from combed flaxAnd those who weave
        white cloth will be ashamed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '[Those who are] the pillars and foundations of Egypt will be crushed;And
        all those who work for wages will be grieved in soul.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The princes of Zoan are complete fools;The counsel of the Pharaoh\u2019s
        wisest advisors has become stupid.How can you say to Pharaoh,\u201CI am a
        son of the wise, a son of ancient kings?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Where then are your wise men?Please let them tell you,And let them
        understand what the Lord of hostsHas purposed against Egypt [if they can].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The princes of Zoan have acted like fools,The princes of Memphis
        are deluded [and entertain false hope];  Those who are the cornerstone of
        her tribesHave led Egypt astray.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The Lord has mixed a spirit of distortion within her;Her leaders
        have caused Egypt to stagger in all that she does,As a drunken man staggers
        in his vomit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There will be no work for EgyptWhich head or tail, [high] palm branch
        or [low] bulrush, may do.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'In that day the Egyptians will become like [helpless] women, and
        they will tremble and be frightened because of the waving of the hand of
        the Lord of hosts, which He is going to wave over them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The land of Judah [Assyria\u2019s ally] will become a terror to the
        Egyptians; everyone to whom Judah is mentioned will be in dread of it, because
        of the purpose of the Lord of hosts which He is planning against Egypt.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'In that day five cities in the land of Egypt will speak the language
        of [the Hebrews of] Canaan and swear allegiance to the Lord of hosts. One
        [of them] will be called the City of Destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'In that day there will be an altar to the Lord in the midst of the
        land of Egypt, and a memorial stone to the Lord near its border. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'It will become a sign and a witness to the Lord of hosts in the land
        of Egypt; for they will cry to the Lord because of oppressors, and He will
        send them a Savior, a [Great] Defender, and He will rescue them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And so the Lord will make Himself known to Egypt, and the Egyptians
        will know [heed, honor, and cherish] the Lord in that day. They will even
        worship with sacrifices [of animals] and offerings [of produce]; they will
        make a vow to the Lord and fulfill it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'The Lord will strike Egypt, striking but healing it; so they will
        return to the Lord, and He will respond to them and heal them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In that day there will be a highway from Egypt to Assyria, and the
        Assyrians will come into Egypt and the Egyptians into Assyria; and the Egyptians
        will worship and serve [the Lord] with the Assyrians.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'In that day Israel will be the third party with Egypt and with Assyria
        [in a Messianic league], a blessing in the midst of the earth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "whom the Lord of hosts has blessed, saying, \u201CBlessed is Egypt
        My people, and Assyria the work of My hands, and Israel My heritage.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy about Egypt and Cush (Ancient Ethiopia)'
      title: Prophecy about Egypt and Cush (Ancient Ethiopia)
      number: 1
      content: '  In the year that the Tartan [the Assyrian commander in chief] came
        to Ashdod [in Philistia], when Sargon king of Assyria sent him and he fought
        against Ashdod and captured it, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "at that time the Lord spoke through Isaiah the son of Amoz, saying,
        \u201CGo, untie the sackcloth from your hips and take your sandals off your
        feet.\u201D And he did so, walking around stripped [to his loincloth] and
        barefoot. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the Lord said, \u201CEven as My servant Isaiah has walked stripped
        and barefoot for three years as a sign and forewarning concerning Egypt and
        Cush (Ethiopia), "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "in the same way the king of Assyria will lead away the Egyptian captives
        and the Cushite exiles, young and old, stripped and barefoot, even with buttocks
        uncovered\u2014to the shame of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then they will be dismayed and ashamed because of Cush their hope
        and Egypt their boast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "So the inhabitants of this coastland [the Israelites and their neighbors]
        will say in that day, \u2018Look what has happened to those in whom we hoped
        and trusted and to whom we fled for help to be spared from the king of Assyria!
        But we, how will we escape [captivity and exile]?\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Commands That Babylon Be Taken'
      title: God Commands That Babylon Be Taken
      number: 1
      content: "  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        the Desert of the Sea (the seasonally flooded plains just south of Babylon):As
        windstorms in the Negev (the South) sweep through,So it (God\u2019s judgment)
        comes from the desert, from [the hostile armies of] a terrifying land.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "A harsh vision has been shown to me;The treacherous one deals treacherously,
        and the destroyer destroys.Go up, Elam! Lay siege, Media!All the groaning
        [caused by Babylon\u2019s ruthless oppressions] I [the Lord] have brought
        to an end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore [continues Isaiah] my loins are filled with anguish;Pains
        have seized me like the pains of a woman in childbirth;I am so bent and bewildered
        that I cannot hear, I am so terrified that I cannot see.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My mind reels, horror overwhelms me;The twilight I longed for has
        been turned into fear and trembling for me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They set the table [for the doomed banquet], they spread out the
        cloth, they eat, they drink;\u201CRise up, captains [of Belshazzar\u2019s
        court], oil your shields [for battle, for your enemy is at the gates]!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "This is what the Lord says to me,\u201CGo, station the lookout, let
        him report what he sees.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "When he sees a chariot, horsemen in pairs,A train of donkeys and
        a train of camels,Let him pay attention and listen closely, very closely.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the lookout called like a lion,\u201CO Lord, I stand continually
        on the watchtower by day,And I am stationed every night at my guard post.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Now look! Here comes a troop of riders, horsemen in pairs.\u201DAnd
        one said, \u201CFallen, fallen is Babylon;And all the carved images of her
        gods are shattered on the ground.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Oracles about Edom and Arabia'
      title: Oracles about Edom and Arabia
      number: 10
      content: 'O my threshed people [Judah, who must be judged and trampled down
        by Babylon], my afflicted of the threshing floor.What I have heard from the
        Lord of hosts,The God of Israel, I have [joyfully] announced to you [that
        Babylon is to fall].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Dumah (Edom):Someone keeps calling to me from Seir (Edom),\u201CWatchman,
        what is left of the night [of Assyrian oppression]?Watchman, what is left
        of the night? [How long until morning?]\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The watchman says,\u201CThe morning comes [only briefly], but also
        [comes] the night [of Babylonian oppression].If you would ask [of me then],
        ask [again, if Edom really wishes to know];Come back again.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Arabia:In the thickets of Arabia you must spend the night,Caravans of Dedanites.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Bring water for the thirsty [Dedanites],O inhabitants of the land
        of Tema [in Arabia];Meet the fugitive with bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For they have fled from the swords,From the drawn sword, from the
        bent bowAnd from the press of battle and grief of war.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "For the Lord has said this to me, \u201CWithin a year, according
        to the years of a hired man [who will work no longer than was agreed], all
        the splendor of [the tribe of] Kedar will end; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "and the remainder of the number of archers, the mighty men of the
        sons of Kedar, will be few; for the Lord, the God of Israel, has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Valley of Vision'
      title: The Valley of Vision
      number: 1
      content: '  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        the Valley of Vision:What is the matter with you now, that you have all gone
        up to the housetops,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'You [Jerusalem] who were full of noise,A tumultuous city, a joyous
        and exuberant city;Your slain were not slain [in a glorious death] with the
        sword,Nor did they die in battle.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'All your leaders have fled together [with your king],And have been
        captured without the bow [which they had thrown away];All of you who were
        found were taken captive together,Though they had fled far away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Therefore I say, \u201CLook away from me;Let me weep bitterly.Do
        not try to comfort me over the destruction of the daughter of my people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For the Lord God of hosts has a day of panic and of tumult, of trampling,
        of confusionIn the Valley of Vision,A [day of] breaking down wallsAnd a crying
        [for help] to the mountain.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Elam took up the quiverWith the chariots, infantry and horsemen;And
        Kir uncovered the shield.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And it came to pass that your choicest valleys were full of chariots,And
        the horsemen took their fixed positions [in an offensive array] at the gate
        [of Jerusalem].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then God removed the [protective] covering of Judah;And in that day
        you looked to the weapons of the House of the Forest (Solomon\u2019s armory).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You saw that the breachesIn the wall of the City of David [the citadel
        of Zion] were many;You collected [within the city\u2019s walls] the waters
        of the Lower Pool (Siloam).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then you counted the houses of JerusalemAnd you tore down the houses
        [to get materials] to fortify the city wall [by extending it].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You also made a reservoir between the two wallsFor the waters of
        the Old Pool,But you did not look to its Maker,Nor did you recognize Him
        who planned it long ago.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Therefore in that day the Lord God of hosts called you to weeping,
        to mourning,To shaving the head and to wearing sackcloth [in humiliation].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Instead, there is joy and jubilation,Killing of oxen and slaughtering
        of sheep,Eating meat and drinking wine, saying,\u201CLet us eat and drink,
        for tomorrow we may die.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But the Lord of hosts revealed Himself in my ears,\u201CThis sin
        absolutely will not be forgiven youUntil you die,\u201D says the Lord God
        of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For the Lord God of hosts says this, \u201CGo to this [contemptible]
        steward,To Shebna, who is in charge of the royal household [but is building
        himself a tomb worthy of a king, and say to him],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018What business do you have here?And whom do you have here,That
        you have hewn out a tomb here for yourself,You who hew a sepulcher on the
        height,You who carve a resting place for yourself in the rock?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Listen carefully, the Lord is about to hurl you away violently, O
        man;And He is about to grasp you firmly  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And roll you up tightly like a ballAnd toss you into a vast country;There
        you will dieAnd there your splendid chariots will be,You shame of your master\u2019s
        house.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will depose you from your office,And you will be pulled down from
        your position [of importance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Then it will come to pass in that dayThat I will summon My servant
        Eliakim the son of Hilkiah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And I will clothe him with your tunic [of distinction]And tie your
        sash securely around him.I will entrust him with your authority;He will become
        a father to the inhabitants of Jerusalem and to the house of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then I will set on his shoulder the key of the house of David;When
        he opens no one will shut,When he shuts no one will open.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will drive him like a peg in a firm place,And he will become a
        throne of honor and glory to his father\u2019s house.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "So they will hang on him all the honor and glory [the complete responsibility]
        of his father\u2019s house, offspring and issue [of the family, high and
        low], all the least of the articles, from the bowls to all the jars. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In that day,\u201D declares the Lord of hosts, \u201Cthe peg (Eliakim)
        that was driven into the firm place will give way; it will even break off
        and fall, and the burden hanging on it will be cut off, for the Lord has
        spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fall of Tyre'
      title: The Fall of Tyre
      number: 1
      content: '  The [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        Tyre:Wail, O ships of Tarshish,For Tyre is destroyed, without house, without
        harbor;It is reported to them from the land of Cyprus (Kittim).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Be silent, you inhabitants of the coastland,You merchants of Sidon; 
        Your messengers crossed the sea  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And they were on great waters.The grain of the Shihor, the harvest
        of the Nile River, was Tyre\u2019s revenue;And she was the market of nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Be ashamed, O Sidon [mother-city of Tyre, now like a widow bereaved
        of her children];For the sea speaks, the stronghold of the sea, saying,\u201CI
        have neither labored nor given birth [to children];I have neither brought
        up young men nor reared virgins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'When the report reaches Egypt,They will be in agony at the report
        about Tyre.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Cross over to Tarshish [to seek safety as exiles];Wail, O inhabitants
        of the coastland [of Tyre].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Is this your jubilant city,Whose origin dates back to antiquity,Whose
        feet used to carry her [far away] to colonize distant places?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who has planned this against Tyre, the bestower of crowns,Whose merchants
        were princes, whose traders were the honored of the earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The Lord of hosts has planned it, to defile the pride of all beauty,To
        bring into contempt and humiliation all the honored of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Overflow your land like [the overflow of] the Nile, O Daughter of
        Tarshish;There is no more restraint [on you to make you pay tribute to Tyre].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He has stretched out His hand over the sea,He has shaken the kingdoms;The
        Lord has given a command concerning Canaan to destroy her strongholds and
        her fortresses [like Tyre and Sidon].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He has said, \u201CYou shall never again exult [in triumph], O crushed
        Virgin Daughter of Sidon.Arise, cross over to Cyprus; even there you will
        find no rest.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Now look at the land of the Chaldeans (Babylonia)\u2014this is the
        people which was not; the Assyrians allocated Tyre for desert creatures\u2014they
        set up their siege towers, they stripped its palaces, they made it a ruin.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Wail, O ships of Tarshish,For your stronghold [of Tyre] is destroyed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Now in that day Tyre will be forgotten for seventy years, like the
        days of one king. At the end of seventy years it will happen to Tyre as in
        the prostitute\u2019s song:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Take a harp, walk around the city,O forgotten prostitute;Play the
        strings skillfully, sing many songs,That you may be remembered.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "It will come to pass at the end of seventy years that the Lord will
        remember Tyre. Then she will return to her prostitute\u2019s wages and will
        play the [role of a] prostitute [by trading] with all the kingdoms on the
        face of the earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But her commercial gain and her prostitute\u2019s wages will be dedicated
        to the Lord; it will not be treasured or stored up, but her commercial gain
        will become sufficient food and stately clothing for those who dwell (minister)
        in the presence of the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judgment on the Earth'
      title: Judgment on the Earth
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, the Lord  lays waste to the earth, devastates it, twists
        and distorts its face and scatters its inhabitants. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the people will be like the priest, the servant like his master,
        the maid like her mistress, the buyer like the seller, the lender like the
        borrower, the creditor like the debtor [as God\u2019s impartial judgment
        of sin comes on all]. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The earth will be completely laid waste and utterly pillaged, for
        the Lord has spoken this word. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The earth dries up and crumbles away, the world dries out and crumbles
        away, the exalted of the people of the earth fade away. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The earth also is polluted by its inhabitants, because they have
        transgressed laws, violated statutes, and broken the everlasting covenant. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore, a curse devours the earth, and those who live on it suffer
        the punishment of their guilt. Therefore, the inhabitants of the earth are
        burned [under the curse of God\u2019s wrath], and few people are left.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The new wine mourns,The vine decays;All the merry-hearted sigh and
        groan.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The mirth of the timbrels (tambourines) ceases,The noise of those
        who rejoice ends,The joy of the harp ceases.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'They do not drink wine with a song;Strong drink is bitter to those
        who drink it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The city of chaos is broken down;Every house is shut up so that no
        one may enter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'There is an outcry in the streets concerning the wine;All jubilation
        is darkened,The joy of the earth is banished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Horrible desolation is left in the city,And the gate is battered
        into ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For so it will be in the midst of the earth among the peoples,As
        the shaking of an olive tree,As the gleanings when the grape harvest is over
        [and only a little of the fruit remains].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They [who have escaped and remain] raise their voices, they shout
        for joy;They rejoice from the [Mediterranean] Sea in the majesty of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Therefore honor and glorify the Lord in the east [in the region of
        light],The name of the Lord, the God of Israel [honor His name],In the coastlands
        and islands of the [Mediterranean] Sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "From the ends of the earth we hear songs, \u201CGlory and honor to
        the Righteous One,\u201DBut I say, \u201CI waste away, I waste away. Woe
        to me!The treacherous deal treacherously,Indeed, the treacherous deal very
        treacherously.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Terror and pit [of destruction] and snareConfront you, O inhabitant
        of the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then it will be that he who flees at the sound of terror will fall
        into the pit,And he who comes up out of the pit will be caught in the snare;For
        the windows of heaven are opened, and the foundations of the earth tremble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The earth is broken completely apart,The earth is split apart,The
        earth is shaken violently.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The earth reels back and forth like a drunkardAnd sways like a shack;Its
        transgression lies heavily upon it,And it will fall and not rise again.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'So it will happen in that dayThat the Lord will visit and punish
        the host (fallen angels) of heaven on high,And the kings of the earth on
        the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They will be gathered togetherAs prisoners [are gathered] in a dungeon;They
        will be shut up in prison,And after many days they will be visited and punished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: Then the full moon will be embarrassed and the sun ashamed,For the
        Lord of hosts will reign on Mount Zion and in Jerusalem,And His glory and
        brilliance will shine before His elders.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Song of Praise for God\u2019s Favor"
      title: "Song of Praise for God\u2019s Favor"
      number: 1
      content: '  O Lord, You are my God;I will exalt You, I will praise and give
        thanks to Your name;For You have done miraculous things,Plans formed long,
        long ago, [fulfilled] with perfect faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For You have made a city into a heap [of trash],A fortified city
        into a ruin;A palace of foreigners is no longer a city,It will never be rebuilt.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore a strong people will honor You;Cities of terrible and violent
        nations will fear You.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For You have been a stronghold for the helpless,A stronghold for
        the poor in his distress,A shelter from the storm, a shade from the heat;For
        the breath of tyrantsIs like a rainstorm against a wall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Like heat in a dry land, You will subdue the noise of foreigners
        [rejoicing over their enemies];Like heat in the shadow of a cloud, the song
        of the tyrants is silenced.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "On this mountain [Zion] the Lord of hosts will prepare a lavish banquet
        for all peoples [to welcome His reign on earth],A banquet of aged wines\u2014choice
        pieces [flavored] with marrow,Of refined, aged wines.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And on this mountain He will destroy the covering that is [cast]
        over all peoples,And the veil [of death] that is woven and spread over all
        the nations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He will swallow up death [and abolish it] for all time.And the Lord
        God will wipe away tears from all faces,And He will take away the disgrace
        of His people from all the earth;For the Lord has spoken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "It will be said in that day,\u201CIndeed, this is our God for whom
        we have waited that He would save us.This is the Lord for whom we have waited;Let
        us shout for joy and rejoice in His salvation.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the hand of the Lord will rest on this mountain [Zion],And Moab
        will be trampled down in his placeAs straw is trampled down in the [filthy]
        water of a manure pile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Moab will spread out his hands in the middle of the filthAs a
        swimmer spreads out his hands to swim,But the Lord will humiliate his pride
        in spite of the [skillful] movements of his hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: The high fortifications of your walls He will bring down,Lay low,
        and cast to the ground, to the dust.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Song of Trust in God\u2019s Protection"
      title: "Song of Trust in God\u2019s Protection"
      number: 1
      content: "  In that day this song will be sung in the land of Judah:\u201CWe
        have a strong city;He sets up salvation as walls and ramparts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Open the gates, that the righteous nation may enter,The one that
        remains faithful and trustworthy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "You will keep in perfect and constant peace the one whose mind is
        steadfast [that is, committed and focused on You\u2014in both inclination
        and character],Because he trusts and takes refuge in You [with hope and confident
        expectation].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Trust [confidently] in the Lord forever [He is your fortress, your
        shield, your banner],For the Lord God is an everlasting Rock [the Rock of
        Ages].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For He has thrown down the [arrogant] ones who dwell on high, the
        lofty and inaccessible city;He lays it low, He lays it low to the ground,
        He hurls it to the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The foot will trample it,  Even the feet of the suffering, and the
        steps of the helpless.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "The way of the righteous [those in right-standing with God\u2014living
        in moral and spiritual integrity] is smooth and level;O Upright One, make
        a level path for the just and righteous.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Indeed, in the path of Your judgments, O Lord,We have waited expectantly
        for You;Your name, even Your memory, is the desire and deep longing of our
        souls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In the night my soul longs for You [O Lord],Indeed, my spirit within
        me seeks You diligently;For [only] when Your judgments are experienced on
        the earthWill the inhabitants of the world learn righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Though the wicked is shown compassion and favor,He does not learn
        righteousness;In the land of uprightness he deals unjustly,And refuses to
        see the majesty of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: '  Though Your hand is lifted up [to strike], O Lord, the wicked do
        not see it.Let them see Your zeal for Your people and be put to shame;Indeed,
        let the fire reserved for Your enemies consume them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Lord, You will establish peace for us,Since You have also performed
        for us all that we have done.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'O Lord our God, other masters besides You have ruled over us;But
        through You alone we confess Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The [wicked] dead will not live [again], the spirits of the dead
        will not rise and return;Therefore You have punished and destroyed them,And
        You have wiped out every memory of them [every trace of them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'You have increased the nation, O Lord;You have increased the nation,
        You are glorified;You have extended all the borders of the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Lord, they sought You in distress;They managed only a prayerful
        whisperWhen Your discipline was upon them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As a woman with child approaches the time to give birth,She is in
        pain and struggles and cries out in her labor,So we were before You, O Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'We have been with child, we have twisted and struggled in labor;We
        gave birth, as it seems, only to wind.We could not accomplish salvation for
        the earth,Nor were inhabitants of the world born.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Your dead will live;  Their dead bodies will rise.You who lie in
        the dust, awake and shout for joy!For your dew is a dew of [celestial] light
        [heavenly, supernatural],And the earth will give birth to the spirits of
        the dead.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Come, my people, enter your chambersAnd shut your doors behind you;Hide
        for a little whileUntil the [Lord\u2019s] wrath is past.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: Listen carefully, the Lord is about to come out of His [heavenly]
        placeTo punish the inhabitants of the earth for their wickedness [their sin,
        their injustice, their wrongdoing];The earth will reveal the [innocent] blood
        shed upon herAnd will no longer cover her slain.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Deliverance of Israel'
      title: The Deliverance of Israel
      number: 1
      content: '  In that day the Lord will punish Leviathan the fleeing serpentWith
        His fierce and great and mighty sword [rescuing Israel from her enemy],Even
        Leviathan the twisted serpent;And He will kill the dragon who lives in the
        sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "In that day [it will be said of the redeemed nation of Israel],\u201CA
        vineyard of wine, sing in praise of it!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I, the Lord, am its Keeper;I water it every moment.So that no one
        will harm it,I guard it night and day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'I have no wrath.Should anyone give Me briars and thorns in battle,I
        would step on them, I would set them all on fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Or let him (Israel) cling to My strength and rely on My protection
        [My stronghold],Let him make peace with Me,Let him make peace with Me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '  In the generations to come Jacob will take root;Israel will blossom
        and sprout,And they will fill the surface of the world with fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Like the striking by Him who has struck them, has He struck them?Or
        like the slaughter of His slain, have they been slain?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You contended with them by exile, by driving them away [from Canaan];He
        has expelled them with His fierce wind on the day of the east wind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore through this the wickedness [the sin, the injustice, the
        wrongdoing] of Jacob (Israel) will be atoned for and forgiven;And this will
        be the full price [that God requires] for taking away his sin:When Israel
        makes all the stones of the [pagan] altars like crushed chalk stones;When
        the Asherim and the incense altars will not stand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the fortified city is isolated,A settlement deserted and abandoned
        like the desert;There the calf will graze,And there it will lie down and
        feed on its branches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When its branches are dry, they are broken off;The women come and
        make a fire with them.For they are not a people of understanding,Therefore
        He who made them will not have compassion on them,And He who created them
        will not be gracious to them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'In that day the Lord will thresh [out His grain] from the flowing
        stream of the River [Euphrates] to the Brook of Egypt, and you will be gathered
        up one by one, O sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: It will come to pass in that day that a great trumpet will be blown,
        and those who were lost and perishing in the land of Assyria and who were
        scattered in the land of Egypt will come and worship the Lord on the holy
        mountain at Jerusalem.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ephraim\u2019s Captivity Predicted"
      title: "Ephraim\u2019s Captivity Predicted"
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to [Samaria] the splendid crown of the
        drunkards of Ephraim,And to the fading flower of its glorious beauty,Which
        is at the head of the rich valleyOf those who are overcome with wine!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Listen carefully, the Lord has a strong and mighty agent [the Assyrian];Like
        a tempest of hail, a disastrous storm,Like a tempest of mighty overflowing
        waters,He has cast it down to the earth with His hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "The splendid crown of the drunkards of Ephraim is trampled by [the
        foreigners\u2019] feet.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the fading flower of its glorious beauty,Which is at the head
        of the rich valley,Will be like the early fig before the summer,Which one
        sees,And as soon as it is in his handHe [greedily] swallows it [and so will
        the Assyrians rapidly devour Samaria, Israel\u2019s capital].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'In that day the Lord of hosts will become a magnificent crownAnd
        a glorious diadem to the [converted] remnant of His people,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A spirit of justice for him who sits in judgment [administering the
        law],A strength to those who drive back the battle at the gate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But even these reel with wine and stagger from strong drink:The priest
        and the prophet reel with strong drink;They are confused by wine, they stagger
        from strong drink;They reel while seeing visions,They stagger when pronouncing
        judgment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For all the tables are full of filthy vomit, so that there is no
        place [that is clean.]  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "  They say \u201CTo whom would He teach knowledge?And to whom would
        He explain the message?Those just weaned from milk?Those just taken from
        the breast?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For He says,\u2018Precept upon precept, precept upon precept,Rule
        upon rule, rule upon rule,Here a little, there a little.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Indeed, the Lord will teach this people [in a more humiliating way]By
        [men with] stammering lips and a foreign tongue,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "He who said to them, \u201CThis is the place of quiet, give rest
        to the weary,\u201DAnd, \u201CThis is the resting place,\u201D yet they would
        not listen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Judah Is Warned'
      title: Judah Is Warned
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore the word of the Lord to them will be [merely monotonous
        repetitions]:\u201CPrecept upon precept, precept upon precept,Rule upon rule,
        rule upon rule,Here a little, there a little.\u201DThat they may go and stumble
        backward, and be broken, ensnared, and taken captive.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Therefore, hear the word of the Lord, you arrogant menWho rule this
        people who are in Jerusalem!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Because you have said, \u201CWe have made a covenant with death,And
        with Sheol (the place of the dead) we have made an agreement,When the overwhelming
        scourge passes by, it will not reach us,For we have made lies our refuge
        and we have concealed ourselves in deception.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Therefore the Lord God says this,\u201CListen carefully, I am laying
        in Zion a Stone, a tested Stone,A precious Cornerstone for the [secure] foundation,
        firmly placed.He who believes [who trusts in, relies on, and adheres to that
        Stone] will not be disturbed or give way [in sudden panic].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "I will make justice the measuring lineAnd righteousness the mason\u2019s
        level;Then hail will sweep away the refuge of liesAnd waters will flood over
        the secret [hiding] place.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Your covenant with death will be annulled,And your agreement with
        Sheol (the place of the dead) will not stand;When the overwhelming scourge
        passes through,Then you will become its trampling ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "As often as it passes through, it will seize you;For morning after
        morning it will pass through, by day and by night,And it will be sheer terror
        to understand what it means.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'For the bed is too short to stretch out on,And the blanket is too
        narrow to wrap around oneself [and likewise all their preparations are inadequate].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'For the Lord will rise up as at Mount Perazim,He will be stirred
        up as in the Valley of Gibeon,To do His work, His unusual and incredible
        work,And to accomplish His work, His extraordinary work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Now do not carry on as scoffers,Or the bands which bind you will
        be made stronger;For I have heard from the Lord God of hosts [a decree]Of
        decisive destruction on all the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Listen and hear my voice;Listen carefully and hear my words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Does the farmer plow all day to plant seed?Does he continually dig
        furrows and harrow his ground [after it is prepared]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'When he has leveled its surface,Does he not sow [the seed of] dill
        and scatter cumin,And plant wheat in rows,And barley in its [intended] place
        and rye within its border?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For his God instructs [him correctly] and teaches him properly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'For dill is not threshed with a sharp threshing sledge,Nor is a cartwheel
        rolled over cumin;But dill is beaten out with a staff, and cumin with a rod.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Bread grain is crushed fine,Indeed, the farmer does not continue
        to thresh it forever.Because the wheel of his cart and his horses eventually
        damage it,He does not thresh it longer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: This also comes from the Lord of hosts,Who has made His counsel wonderful
        and His wisdom great.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Jerusalem Is Warned'
      title: Jerusalem Is Warned
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to Ariel, to Ariel, the city where David
        [once] camped!Add yet another year; let the feasts run their course [but
        only one year more].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then I will harass Ariel,And she will be a city of mourning and lamenting
        (crying out in grief)Yet she will be like an Ariel [an altar hearth] to Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will camp against you and encircle you,And I will hem you in with
        siege works,And I will raise fortifications against you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then you [Jerusalem] will be brought low,You will speak from the
        earth,And from the dust where you lie face downYour muffled words will come.Your
        voice will also be like that of a spirit from the earth [like one produced
        by a medium],And your speech will whisper and squeak from the dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But the multitude of your enemies [that assault you] will become
        like fine dust,And the multitude of the tyrants like the chaff which blows
        away;And it will happen in an instant, suddenly [that your enemy is destroyed].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You will be punished by the Lord of hosts with thunder and earthquake
        and great noise,With whirlwind and tempest and the flame of a consuming fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the multitude of all the nations that fight against Ariel (Jerusalem),Even
        all who fight against her and her stronghold, and who distress her,Will be
        like a dream, a vision of the night.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'It will be as when a hungry man dreamsThat he is eating,But when
        he awakens, his hunger is not satisfied;Or as when a thirsty man dreamsThat
        he is drinking,But when he awakens, in fact, he is faintAnd his thirst is
        not quenched.So will the multitude of all the nations beWho fight against
        Mount Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Stop and take some time and wonder [at this prophecy],Blind yourselves
        and be blinded [at its fulfillment by your spiritual incompetence].They are
        drunk, but not from wine;They stagger, but not from strong drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For the Lord has poured over you a spirit of deep sleep.He has closed
        your eyes, [you who are] the prophets;And He has covered your heads, [you
        who are] the seers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "The entire vision [of all these things] will be to you like the words
        of a scroll that is sealed, which they give to one who can read, saying,
        \u201CRead this, please,\u201D he shall say, \u201CI cannot, for it is sealed.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Then the book will be given to the one who cannot read, saying, \u201CRead
        this, please.\u201D And he will say, \u201CI cannot read.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Lord said,\u201CBecause this nation approaches [Me only]
        with their wordsAnd honors Me [only] with their lip service,But they remove
        their hearts far from Me,And their reverence for Me is a tradition that is
        learned by rote [without any regard for its meaning],  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Therefore, listen carefully, I will again do marvelous and amazing
        things with this people, wonderful and astonishing things;And the wisdom
        of their wise men will perish,And the understanding of their discerning men
        will be hidden.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Woe (judgment is coming) to those who [try to] deeply hide their
        plans from the Lord,Whose deeds are done in a dark place,And who say, \u201CWho
        sees us?\u201D or \u201CWho knows us?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: Blessing after Discipline'
      title: Blessing after Discipline
      number: 16
      content: "You turn things upside down [with your perversity]!Shall the potter
        be considered equal with the clay,That the thing that is made would say to
        its maker, \u201CHe did not make me\u201D;Or the thing that is formed say
        to him who formed it, \u201CHe has no understanding\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Is it not yet a very little whileUntil Lebanon will be turned into
        a fertile field,And the fertile field regarded as a forest?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'On that day the deaf will hear the words of a book,And out of their
        gloom and darkness the eyes of the blind will see [the words of the book].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The afflicted also will increase their joy in the Lord,And the needy
        of mankind will rejoice and celebrate in the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "For the tyrant will come to an end and the scorner will be finished,Indeed
        all who are intent on doing evil will be cut off\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Those who cause a person to be condemned with a [false] word,And
        lay a trap for him who upholds justice at the [city] gate,And defraud the
        one in the right with meaningless arguments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Therefore, the Lord, who redeemed Abraham [from paganism] says this,
        concerning the house of Jacob (Israel):\u201CJacob will not be ashamed, nor
        will his face turn pale [with disappointment because of his children\u2019s
        degenerate behavior];  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For when he sees his children, the work of My hands, in his midst,They
        will sanctify My Name;They will sanctify the Holy One of JacobAnd will stand
        in awe and reverent fear of the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: Those who err in mind will know the truth,And those who criticize
        and murmur discontentedly will accept instruction.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Judah Warned against Egyptian Alliance'
      title: Judah Warned against Egyptian Alliance
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CWoe (judgment is coming) to the rebellious children,\u201D
        declares the Lord,\u201CWho carry out a plan, but not Mine,And make an alliance
        [by pouring out a libation], but not of My Spirit,In order to add sin to
        sin;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Who proceed down to EgyptWithout consulting Me,To take refuge in
        the stronghold of PharaohAnd to take shelter in the shadow of Egypt!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Therefore the safety and protection of Pharaoh will be your shameAnd
        the refuge in the shadow of Egypt, your humiliation and disgrace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For his princes are at ZoanAnd his ambassadors arrive at Hanes [in
        Egypt].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "All will be ashamed because of a people (the Egyptians) who cannot
        benefit them,Who are not a help or benefit, but a shame and also a disgrace.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A [mournful, inspired] oracle (a burden to be carried) concerning
        the beasts of the Negev (the South):Through a land of trouble and anguish,From
        where come lioness and lion, viper and [fiery] flying serpent,They carry
        their riches on the shoulders of young donkeysAnd their treasures on the
        humps of camels,To a people (Egyptians) who cannot benefit them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "For Egypt\u2019s help is worthless and good for nothing.Therefore,
        I have called her\u201CRahab Who Has Been Exterminated.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Now, go, write it on a tablet before themAnd inscribe it on a scroll,So
        that it may serve in the time to comeAs a witness [against them] forevermore.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For this is a rebellious people, lying sons,Sons who refuse to listen
        toThe law and instruction of the Lord;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Who say to the seers, \u201CYou must not see visions from God\u201D;And
        to the prophets, \u201CYou must not prophesy to us what is right!Speak to
        us pleasant things and smooth words,Prophesy [deceitful] illusions [that
        we will enjoy].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Get out of the [true] way, turn aside from the path [of God],Stop
        bothering us with the Holy One of Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Therefore, the Holy One of Israel says this,\u201CBecause you have
        refused and rejected this word [of Mine]And have put your trust in oppression
        and guile, and have relied on them,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Therefore this wickedness [this sin, this injustice, this wrongdoing]
        will be to youLike a crack [in a wall] about to fall,A bulge in a high wall,Whose
        collapse comes suddenly in an instant,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Whose collapse is like the smashing of a potter\u2019s jar,Crushed
        so savagelythat there cannot be found among its pieces a potsherd [large
        enough]To take [coals of] fire from a fireplace,Or to scoop water from a
        cistern.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For the Lord God, the Holy One of Israel has said this,\u201CIn returning
        [to Me] and rest you shall be saved,In quietness and confident trust is your
        strength.\u201DBut you were not willing,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And you said, \u201CNo! We will flee on horses!\u201DTherefore you
        will flee [from your enemies]!And [you said], \u201CWe will ride on swift
        horses!\u201DTherefore those who pursue you shall be swift.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: God Is Gracious and Just'
      title: God Is Gracious and Just
      number: 17
      content: 'A thousand of you will flee at the threat of one man;You will flee
        at the threat of five,Until you are left like a flag on the top of a mountain,And
        like a signal on a hill.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Therefore the Lord waits [expectantly] and longs to be gracious to
        you,And therefore He waits on high to have compassion on you.  For the Lord
        is a God of justice;Blessed (happy, fortunate) are all those who long for
        Him [since He will never fail them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  O people in Zion, inhabitant in Jerusalem, you will weep no longer.
        He will most certainly be gracious to you at the sound of your cry for help;
        when He hears it, He will answer you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Though the Lord gives you the bread of adversity and the water of
        oppression, yet your Teacher will no longer hide Himself, but your eyes will
        [constantly] see your Teacher. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Your ears will hear a word behind you, \u201CThis is the way, walk
        in it,\u201D whenever you turn to the right or to the left. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And you will defile your carved images overlaid with silver, and
        your cast images plated with gold. You will scatter them like a bloodstained
        cloth, and will say to them, \u201CBe gone!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Then He will give you rain for the seed with which you sow the ground,
        and bread [grain] from the produce of the ground, and it will be rich and
        plentiful. In that day your livestock will graze in large and roomy pastures. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Also the oxen and the young donkeys that work the ground will eat
        salted fodder, which has been winnowed with shovel and pitchfork. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'On every lofty mountain and on every high hill there will be streams
        of water on the day of the great slaughter (the day of the Lord), when the
        towers fall [and all His enemies are destroyed]. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The light of the full moon will be like the light of the sun, and
        the light of the sun will be seven times brighter, like the light of seven
        days [concentrated in one], in the day the Lord binds up the fracture of
        His people and heals the wound He has inflicted [because of their sins].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now look, the name of the Lord comes from far away,Burning with His
        anger, and heavy with smoke;His lips are full of indignation,And His tongue
        is like a consuming fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'His breath is like an overflowing river,Which reaches to the neck,To
        sift the nations back and forth in a sieve [of disaster],And to put in the
        jaws of the peoples the bridle which leads to ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'You will have a song as in the night when a holy feast is kept,And
        joy of heart as when one marches [in procession] with a flute,To go to the
        [temple on the] mountain of the Lord, to the Rock of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the Lord will make His majestic voice heard,And show the descending
        of His arm [striking] in [His] fierce anger,And in the flame of a devouring
        fire,In the crashing sound of heavy rain, cloudburst, and hailstones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For at the voice of the Lord the Assyrians will be terrified,  When
        He strikes [them] with the rod.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And every blow of the rod of punishment,Which the Lord will lay on
        them,Will be to the music of Israel\u2019s tambourines and lyres;And in battles,
        brandishing weapons, He will fight Assyria.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: For Topheth [in Hinnom] has long been ready;Indeed, it has been prepared
        for the [Assyrian] king.He has made it deep and wide,A pit of fire with plenty
        of wood;The breath of the Lord, like a river of brimstone (blazing sulfur),
        kindles and fans it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Look Not to Egypt but to God'
      title: Look Not to Egypt but to God
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to those who go down to Egypt for help,Who
        rely on horsesAnd trust in chariots because they are many,And in horsemen
        because they are very strong,But they do not look to the Holy One of Israel,
        nor seek and consult the Lord!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yet He is also wise and will bring disaster,And does not retract
        His words,But will arise against the house of evildoersAnd against the helpers
        of those who do evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Now the Egyptians are men and not God,And their horses are flesh
        and not spirit;And the Lord will stretch out His hand,And he (Egypt) who
        helps will stumble,And he (Judah) who is helped will fall,And all of them
        will perish together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For so the Lord says to me,\u201CAs the lion or the young lion growls
        over his prey,And though a large group of shepherds is called out against
        himHe will not be terrified at their voice nor cringe at their noise,So the
        Lord of hosts will come down to wage war on Mount Zion and on its hill.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Like flying birds, so will the Lord of hosts protect Jerusalem;He
        will protect and save it,He will pass over and rescue it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Return to Him from whom you have so deeply defected, O sons of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For in that day every man will reject and throw away his idols of
        silver and his idols of gold [in disgust], which your own hands have sinfully
        made for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the Assyrian will fall by a sword not of man,And a sword not
        of man will devour him.And he will flee from the sword [of God],And his young
        men will become forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CHis rock [his stronghold] will pass away because of panic,And
        his princes will be terrified at the [sight of the battle] standard,\u201DDeclares
        the Lord, whose fire is in Zion and whose furnace is in Jerusalem."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Glorious Future'
      title: The Glorious Future
      number: 1
      content: '  Behold, a King will reign in righteousness,And princes will rule
        with justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Each [one of them] will be like a hiding place from the windAnd a
        shelter from the storm,Like streams of water in a dry land,Like the shade
        of a huge rock in a parched and weary land [to those who turn to them].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then the eyes of those who see will not be blinded,And the ears of
        those who hear will listen attentively.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The heart (mind) of those who act impulsively will discern the truth,And
        the tongue of the stammerers will hurry to speak clearly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The fool (the good-for-nothing) will no longer be called noble,Nor
        the rogue said to be generous.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the fool speaks nonsense,And his heart (mind) plans wickedness:To
        practice ungodliness and to speak error concerning the Lord,To keep the craving
        of the hungry unsatisfiedAnd to deprive the thirsty of drink.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'As for the rogue, his weapons are evil;He conceives wicked plansTo
        ruin the poor with lies,Even when the plea of the needy one is just and right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But the noble man conceives noble and magnificent things;And he stands
        by what is noble and magnificent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Rise up, you women who are carefree,And hear my voice,You confident
        and unsuspecting daughters!Listen to what I am saying.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'In little more than a yearYou will tremble [with anxiety], you unsuspecting
        and complacent women;For the vintage has ended,And the harvest will not come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Tremble, you women who are carefree;Tremble with fear, you complacent
        ones!Strip, undress and wear sackcloth on your waist [in grief],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Beat your breasts [in mourning] for the beautiful fields, for the
        fruitful vine,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For the land of my people growing over with thorns and briars\u2014Yes,
        [mourn] for all the houses of joy in the joyous city.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'For the palace has been abandoned, the populated city deserted;The
        hill [of the city] and the watchtower have become caves [for wild animals]
        forever,A delight for wild donkeys, a pasture for flocks,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Until the Spirit is poured out upon us from on high,And the wilderness
        becomes a fertile field,And the fertile field is valued as a forest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then justice will dwell in the wilderness,And righteousness will
        live in the fertile field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the effect of righteousness will be peace,And the result of righteousness
        will be quietness and confident trust forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then my people will live in a peaceful surrounding,And in secure
        dwellings and in undisturbed resting places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'But it will hail, when the forest comes down,And the [capital] city
        will fall in utter humiliation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: Blessed (happy, fortunate) are you who cast your seed upon all waters
        [when the river overflows its banks and irrigates the land],You who allow
        the ox and the donkey to roam freely.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Judgment of God'
      title: The Judgment of God
      number: 1
      content: '  Woe (judgment is coming) to you, O destroyer,You who were not destroyed,And
        he who is treacherous, while others did not deal treacherously with him.As
        soon as you finish destroying, you will be destroyed;As soon as you stop
        dealing treacherously, others will deal treacherously with you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'O Lord, be gracious to us; we have waited [expectantly] for You.Be
        the arm of Your servants every morning [that is, their strength and their
        defense],Our salvation also in the time of trouble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'At the sound of the tumult, the peoples flee;At the lifting up of
        Yourself nations scatter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Your spoil [of Israel\u2019s foe] is gathered [by the people of Jerusalem]
        as the caterpillar gathers;As locusts swarming so people swarm on it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord is exalted, for He dwells on high;He has filled Zion with
        justice and righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And He will be the security and stability of your times,A treasure
        of salvation, wisdom and knowledge;The fear of the Lord is your treasure.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Now look, their brave men shout outside;The ambassadors [seeking
        a treaty] of peace weep bitterly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The highways are deserted, the traveler has ceased [to appear]. 
        The enemy has broken the covenant, he has rejected the cities,He has no regard
        for [any] man.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The land mourns and dries out,Lebanon is shamed and [its lush foliage]
        withers;  Sharon is like a desert plain,And Bashan and [Mount] Carmel shake
        off their leaves.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CNow I will arise,\u201D says the Lord.\u201CNow I will be exalted;
        now I will be lifted up.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'You have conceived dried grass, you will give birth to stubble;My
        breath is a fire that will consume you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The peoples will be burned to lime,Like thorns cut down which are
        burned in the fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CYou who are far away, hear what I have done;And you who are
        near, acknowledge My might.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "The sinners in Zion are terrified;Trembling has seized the godless.[They
        cry] \u201CWho among us can live with the consuming fire?Who among us can
        live with everlasting burning?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He who walks righteously and speaks with integrity,Who rejects gain
        from fraud and from oppression,Who shakes his hand free from the taking of
        bribes,Who stops his ears from hearing about bloodshedAnd shuts his eyes
        to avoid looking upon evil;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He will dwell on the heights,His place of defense will be the fortress
        of rocks,His bread will be given him;His water will be permanent.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Your eyes will see the King in His beauty;They will see a far-distant
        land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Your mind will meditate on the terror [asking]:\u201CWhere is he
        who counts?Where is he who weighs [the tribute]?Where is he who counts the
        towers?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'You will no longer see the fierce and insolent people,A people of
        unintelligible speech which no one comprehends,Of a strange and stammering
        tongue which no one understands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Look upon Zion, the city of our appointed feasts and observances;Your
        eyes will see Jerusalem, a undisturbed settlement,A tent which will not be
        taken down;Not one of its stakes will ever be pulled up,Nor any of its ropes
        be severed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'But there the mighty and magnificent Lord will be for usA place of
        broad rivers and streams,Where no oar-driven boat will go,And on which no
        mighty and stately ship will pass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the Lord is our Judge,The Lord is our Ruler,The Lord is our King;He
        will save us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Your ship\u2019s ropes (tackle) hang loose;They cannot hold the base
        of their mast firmly,Nor spread out the sail.Then an abundance of spoil and
        plunder will be divided;Even the lame will take the plunder.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And no inhabitant [of Zion] will say, \u201CI am sick\u201D;The people
        who dwell there will be forgiven their wickedness [their sin, their injustice,
        their wrongdoing]."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Wrath against Nations"
      title: "God\u2019s Wrath against Nations"
      number: 1
      content: '  Come near, you nations, to hear; and listen, O peoples!Let the
        earth and all that is in it hear, and the world and all that comes forth
        from it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For the Lord is angry at all the nations,And His wrath is against
        all their armies;He has utterly doomed them,He has given them over to slaughter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So their slain will be thrown out,And the stench of their corpses
        will rise,And the mountains will flow with their blood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'All the host of heaven will be dissolved,And the skies will be rolled
        up like a scroll;All their hosts [the stars and the planets] will also wither
        awayAs a leaf withers from the vine,And as a fig withers from the fig tree.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For My sword is satiated [with blood] in heaven;Indeed, it will come
        down for judgment on EdomAnd on the people whom I have doomed for destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "The sword of the Lord is filled with blood [from sacrifices],It drips
        with fat, with the blood of lambs and goats,With the fat of the kidneys of
        rams.For the Lord has a sacrifice in Bozrah (Edom\u2019s capital city)And
        a great slaughter in the land of Edom.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Wild oxen will also fall with themAnd the young bulls with the strong
        bulls;And their land will be soaked with blood,And their dust made greasy
        with fat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For the Lord has a day of vengeance,A year of retribution for the
        cause of Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The streams [of Edom] will be turned into pitch,And its dust into
        brimstone,And its land will become burning pitch.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The burning will not be quenched night or day;Its smoke will go up
        forever.From generation to generation it will lie in ruins;No one will ever
        again pass through it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But the pelican and the porcupine will take possession of it;The
        owl and the raven will dwell in it.And He will stretch over it (Edom) the
        measuring line of desolationAnd the plumb line of emptiness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Its nobles\u2014there is no one thereWhom they may proclaim king\u2014And
        all its princes will be nothing.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Thorns will come up in its fortified palaces,Nettles and brambles
        in its fortified cities;It will be a haunt for jackals,An abode for ostriches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The creatures of the desert will encounter jackalsAnd the hairy goat
        will call to its kind;Indeed, Lilith (night demon) will settle thereAnd find
        herself a place of rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'There the arrow snake will make her nest and lay her eggs,And hatch
        them and gather her young under her protection;Indeed, the birds of prey
        will be gathered there [to breed],Every one with its own kind.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Seek from the book of the Lord, and read:Not one of these [creatures]
        will be missing;None will lack its mate.For His mouth has commanded,And His
        Spirit has gathered them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: The Lord has cast the lot for them,And His hand has divided and apportioned
        Edom to the wild beasts by measuring-line.They will possess it forever;From
        generation to generation they will dwell in it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zion\u2019s Joyful Future"
      title: "Zion\u2019s Joyful Future"
      number: 1
      content: '  The wilderness and the dry land will be glad;The Arabah (desert)
        will shout in exultation and blossomLike the autumn crocus.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'It will blossom abundantlyAnd rejoice with joy and singing.The glory
        of Lebanon will be given to it,The majesty of [Mount] Carmel and [the plain]
        of Sharon.They will see the glory of the Lord,The majesty and splendor of
        our God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Encourage the exhausted, and make staggering knees firm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Say to those with an anxious and panic-stricken heart,\u201CBe strong,
        fear not!Indeed, your God will come with vengeance [for the ungodly];The
        retribution of God will come,But He will save you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then the eyes of the blind will be openedAnd the ears of the deaf
        will be unstopped.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the lame will leap like a deer,And the tongue of the mute will
        shout for joy.For waters will break forth in the wildernessAnd streams in
        the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And the burning sand (mirage) will become a pool [of water]And the
        thirsty ground springs of water;In the haunt of jackals, where they lay resting,Grass
        becomes reeds and rushes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'A highway will be there, and a roadway;And it will be called the
        Holy Way.The unclean will not travel on it,But it will be for those who walk
        on the way [the redeemed];And fools will not wander on it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'No lion will be there,Nor will any predatory animal come up on it;They
        will not be found there.But the redeemed will walk there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: And the ransomed of the Lord will returnAnd come to Zion with shouts
        of jubilation,And everlasting joy will be upon their heads;They will find
        joy and gladness,And sorrow and sighing will flee away.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Sennacherib Invades Judah'
      title: Sennacherib Invades Judah
      number: 1
      content: '  Now in the fourteenth year of King Hezekiah, Sennacherib king of
        Assyria came up against all the fortified cities of Judah and conquered them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the king of Assyria sent the Rabshakeh [his military commander]
        from Lachish [the Judean fortress commanding the road from Egypt] to King
        Hezekiah at Jerusalem with a large army. And he stood by the canal of the
        Upper Pool on the highway to the Fuller\u2019s Field. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was in charge of the [royal]
        household, and Shebna the scribe, and Joah the son of Asaph, the recording
        historian, came out to [meet] him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh said to them, \u201CSay to Hezekiah, \u2018This
        is what the great king, the king of Assyria says, \u201CWhat is [the reason
        for] this confidence that you have? "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I say, \u2018Your plan and strength for the war are only empty words.\u2019
        Now in whom do you trust and on whom do you rely, that you have rebelled
        against me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Listen carefully, you rely on the staff of this broken reed, Egypt,
        which will pierce the hand of any man who leans on it. So is Pharaoh king
        of Egypt to all who rely on him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But if you say to me, \u2018We trust in and rely on the Lord our
        God,\u2019 is it not He whose high places and whose altars Hezekiah has taken
        away, saying to Judah and to Jerusalem, \u2018You shall worship before this
        altar\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So now, exchange pledges with my master the king of Assyria and I
        will give you two thousand horses, if you are able on your part to put riders
        on them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "How then can you repulse [the attack of] a single commander of the
        least of my master\u2019s servants, and rely on Egypt for chariots and for
        horsemen? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Moreover, is it without the Lord that I have now come up against
        this land to destroy it? The Lord said to me, \u2018Go up against this land
        and destroy it.\u2019\u2009\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Eliakim and Shebna and Joah said to the Rabshakeh, \u201CPlease,
        speak to your servants in Aramaic, because we understand it; and do not speak
        to us in Judean (Hebrew) in the hearing of the people who are [stationed]
        on the wall.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "But the Rabshakeh said, \u201CHas my master sent me to speak these
        words only to your master and to you, and not to the men sitting on the wall,
        doomed to eat their own dung and drink their own urine with you?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then the Rabshakeh stood and called out with a loud voice in Judean
        (Hebrew): \u201CHear the words of the great king, the king of Assyria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "This is what the king says, \u2018Do not let Hezekiah deceive you,
        for he will not be able to rescue you; "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "nor let Hezekiah make you trust in the Lord, saying, \u201CThe Lord
        will most certainly rescue us; this city will not be given into the hand
        of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Do not listen to Hezekiah,\u2019 for this is what the king of Assyria
        says, \u2018Make peace with me and come out to me, and each one of you will
        eat from his own vine and each from his own fig tree and each [one of you]
        drink from the water of his own cistern, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'until I come and take you away to a land like your own land, a land
        of grain and new wine, a land of bread and vineyards. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Beware that Hezekiah does not mislead you by saying, \u201CThe Lord
        will rescue us.\u201D Has any one of the gods of the nations [ever] rescued
        his land from the hand of the king of Assyria? "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Where are the gods of Hamath and Arpad [in Aram]? Where are the gods
        of Sepharvaim? And when have they rescued Samaria from my hand? '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Who among all the gods of these lands have rescued their land from
        my hand, that [you should think that] the Lord would rescue Jerusalem from
        my hand?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But they kept silent and did not say a word to him in reply, for
        King Hezekiah\u2019s command was, \u201CDo not answer him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Then Eliakim the son of Hilkiah, who was in charge of the household,
        and Shebna the scribe and Joah the son of Asaph, the recording historian,
        came to Hezekiah with their clothes torn [in grief], and told him the words
        of the Rabshakeh [the Assyrian commander].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Hezekiah Seeks Isaiah\u2019s Help"
      title: "Hezekiah Seeks Isaiah\u2019s Help"
      number: 1
      content: '  And when King Hezekiah heard this, he tore his clothes and covered
        himself with sackcloth and went into the house of the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then he sent Eliakim, who was in charge of the [royal] household,
        and Shebna the scribe, and the elders of the priests, covered with sackcloth,
        to Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "They said to him, \u201CThis is what Hezekiah says, \u2018This day
        is a day of distress, rebuke and disgrace; for children have come to birth,
        and there is no strength to deliver them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It may be that the Lord your God will hear the words of the Rabshakeh
        [the commander], whom his master the king of Assyria has sent to taunt and
        defy the living God, and will avenge the words which the Lord your God has
        heard. Therefore, offer a prayer for the remnant [of His people] that is
        left.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So the servants of King Hezekiah came to Isaiah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Isaiah said to them, \u201CYou shall say the following to your master:
        \u2018This is what the Lord says, \u201CDo not be afraid because of the words
        that you have heard, with which the servants of the king of Assyria have
        blasphemed Me. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Listen carefully, I will put a spirit in him so that he will hear
        a rumor and return to his own land. And I will make him fall by the sword
        in his own land.\u201D\u2009\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'So the Rabshakeh returned and found the king of Assyria fighting
        against Libnah [a fortified city of Judah], for he had heard that the king
        had left Lachish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And Sennacherib king of Assyria, heard them say concerning Tirhakah
        king of Cush (Ethiopia), \u201CHe has come out to fight against you.\u201D
        And when he heard it, he sent messengers to Hezekiah, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou shall say to Hezekiah king of Judah, \u2018Do not let your
        God in whom you trust deceive you, saying, \u201CJerusalem will not be given
        into the hand of the king of Assyria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Listen carefully, you have heard what the kings of Assyria have done
        to all lands, utterly destroying them. So will you be rescued? '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "Did the gods of the nations which my fathers destroyed rescue them\u2014Gozan,
        Haran [of Mesopotamia], Rezeph, and the sons of Eden who were in Telassar? "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer in the Temple"
      title: "Hezekiah\u2019s Prayer in the Temple"
      number: 13
      content: "Where is the king of Hamath, the king of Arpad [of northern Syria],
        the king of the city of Sepharvaim, [the king of] Hena, or [the king of]
        Ivvah?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then Hezekiah took the letter from the hand of the messengers and
        read it, and he went up to the house of the Lord and spread it out before
        the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And Hezekiah prayed to the Lord saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u201CO Lord of hosts, God of Israel, who is enthroned above the
        cherubim, You are the God, You alone, of all the kingdoms of the earth. You
        have made heaven and earth. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Incline Your ear, O Lord, and hear; open Your eyes, O Lord, and see;
        and hear all the words of Sennacherib that he has sent to taunt and defy
        the living God. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'It is true, O Lord, that the kings of Assyria have laid waste all
        the countries and their lands, '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "and have cast the gods [of those peoples] into the fire, for they
        were not gods but the work of men\u2019s hands, wood and stone. Therefore
        they have destroyed them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: God Answers through Isaiah'
      title: God Answers through Isaiah
      number: 20
      content: "Now, O Lord our God, save us from his hand so that all the kingdoms
        of the earth may know and fully realize that You alone, Lord, are God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then Isaiah son of Amoz sent word to Hezekiah, saying, \u201CFor
        the Lord, the God of Israel says this, \u2018Because you have prayed to Me
        about Sennacherib king of Assyria, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "this is the word that the Lord has spoken against him:\u201CShe has
        shown contempt for you and mocked you,The Virgin Daughter of Zion (Jerusalem);She
        has shaken her head behind you,The Daughter of Jerusalem!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Whom have you taunted and blasphemed?And against whom have you raised
        your voiceAnd haughtily lifted up your eyes?Against the Holy One of Israel!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Through your servants you have taunted and defied the Lord,And you
        have said, \u2018With my many chariots I have gone up to the heights of the
        mountains,To the remotest parts of Lebanon.I cut down its tallest cedars
        and its choicest cypress trees;And I will go to its remotest height, its
        most luxuriant and thickest forest.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "I dug wells and drank [foreign] waters,And with the sole of my feet
        I dried upAll the canals [of the Nile] of Egypt.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Have you not heard [says the God of Israel]That I did it long ago,That
        I planned it in ancient times?Now I have brought it to pass,That you [king
        of Assyria] would [be My instrument to] turn fortified cities into ruinous
        heaps.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Therefore their inhabitants had little power,They were terrorized
        and shamed;They were like the grass of the field and the green vegetation,Like
        grass on the housetops and like a field [of grain] scorched before it is
        grown.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But I know your sitting downAnd your going out and your coming in
        [every detail of your life],And your raging against Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Because your raging against MeAnd your arrogance has come up to My
        ears,I will put My hook in your noseAnd My bridle in your mouth,And I will
        turn you back by the way you came.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "\u201CThis shall be the sign [of these things] to you [Hezekiah]:
        you are to eat this year what grows of itself, and in the second year that
        which springs from the same, and in the third year you are to sow and harvest,
        and plant vineyards and eat their fruit. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'The surviving remnant of the house of Judah will again take root
        downward and bear fruit upward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For out of Jerusalem will come a remnant and from Mount Zion a band
        of survivors. The zeal of the Lord of hosts will do this.\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "\u201CTherefore, the Lord says this concerning the king of Assyria,
        \u2018He will not come into this city or shoot an arrow there, or come before
        it with shield, or raise an assault ramp against it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "By the way that he came, by the same way he will return, and he will
        not come into this city,\u2019 declares the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: Assyrians Destroyed'
      title: Assyrians Destroyed
      number: 35
      content: "\u2018For I will defend this city to save it, for My own sake and
        for the sake of My servant David.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And the angel of the Lord went out and struck 185,000 in the camp
        of the Assyrians; and when the [surviving] men got up early the next morning,
        they saw all the dead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed and returned and lived at
        Nineveh. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: It came to pass as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god,
        that Adrammelech and Sharezer his sons killed him with the sword; and they
        escaped into the land of Ararat [in Armenia]. And Esarhaddon his son became
        king in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Healed'
      title: Hezekiah Healed
      number: 1
      content: "  In those days Hezekiah [king of Judah] became sick and was at the
        point of death. And Isaiah the prophet, the son of Amoz, came to him and
        said, \u201CFor the Lord says this, \u2018Set your house in order and prepare
        a will, for you shall die; you will not live.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Then Hezekiah turned his face to the wall and prayed to the Lord, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "and said, \u201CPlease, O Lord, just remember how I have walked before
        You in faithfulness and truth, and with a whole heart [absolutely devoted
        to You], and have done what is good in Your sight.\u201D And Hezekiah wept
        greatly.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then the word of the Lord came to Isaiah, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CGo and say to Hezekiah, \u2018For the Lord, the God of David
        your father says this, \u201CI have heard your prayer, I have seen your tears;
        listen carefully, I will add fifteen years to your life. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will rescue you and this city from the hand of the king of Assyria;
        and I will defend this city [Jerusalem].\u201D\u2009\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CThis shall be the sign to you from the Lord, that the Lord
        will do this thing that He has spoken: "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Listen carefully, I will turn the shadow on the stairway [denoting
        the time of day] ten steps backward, the shadow on the stairway (sundial)
        of Ahaz.\u201D And the sunlight went ten steps backward on the stairway where
        it had [previously] gone down.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  This is the writing of Hezekiah king of Judah after he had been
        sick and had recovered from his illness:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "I said, \u201CIn mid-lifeI am to go through the gates of Sheol (the
        place of the dead),I am to be summoned, deprived of the remainder of my years.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "I said, \u201CI will not see the Lord,The Lord in the land of the
        living;I will no longer see man among the inhabitants of the world.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "My dwelling (body) is pulled up and removed from me like a shepherd\u2019s
        tent;I have rolled up my life as a weaver [rolls up the finished web].He
        cuts me free from the warp [of the loom];From day to night You bring me to
        an end.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I lay down until morning.Like a lion, so He breaks all my bones;From
        day until night You bring me to an end.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Like a swallow, like a crane, so I chirp;I coo like a dove.My eyes
        look wistfully upward;O Lord, I am oppressed, take my side and be my security.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhat shall I say?For He has spoken to me, and He Himself has
        done it;I will wander aimlessly all my years because of the bitterness of
        my soul.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'O Lord, by these things men live,And in all these is the life of
        my spirit;Restore me to health and let me live!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Indeed, it was for my own well-being that I had such bitterness;But
        You have loved back my life from the pit of nothingness (destruction),For
        You have cast all my sins behind Your back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'For Sheol cannot praise or thank You,Death cannot praise You and
        rejoice in You;Those who go down to the pit cannot hope for Your faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'It is the living who give praise and thanks to You, as I do today;A
        father tells his sons about Your faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The Lord is ready to save me;Therefore we will play my songs on stringed
        instrumentsAll the days of our lives at the house of the Lord.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Now Isaiah had said, \u201CHave them take a cake of figs and rub
        it [as an ointment] on the inflamed spot, that he may recover.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Hezekiah also had said, \u201CWhat is the sign that I will go up
        to the house of the Lord?\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Hezekiah Shows His Treasures'
      title: Hezekiah Shows His Treasures
      number: 1
      content: '  At that time Merodach-baladan son of Baladan, king of Babylon,
        sent [messengers with] letters and a present to Hezekiah, for he had heard
        that he had been sick and had recovered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Hezekiah was pleased and showed them his treasure house\u2014the
        silver, the gold, the spices, the precious oil, his entire armory and everything
        that was found in his treasuries. There was nothing in his house nor in all
        his area of dominion that Hezekiah did not show them. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Then Isaiah the prophet came to King Hezekiah and asked, \u201CWhat
        did these men say? From where have they come to you?\u201D And Hezekiah said,
        \u201CThey came to me from a far country, from Babylon.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then Isaiah said, \u201CWhat have they seen in your house?\u201D
        And Hezekiah answered, \u201CThey have seen everything that is in my house;
        there is nothing among my treasures that I have not shown them.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Then Isaiah said to Hezekiah, \u201CHear the word of the Lord of
        hosts, "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u2018Listen carefully, the days are coming when everything that
        is in your house and everything that your predecessors have stored up until
        this day will be carried to Babylon; nothing will be left,\u2019 says the
        Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u2018And some of your own sons (descendants) who will come from
        you, whom you will father, will be taken away, and they will become officials
        in the palace of the king of Babylon.\u2019\u2009\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "Then said Hezekiah to Isaiah, \u201CThe word of the Lord which you
        have spoken is good.\u201D For he thought, \u201CThere will be peace and
        faithfulness [to God\u2019s promises to us] in my days.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Greatness of God'
      title: The Greatness of God
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CComfort, O comfort My people,\u201D says your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSpeak tenderly to Jerusalem,And call out to her, that her time
        of compulsory service in warfare is finished,That her wickedness has been
        taken away [since her punishment is sufficient],That she has received from
        the Lord\u2019s handDouble [punishment] for all her sins.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "A voice of one is calling out,\u201CClear the way for the Lord in
        the wilderness [remove the obstacles];Make straight and smooth in the desert
        a highway for our God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Every valley shall be raised,And every mountain and hill be made
        low;And let the rough ground become a plain,And the rugged places a broad
        valley.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the glory and majesty and splendor of the Lord will be revealed,And
        all humanity shall see it together;For the mouth of the Lord has spoken it.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "A voice says, \u201CCall out [prophesy].\u201DThen he answered, \u201CWhat
        shall I call out?\u201D[The voice answered:] All humanity is [as frail as]
        grass, and all that makes it attractive [its charm, its loveliness] is [momentary]
        like the flower of the field.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The grass withers, the flower fades,When the breath of the Lord blows
        upon it;Most certainly [all] the people are [like] grass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The grass withers, the flower fades,But the word of our God stands
        forever.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "O Zion, herald of good news,Get up on a high mountain.O Jerusalem,
        herald of good news,Lift up your voice with strength,Lift it up, do not fear;Say
        to the cities of Judah,\u201CHere is your God!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Listen carefully, the Lord God will come with might,And His arm will
        rule for Him.Most certainly His reward is with Him,And His restitution accompanies
        Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He will protect His flock like a shepherd,He will gather the lambs
        in His arm,He will carry them in His bosom;He will gently and carefully lead
        those nursing their young.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who has measured the waters in the hollow of His hand,And marked
        off the heavens with a span [of the hand],And calculated the dust of the
        earth with a measure,And weighed the mountains in a balanceAnd the hills
        in a pair of scales?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who has directed the Spirit of the Lord,Or has taught Him as His
        counselor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'With whom did He consult and who enlightened Him?  Who taught Him
        the path of justice and taught Him knowledgeAnd informed Him of the way of
        understanding?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In fact, the nations are like a drop from a bucket,And are regarded
        as a speck of dust on the scales;Now look, He lifts up the islands like fine
        dust.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And [the forests of] Lebanon cannot supply sufficient fuel to start
        a fire,Nor are its wild beasts enough for a burnt offering [worthy of the
        Lord].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'All the nations are as nothing before Him,They are regarded by Him
        as less than nothing and meaningless.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'To whom then will you liken God?Or with what likeness will you compare
        Him?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: '  As for the cast image (idol), a metalworker casts it,A goldsmith
        overlays it with goldAnd a silversmith casts its silver chains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'He who is too impoverished for such an offering [to give to his god]Chooses
        a tree that will not rot;He seeks out for himself a skillful craftsmanTo
        [carve and] set up an idol that will not totter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Do you [who worship idols] not know? Have you not heard?Has it not
        been told to you from the beginning?Have you not understood from the foundations
        of the earth [the omnipotence of God and the stupidity of bowing to idols]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'It is He who sits above the circle of the earth,And its inhabitants
        are like grasshoppers;[It is He] who stretches out the heavens like a veilAnd
        spreads them out like a tent to dwell in.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'It is He who reduces dignitaries to nothing,Who makes the judges
        (rulers) of the earth meaningless (useless).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Scarcely have they been planted,Scarcely have they been sown,Scarcely
        has their stock taken root in the earth,But He merely blows on them, and
        they wither,And a strong wind carries them away like stubble.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CTo whom then will you compare MeThat I would be his equal?\u201D
        says the Holy One.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Lift up your eyes on highAnd see who has created these heavenly bodies,The
        One who brings out their host by number,He calls them all by name;Because
        of the greatness of His might and the strength of His power,Not one is missing.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Why, O Jacob, do you say, and declare, O Israel,\u201CMy way is hidden
        from the Lord,And the justice due me escapes the notice of my God\u201D?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Do you not know? Have you not heard?The Everlasting God, the Lord,
        the Creator of the ends of the earthDoes not become tired or grow weary;There
        is no searching of His understanding.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He gives strength to the weary,And to him who has no might He increases
        power.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Even youths grow weary and tired,And vigorous young men stumble badly,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: But those who wait for the Lord [who expect, look for, and hope in
        Him]Will gain new strength and renew their power;They will lift up their
        wings [and rise up close to God] like eagles [rising toward the sun];They
        will run and not become weary,They will walk and not grow tired.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Encouraged'
      title: Israel Encouraged
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CListen to Me in silence, you islands and coastlands,And let
        the nations gain their strength;Let them come near, then let them speak;Let
        us come together for judgment [and decide the issue between us concerning
        the enemy from the east].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Who has stirred up and put into action one from the east [the king
        of Persia, Cyrus the Great]Whom He calls in righteousness to His service
        and whom victory meets at every step?The Lord turns nations over to himAnd
        subdues kings.He makes them like dust with his sword,Like wind-driven chaff
        with his bow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He (Cyrus) pursues them and passes along safely,By a way his feet
        had not traveled before.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who has performed and done this,Calling forth [and guiding the destinies
        of] the generations [of the nations] from the beginning?\u2018I, the Lord\u2014the
        first, and with the last [existing before history began, the ever-present,
        unchanging God]\u2014I am He.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The islands and coastlands have seen and they fear;The ends of the
        earth tremble;They have drawn near and have come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "They each help his neighborAnd say to his brother [as he fashions
        his idols], \u201CBe of good courage!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "So the craftsman encourages the goldsmith,And he who smooths metal
        with the smith\u2019s hammer encourages him who beats the anvil,Saying of
        the soldering (welding), \u201CThat is good\u201D;And he fastens the idol
        with nails,So that it will not totter nor be moved.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CBut you, Israel, My servant,Jacob whom I have chosen,The offspring
        of Abraham My friend,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "You whom I [the Lord] have taken from the ends of the earth,And called
        from its remotest partsAnd said to you, \u2018You are My servant,I have chosen
        you and have not rejected you [even though you are exiled].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Do not fear [anything], for I am with you;Do not be afraid, for I
        am your God.I will strengthen you, be assured I will help you;I will certainly
        take hold of you with My righteous right hand [a hand of justice, of power,
        of victory, of salvation].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Indeed, all those who are angry with you will be put to shame and
        humiliated;Those who strive against you will be as nothing and will perish.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'You shall search for those who quarrel with you, but will not find
        them;They who war against you will be as nothing, as nothing at all.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "For I the Lord your God keep hold of your right hand; [I am the Lord],Who
        says to you, \u2018Do not fear, I will help you.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Do not fear, you worm Jacob, you men of Israel;I will help you,\u201D
        declares the Lord, \u201Cand your Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In fact, I have made of you a new, sharp threshing implement with
        sharp edges;You will thresh the mountains and crush them,And make the hills
        like chaff.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You will winnow them, and the wind will carry them away,And a high
        wind will scatter them;But you will rejoice in the Lord,You will glory in
        the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThe poor and needy are seeking water, but there is none;Their
        tongues are parched with thirst.I, the Lord, will answer them Myself;I, the
        God of Israel, will not neglect them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I will open rivers on the barren heightsAnd springs in the midst
        of the valleys;I will make the wilderness a reed-pool of waterAnd the dry
        land springs of water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will put the cedar in the wilderness,The acacia, the myrtle and
        the olive tree;I will place the juniper in the desertTogether with the box
        tree and the cypress,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So that they may see and know,And consider and understand together,That
        the hand of the Lord has done this,That the Holy One of Israel has created
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CPresent your case [for idols made by men\u2019s hands],\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201CProduce your evidence [of divinity],\u201DSays the king
        of Jacob.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Let them bring forward [their evidence] and tell us what is going
        to happen.Regarding the former events, tell what they were,That we may consider
        them and know their outcome;Or announce to us the things that are going to
        come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Tell us the things that are to come afterward,That we may know that
        you are gods;Indeed, you should do something good or do evil, that we may
        be afraid and fear [you] together [as we observe the miracle].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Hear this! You [idols] are less than nothing,And your work is worthless;The
        worshiper who chooses you [as a god] is repulsive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI have stirred up and put into action one from the north [the
        king of Persia, Cyrus the Great], and he has come;From the rising of the
        sun he will call on My Name [in prayer].And he will trample on [the Babylonian]
        officials as on mortar,Even as a potter treads clay.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Who [among the idols] has declared this from the beginning, so that
        we could know?Or from earlier times, so that we could say, \u201CHe is [unquestionably]
        right!\u201D?In fact, there was no one who declared it,Indeed, there was
        no one who proclaimed it;There was no one at all who heard you speak [for
        you pagan gods are speechless].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CI was first to say to Zion, \u2018Listen carefully, here they
        are [the Jews who will be restored to their own land].\u2019And to Jerusalem,
        \u2018I will provide a messenger (Isaiah) to bring the good news [that Cyrus
        will be stirred up and put into action to save them].\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'But when I look [on the pagan prophets and priests], there is no
        one [who could predict these events],And there is no counselor among them,Who,
        if I ask, can give an answer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: In fact, all of these [pagan prophets and priests] are false;Their
        works are worthless,Their cast images are [merely] wind and emptiness.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Promise concerning His Servant"
      title: "God\u2019s Promise concerning His Servant"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBehold, My Servant, whom I uphold;My Chosen One in whom My
        soul delights.I have put My Spirit upon Him;He will bring forth justice to
        the nations.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He will not call out or shout aloud,Nor make His voice heard in the
        street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'A broken reed He will not break [off]And a dimly burning wick He
        will not extinguish [He will not harm those who are weak and suffering];He
        will faithfully bring forth justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "He will not be disheartened or crushed [in spirit];[He will persevere]
        until He has established justice on the earth;And the coastlands will wait
        expectantly for His law.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'This is what God the Lord says,He who created the heavens and stretched
        them out,Who spread out the earth and its produce,Who gives breath to the
        people on itAnd spirit to those who walk on it,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CI am the Lord, I have called You (the Messiah) in righteousness
        [for a righteous purpose],I will also take You by the hand and keep watch
        over You,And I will appoint You as a covenant to the people [Israel],As a
        light to the nations (Gentiles),  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'To open the eyes of the blind,To bring out prisoners from the dungeonAnd
        those who sit in darkness from the prison.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'I am the Lord, that is My Name;My glory I will not give to another,Nor
        My praise to carved idols.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Indeed, the former things have come to pass,Now I declare new things;Before
        they spring forth I proclaim them to you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Sing to the Lord a new song,  Sing His praise from the end of the
        earth!You who go down to the sea, and all that is in it,You islands and coastlands,
        and those who inhabit them [sing His praise]!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Let the wilderness and its cities lift up their voices,The villages
        where Kedar lives.Let the inhabitants of Sela shout for joy,Let them shout
        joyfully from the tops of the mountains.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Let them give glory to the LordAnd declare His praise in the islands
        and coastlands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: The Blindness of the People'
      title: The Blindness of the People
      number: 13
      content: 'The Lord will go forth like a warrior,He will stir up His zeal like
        a man of war;He will shout out, yes, He will raise a war cry.He will prevail
        [mightily] against His enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "\u201CI [the Lord] have been silent for a long time,I have been still
        and restrained Myself.  Now I will moan like a woman in labor,I will both
        gasp and pant.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I will lay waste the mountains and hillsAnd wither all their vegetation;I
        will turn the rivers into coastlandsAnd dry up the ponds.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I will lead the blind by a way they do not know;I will guide them
        in paths that they do not know.I will make darkness into light before themAnd
        rugged places into plains.These things I will do [for them],And I will not
        leave them abandoned or undone.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Those who trust in carved idols will be turned back,And utterly put
        to shame,Who say to cast images,\u201CYou are our gods.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Hear, you deaf!And look, you blind, that you may see.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Who is blind but My servant [Israel],Or deaf like My messenger whom
        I send?Who is blind like the one who is at peace with Me [in a covenant relationship],Or
        so blind as the servant of the Lord?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'You have seen many things, but you do not observe them;  Your ears
        are open, but no one hears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "The Lord was pleased for His righteousness\u2019 sakeTo make the
        law great and prove to be glorious.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But this is a people despoiled and plundered;All of them are trapped
        in holes,Or are hidden away in prisons.They have become a prey with no one
        to rescue them,And a spoil, with no one to say, \u201CGive them back!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Who among you will listen to this?Who will listen and pay attention
        in the time to come?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Who gave up Jacob [the kingdom of Judah] for spoil, and [the kingdom
        of] Israel to the plunderers?Was it not the Lord, He against whom we [of
        Judah] have sinned,And in whose ways they [of Israel] were unwilling to walk,And
        whose law and teaching they did not obey?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: Therefore He poured out on Israel the heat of His angerAnd the fierceness
        of battle;And engulfed him in fire,Yet he did not recognize [the lesson of
        repentance which the Assyrian conquest was intended to teach];It burned him,
        but he did not take it to heart.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Redeemed'
      title: Israel Redeemed
      number: 1
      content: "  But now, this is what the Lord, your Creator says, O Jacob,And
        He who formed you, O Israel,\u201CDo not fear, for I have redeemed you [from
        captivity];I have called you by name; you are Mine!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'When you pass through the waters, I will be with you;And through
        the rivers, they will not overwhelm you.When you walk through fire, you will
        not be scorched,Nor will the flame burn you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I am the Lord your God,The Holy One of Israel, your Savior;I
        have given Egypt [to the Babylonians] as your ransom,Cush (ancient Ethiopia)
        and Seba [its province] in exchange for you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because you are precious in My sight,You are honored and I love you,I
        will give other men in return for you and other peoples in exchange for your
        life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Do not fear, for I am with you;I will bring your offspring from the
        east [where they are scattered],And gather you from the west.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "I will say to the north, \u2018Give them up!\u2019And to the south,
        \u2018Do not hold them back.\u2019Bring My sons from far wayAnd My daughters
        from the ends of the earth,  "
      comments: []
    - name: "7: Israel Is God\u2019s Witness"
      title: "Israel Is God\u2019s Witness"
      number: 7
      content: "Everyone who is called by My Name,Whom I have created for My glory,Whom
        I have formed, even whom I have made.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Bring out the people who are blind, even though they have eyes,And
        the deaf, even though they have ears.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "All the nations have gathered togetherSo that the peoples may be
        assembled.Who among them (the idolaters) can predict this [that Judah would
        return from captivity]And proclaim to us the former events?Let them provide
        their witnesses so that they may be justified,Or let them hear and say [in
        acknowledgement], \u201CIt is the truth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CYou are My witnesses,\u201D declares the Lord,\u201CAnd My
        servant whom I have chosen,That you may know and believe MeAnd understand
        that I am He.Before Me there was no God formed,And there will be none after
        Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'I, [only] I, am the Lord,And there is no Savior besides Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I have declared [the future] and saved [the nation] and proclaimed
        [that I am God],And there was no strange (alien) god among you;Therefore
        you are My witnesses [among the pagans],\u201D declares the Lord,\u201CThat
        I am God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Babylon to Be Destroyed'
      title: Babylon to Be Destroyed
      number: 13
      content: "Even from eternity I am He,And there is no one who can rescue from
        My hand;I act, and who can revoke or reverse it?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "This is what the Lord your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel says,\u201CFor
        your sake I have sent [one] to Babylon,And I will bring down all of them
        as fugitives,Even the Chaldeans [who reign in Babylon], into the ships over
        which they rejoiced.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "I am the Lord, your Holy One,The Creator of Israel, your King.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'This is what the Lord says,He who makes a way through the seaAnd
        a path through the mighty waters,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "He who brings out the chariot and the horse,The army and the mighty
        warrior,(They will lie down together, they will not rise again;They have
        been extinguished, they have been put out like a lamp\u2019s wick):  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CDo not remember the former things,Or ponder the things of the
        past.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Listen carefully, I am about to do a new thing,Now it will spring
        forth;Will you not be aware of it?I will even put a road in the wilderness,Rivers
        in the desert.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The beasts of the field will honor Me,Jackals and ostriches,Because
        I have given waters in the wildernessAnd rivers in the desert,To give drink
        to My people, My chosen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: The Shortcomings of Israel'
      title: The Shortcomings of Israel
      number: 21
      content: 'The people whom I formed for MyselfWill make known My praise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CYet you have not called on Me [in prayer and worship], O Jacob;But
        you have grown weary of Me, O Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'You have not brought Me your sheep or goats for your burnt offerings,Nor
        honored Me with your sacrifices.I have not burdened you with offerings,Nor
        wearied you with [demands for offerings of] incense.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'You have not bought Me sweet cane with money,Nor have you filled
        Me with the fat of your sacrifices;But you have burdened Me with your sins,You
        have wearied Me with your wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "\u201CI, only I, am He who wipes out your transgressions for My own
        sake,And I will not remember your sins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  Remind Me [of your merits with a thorough report], let us plead
        and argue our case together;State your position, that you may be proved right.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Your first father [Jacob] sinned,And your spokesmen [the priests
        and the prophets\u2014your mediators] have transgressed against Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: So I will profane the officials of the sanctuary,And I will consign
        Jacob to destruction and [I will subject] Israel to defamation and abuse.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Blessings of Israel'
      title: The Blessings of Israel
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CBut now listen, O Jacob, My servant,And Israel, whom I have
        chosen:  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "This is what the Lord who made youAnd formed you from the womb, who
        will help you says,\u2018Fear not, O Jacob My servant;And Jeshurun (Israel,
        the upright one) whom I have chosen.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For I will pour out water on him who is thirsty,And streams on the
        dry ground;I will pour out My Spirit on your offspringAnd My blessing on
        your descendants;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And they will spring up among the grassLike willows by the streams
        of water.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "One will say, \u2018I am the Lord\u2019s\u2019;And another will name
        himself after Jacob;And another will write on his hand, \u2018I am the Lord\u2019s,\u2019And
        be called by the [honorable] name of Israel.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CFor the Lord, the King of Israel and his Redeemer, the Lord
        of hosts says this,\u2018I am the First and I am the Last;And there is no
        God besides Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Who is like Me? Let him proclaim it and declare it;Yes, let him confront
        Me,Since I established the people of antiquity.And let them [those supposed
        gods] tell those people [who foolishly follow them] the things to comeAnd
        the events that are going to take place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The Folly of Idolatry'
      title: The Folly of Idolatry
      number: 8
      content: "Do not tremble nor be afraid [of the violent upheavals to come];Have
        I not long ago proclaimed it to you and declared it?And you are My witnesses.Is
        there a God besides Me?There is no other Rock;I know of none.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All who make carved idols are nothing. Their precious objects are
        worthless [to them], and their own witnesses (worshipers) fail to see or
        know, so that they will be put to shame. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who has made a god or cast an idol which is profitable for nothing? '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'In fact, all his companions will be put to shame, for the craftsmen
        themselves are mere men. Let them all assemble, let them stand up, let them
        be terrified, let them together be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "The ironsmith shapes iron and uses a chisel and works it over the
        coals. He forms the [idol\u2019s] core with hammers and works it with his
        strong arm. He also becomes hungry and his strength fails; he drinks no water
        and grows tired. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The carpenter stretches out a measuring line, he marks out the shape
        [of the idol] with red chalk; he works it with planes and outlines it with
        the compass; and he makes it like the form of a man, like the beauty of man,
        that it may sit in a house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He cuts cedars for himself, and takes a cypress or an oak and lets
        it grow strong for himself among the trees of the forest. He plants a fir,
        and the rain nourishes it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then it becomes fuel for a man to burn, so he takes one of them and
        warms himself; he also kindles a fire to bake bread. He also makes a god
        [from the same wood] and worships it. He makes it into a carved idol [with
        his own hands] and falls down and worships it! '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "He burns half of the wood in the fire; over this half he [cooks and]
        eats meat, he roasts meat and is satisfied. Also he warms himself and says,
        \u201CAha! I am warm, I have seen the fire.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But from what is left of the wood he makes a god, his carved idol.
        He falls down before it, he worships it and prays to it and says, \u201CSave
        me, for you are my god.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They do not know, nor do they understand, for God has muddied their
        eyes so that they cannot see, and their hearts (minds) as well so that they
        cannot understand. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "No one remembers, nor has knowledge and understanding [enough] to
        say [to himself], \u201CI have burned half of this log in the fire, and also
        baked bread on its coals and have roasted meat and eaten it. Then I make
        the rest of it into an repulsive thing [to God]; I bow down [to worship]
        before a block of wood!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: God Forgives and Redeems'
      title: God Forgives and Redeems
      number: 20
      content: "That kind of man (the idolater) feeds on ashes [and is satisfied
        with ashes]! A deceived mind has led him astray, so that he cannot save himself,
        or ask, \u201CIs this thing [that I am holding] in my right hand not a lie?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CRemember [the foolishness of] these things, O JacobAnd Israel,
        for you are My servant!I formed you, you are My servant;O Israel, you will
        not be forgotten by Me.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "I have wiped out your transgressions like a thick cloudAnd your sins
        like a heavy mist.Return to Me, for I have redeemed you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Shout for joy, O heavens, for the Lord has done it!Shout in triumph,
        you depths of the earth;Break forth into jubilant rejoicing, you mountains,O
        forest, and every tree in it!For the Lord has redeemed Jacob,And He shows
        His glory in Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "For the Lord, your Redeemer, and He who formed you from the womb
        says this,\u201CI am the Lord, Maker of all things,Who alone stretches out
        the heavens,Who spreads out the earth by Myself,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Frustrating the signs and confounding the omens of boasters (false
        prophets),Making fools out of fortune-tellers,Counteracting the wiseAnd making
        their knowledge ridiculous,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Confirming the word of His servantAnd carrying out the plan of His
        messengers.  It is I who says of Jerusalem, \u2018She shall [again] be inhabited!\u2019And
        of the cities of Judah, \u2018They shall [again] be built.\u2019And I will
        raise up and restore her ruins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "  It is I who says to the deep, \u2018Be dried up!\u2019And I will
        make your rivers dry.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "  It is I who says of Cyrus, \u2018He is My shepherd (ruler),And
        he will carry out all that I desire\u2014\u2019Saying of Jerusalem, \u2018She
        shall [again] be built,\u2019And of the temple, \u2018Your foundation shall
        [again] be laid.\u2019\u2009\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Uses Cyrus'
      title: God Uses Cyrus
      number: 1
      content: '  This is what the Lord says to His anointed, to Cyrus [king of Persia],Whose
        right hand I have heldTo subdue nations before him,And I will ungird the
        loins of kings [disarming them];To open doors before him so that gates will
        not be shut:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI will go before you and level the mountains;I will shatter
        the doors of bronze and cut through the bars of iron.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I will give you the treasures of darkness [the hoarded treasures]And
        the hidden riches of secret places,So that you may know that it is I,The
        Lord, the God of Israel, who calls you (Cyrus the Great) by your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For the sake of Jacob My servant,And of Israel My chosen,I have also
        called you by your name;I have given you an honorable nameThough you have
        not known Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I am the Lord, and there is no one else;There is no God except Me.I
        will embrace and arm you, though you have not known Me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'That people may know from the rising to the setting of the sun [the
        world over]That there is no one except Me.I am the Lord, and there is no
        other,  '
      comments: []
    - name: "7: God\u2019s Supreme Power"
      title: "God\u2019s Supreme Power"
      number: 7
      content: 'The One forming light and creating darkness,Causing peace and creating
        disaster;I am the Lord who does all these things.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRain down, O heavens, from above,Let the clouds pour down righteousness
        [all the blessings of God];Let the earth open up, let salvation bear fruit,And
        righteousness spring up with it;I, the Lord, have created it.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CWoe (judgment is coming) to him who quarrels with his Maker\u2014A
        [worthless] piece of broken pottery among other broken pieces [equally worthless]!Shall
        the clay say to the potter, \u2018What are you doing?\u2019Or does the thing
        say, \u2018He has no hands\u2019?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Woe (judgment is coming) to him who says to a father, \u2018What
        are you fathering?\u2019Or to a woman, \u2018With what are you in labor?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "For the Lord, the Holy One of Israel, and its Maker says this,\u201CAsk
        Me about the things to come concerning My sons,And give Me orders concerning
        the work of My hands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I made the earth and created man upon it.My hands, stretched out
        the heavens,And I commanded all their host.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I have stirred up Cyrus and put him into action in righteousness
        [to accomplish My purpose]And I will make all his ways smooth;He will build
        My city and let My exiles go,Without any payment or reward,\u201D says the
        Lord of hosts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For this is what the Lord says,\u201CThe products of Egypt and the
        merchandise of Cush (ancient Ethiopia)And the Sabeans, men of stature,Will
        come over to you and they will be yours;They will walk behind you, in chains
        [of subjection to you] they will come over,And they will bow down before
        you;They will make supplication to you, [humbly and earnestly] saying,  \u2018Most
        certainly God is with you, and there is no other,No other God [besides Him].\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Truly, You are a God who hides Himself,O God of Israel, Savior!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'They will be put to shame and also humiliated, all of them;They who
        make idols will go away together in humiliation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Israel has been saved by the LordWith an everlasting salvation;You
        will not be put to shame or humiliatedfor all eternity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "For the Lord, who created the heavens (He is God, who formed the
        earth and made it; He established it and did not create it to be a wasteland,
        but formed it to be inhabited) says this,\u201CI am the Lord, and there is
        no one else.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "I have not spoken in secret,In a corner of a land of darkness;I did
        not say to the descendants of Jacob,\u2018Seek Me in vain [with no benefit
        for yourselves].\u2019I, the Lord, speak righteousness [the truth\u2014trustworthy,
        a straightforward correlation between deeds and words],Declaring things that
        are upright.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CAssemble yourselves and come;Come together, you survivors of
        the nations!They are ignorant,Who carry around their wooden idols [in religious
        processions or into battle]And keep on praying to a god that cannot save
        them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Declare and present your defense of idols;Indeed, let them consult
        together.Who announced this [rise of Cyrus and his conquests] long before
        it happened?Who declared it long ago?Was it not I, the Lord?And there is
        no other God besides Me,A [consistently and uncompromisingly] just and righteous
        God and a Savior;There is none except Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Turn to Me and be saved, all the ends of the earth;For I am God,
        and there is no other.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'I have sworn [an oath] by Myself,The word is gone out of My mouth
        in righteousnessAnd shall not return,That to Me every knee shall bow, every
        tongue shall swear [allegiance].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "It shall be said of Me, \u2018Only in the Lord are righteousness
        and strength.\u2019To Him people will come,And all who were angry at Him
        will be put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "In the Lord all the offspring of IsraelWill be justified (declared
        free of guilt) and will glory [in God].\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Babylon\u2019s Idols and the True God"
      title: "Babylon\u2019s Idols and the True God"
      number: 1
      content: '  Bel has bowed down, Nebo stoops over;Their idols are on the beasts
        [of burden] and on the cattle.Your burdens [of idols] are loaded [on them],Burdens
        on the weary animals.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'They stooped over, they have bowed down together;They could not rescue
        the burden [of their own idols],But have themselves gone into captivity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CListen to Me,\u201D [says the Lord], \u201CO house of Jacob,And
        all the remnant of the house of Israel,You who have been carried by Me from
        your birthAnd have been carried [in My arms] from the womb,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Even to your old age I am He,And even to your advanced old age I
        will carry you!I have made you, and I will carry you;Be assured I will carry
        you and I will save you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CTo whom would you liken MeAnd make Me equal and compare Me,That
        we may be alike?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Those who lavish gold from the bagAnd weigh out silver on the scalesHire
        a goldsmith, and he makes it into a god;They bow down, indeed they worship
        it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'They lift it on their shoulders [in religious processions or into
        battle] and carry it;They set it in its place and there it remains standing.It
        cannot move from its place.Even if one cries to it [for help], the idol cannot
        answer;It cannot save him from his distress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CRemember this, and take courage;Take it to heart, you rebellious
        and disloyal people.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Remember [carefully] the former things [which I did] from ages past;For
        I am God, and there is no one else;  I am God, and there is no one like Me,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Declaring the end and the result from the beginning,And from ancient
        times the things which have not [yet] been done,Saying, \u2018My purpose
        will be established,And I will do all that pleases Me and fulfills My purpose,\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Calling a bird of prey from the east,From a far country, the man
        (Cyrus) of My purpose.Truly I have spoken; truly I will bring it to pass.I
        have planned it, be assured I will do it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, you stiff-necked people,You who are far from
        righteousness (right standing with God).  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: I bring near My righteousness [in the salvation of Israel], it is
        not far away;And My salvation will not delay.And I will grant salvation in
        Zion,And My glory for Israel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Lament for Babylon'
      title: Lament for Babylon
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCome down and sit in the dust,O virgin daughter of Babylon;Sit
        on the ground [in abject humiliation]; there is no throne for you,O daughter
        of the Chaldeans,For you will no longer be called tender and delicate.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Take millstones [as a female slave does] and grind meal;Remove your
        veil, strip off the skirt,Uncover the leg, cross the rivers [at the command
        of your captors].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Your nakedness will be uncovered,Your shame will also be exposed;I
        will take vengeance and will spare no man.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Our Redeemer [will do all this], the Lord of hosts is His name,The
        Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CSit in silence, and go into darkness,O daughter of the Chaldeans;For
        you will no longer be calledThe queen of kingdoms.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I was angry with My people,I profaned [Judah] My inheritanceAnd gave
        them into your hand [Babylon].You showed them no mercy;You made your yoke
        very heavy on the aged.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And you said, \u2018I shall be a queen forevermore.\u2019You did
        not consider these things,Nor did you [seriously] remember the [ultimate]
        outcome of such conduct.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CNow, then, hear this, you who live a luxuriant life,You who
        dwell safely and securely,Who say in your heart (mind),\u2018I am [the queen],
        and there is no one besides me.I shall not sit as a widow,Nor know the loss
        of children.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But these two things shall come to you abruptly, in one day:Loss
        of children and widowhood.They will come on you in full measureIn spite of
        your many [claims of power through your] sorceries,In spite of the great
        power of your enchantments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For you [Babylon] have trusted and felt confident in your wickedness;
        you have said,\u2018No one sees me.\u2019Your wisdom and your knowledge have
        led you astray,And you have said in your heart (mind),\u2018I am, and there
        is no one besides me.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Therefore disaster will come on you;You will not know how to make
        it disappear [with your magic].And disaster will fall on youFor which you
        cannot atone [with all your offerings to your gods];And destruction about
        which you do not knowWill come on you suddenly.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CPersist, then, [Babylon] in your enchantmentsAnd your many
        sorceriesWith which you have labored from your youth;Perhaps you will be
        able to profit [from them],Perhaps you may prevail and cause trembling.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'You are wearied by your many counsels.Just let the astrologers,The
        stargazers,Those who predict by the new moons [each month]Stand up and save
        you from the things that will come upon you [Babylon].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'In fact, they are like stubble;Fire burns them.They cannot save themselves
        from the power of the flame [much less save the nation],There is no blazing
        coal for warmingNor fire before which to sit!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: This is how they have become to you, those [astrologers and sorcerers]
        with whom you have labored,Those who have done business with you from your
        youth;Each has wandered in his own way.There is no one to save you.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Israel\u2019s Obstinacy"
      title: "Israel\u2019s Obstinacy"
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CHear this, O house of Jacob, you who are called by the name
        of IsraelAnd who come from the seed of Judah,You who swear [allegiance] by
        the name of the LordAnd invoke the God of Israel,  But not in truth (sincerity)
        nor in righteousness [with moral and spiritual integrity].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For they call themselves [citizens of Jerusalem] after the holy cityAnd
        depend on the God of Israel;The Lord of hosts is His name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'I have declared the former things [which happened to Israel] in times
        past;They went forth from My mouth and I proclaimed them;Suddenly I acted,
        and they came to pass.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Because I know that you are obstinate,And your neck is an iron tendonAnd
        your brow is bronze [both unyielding],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "I have declared them to you long ago;Before they came to pass I announced
        them to you,So that you could not say, \u2018My idol has done them,And my
        carved image and my cast image have commanded them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'You have heard [these things foretold]; look at all this [that has
        been fulfilled].And you, will you not declare it?I proclaim to you [specific]
        new things from this time,Even hidden things which you have not known.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "They are created now [called into being by the prophetic word] and
        not long ago;And before today you have not heard of them,So that you will
        not say, \u2018Oh yes! I knew them.\u2019  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'You have not heard, you have not known;Even from long ago your ear
        has not been open.For I [the Lord] knew that you [Israel] would act very
        treacherously;You have been called a transgressor and a rebel from birth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'For the sake of My Name I refrain from My wrath,And for My praise
        I restrain Myself from you,So that I do not cut you off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Indeed, I have refined you, but not as silver;I have tested and chosen
        you in the furnace of affliction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: End of Captivity Promised'
      title: End of Captivity Promised
      number: 11
      content: 'For My own sake, for My own sake, I will do it [I refrain and do
        not completely destroy you];For how can My Name be defiled and profaned [as
        it would if My chosen people were completely destroyed]?And I will not give
        My glory to another [by permitting the worshipers of idols to triumph over
        you].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CListen to Me, O Jacob, and Israel, whom I called;I am He, I
        am the First, I am the Last.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'My hand founded and established the earth,And My right hand spread
        out the heavens;When I call to them, they stand together [in obedience to
        carry out My decrees].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Assemble, all of you, and listen!Who among them [the idols and Chaldean
        astrologers] has declared these things?The Lord loves him (Cyrus of Persia);
        he will do His pleasure and purpose against Babylon,And his arm will be against
        the Chaldeans [who reign in Babylon].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'I, even I, have spoken; indeed, I have called Cyrus;I have brought
        him, and will make his way successful.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Come near to Me, listen to this:From the beginning I have not spoken
        in secret,From the time that it happened, I was there.And now the Lord God
        has sent Me, and His [Holy] Spirit.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "This is what the Lord, your Redeemer, the Holy One of Israel says,\u201CI
        am the Lord your God, who teaches you to profit (benefit),Who leads you in
        the way that you should go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Oh, that you had paid attention to My commandments!Then your peace
        and prosperity would have been like a [flowing] river,And your righteousness
        [the holiness and purity of the nation] like the [abundant] waves of the
        sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Your offspring would have been like the sand,And your descendants
        [in number] like the grains of sand;Their name would never be cut off or
        destroyed from My presence.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Get out of Babylon! Flee from the Chaldeans [who reign there]!Declare
        with a voice of jubilation, proclaim this,Send it out to the end of the earth;Say,
        \u201CThe Lord has redeemed His servant Jacob.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They did not thirst when He led them through the deserts.He made
        the waters flow out of the rock for them;He split the rock and the waters
        flowed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CThere is no peace for the wicked,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Salvation Reaches to the End of the Earth'
      title: Salvation Reaches to the End of the Earth
      number: 1
      content: '  Listen to Me, O islands and coastlands,And pay attention, you peoples
        from far away.The Lord has called Me from the womb;From the body of My mother
        He has named Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He has made My mouth like a sharp sword,In the shadow of His hand
        He has kept Me hidden;And He has made Me a sharpened arrow,In His quiver
        He has hidden Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And [the Lord] said to Me, \u201CYou are My Servant, Israel,In Whom
        I will show My glory.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Then I said, \u201CI have labored in vain,I have spent My strength
        for nothing and vanity (pride, uselessness);However My justice is with the
        Lord,And My reward is with My God.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And now says the Lord, who formed Me from the womb to be His Servant,To
        bring Jacob back to Him and that Israel might be gathered to Him,\u2014For
        I am honored in the eyes of the Lord,And My God is My strength\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "He says, \u201CIt is too trivial a thing that You should be My ServantTo
        raise up the tribes of Jacob and to restore the survivors of Israel;I will
        also make You a light to the nationsThat My salvation may reach to the end
        of the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "This is what the Lord, the Redeemer of Israel, Israel\u2019s Holy
        One says,To the thoroughly despised One,To the One hated by the nationTo
        the Servant of rulers,\u201CKings will see and arise,Princes shall also bow
        down,Because of the Lord who is faithful, the Holy One of Israel who has
        chosen You.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This is what the Lord says,\u201CIn a favorable time I have answered
        You,And in a day of salvation I have helped You;And I will keep watch over
        You and give You for a covenant of the people,To restore the land [from its
        present state of ruin] and to apportion and give as inheritances the deserted
        hereditary lands,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Saying to those who are bound and captured, \u2018Go forth,\u2019And
        to those who are in [spiritual] darkness, \u2018Show yourselves [come into
        the light of the Savior].\u2019They will feed along the roads [on which they
        travel],And their pastures will be on all the bare heights.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'They will not hunger or thirst,Nor will the scorching heat or sun
        strike them down;For He who has compassion on them will lead them,And He
        will guide them to springs of water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And I will make all My mountains a roadway,And My highways will be
        raised.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "In fact, these will come from far away;And, lo, these shall come
        from the north and from the west,And these from the land of Aswan (southern
        Egypt).\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: Promise to Zion'
      title: Promise to Zion
      number: 13
      content: 'Shout for joy, O heavens, and rejoice, O earth,And break forth into
        singing, O mountains!For the Lord has comforted His peopleAnd will have compassion
        on His afflicted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Zion (Jerusalem in captivity) said, \u201CThe Lord has abandoned
        me,And my Lord has forgotten me.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "[The Lord answered] \u201CCan a woman forget her nursing childAnd
        have no compassion on the son of her womb?Even these may forget, but I will
        not forget you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Indeed, I have inscribed [a picture of] you on the palms of My hands;Your
        city walls [Zion] are continually before Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Your builders hurry;Your destroyers and devastatorsWill go away from
        you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Lift up your eyes and look around [at the returning exiles];All these
        gather together and they come to you [to rebuild you].As I live,\u201D declares
        the Lord,\u201CYou [Zion] will indeed clothe yourself with all of them as
        jewels and tie them on as a bride.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "For your ruins and desolate places and your land [once the scene]
        of destruction\u2014Certainly now [in the coming years] will be too cramped
        for the inhabitants,And those who once engulfed you will be far away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "The children of your bereavement [those born in captivity] will yet
        say in your ears,\u2018The place is too cramped for me\u2019;Make room for
        me that I may live here.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then [Zion], you will say in your heart,\u2018Who has borne me these
        children,Since I have been bereaved of my childrenAnd am barren, an exile
        and a wanderer?And who has reared these?Indeed, I was left alone;  From where
        then did these children come?\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "This is what the Lord God says,\u201CListen carefully, I will lift
        up My hand to the [Gentile] nationsAnd set up My banner to the peoples;And
        they will bring your sons in the fold of their garments,And your daughters
        will be carried on their shoulders.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Kings will be your attendants,And their princesses your nurses.They
        will bow down to you with their faces to the earthAnd lick the dust of your
        feet;And you shall know [with an understanding based on personal experience]
        that I am the Lord;For they shall not be put to shame who wait and hope expectantly
        for Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CCan the spoils of war be taken from the mighty man,Or the captives
        of a tyrant be rescued?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Indeed, this is what the Lord says,\u201CEven the captives of the
        mighty man will be taken away,And the tyrant\u2019s spoils of war will be
        rescued;For I will contend with your opponent,And I will save your children.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "I will make those who oppress you consume their own flesh [in mutually
        destructive wars]And they will become drunk with their own blood as with
        sweet wine;And all mankind will know [with a knowledge grounded in personal
        experience] that I, the Lord, am your SaviorAnd your Redeemer, the Mighty
        One of Jacob.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: God Helps His Servant'
      title: God Helps His Servant
      number: 1
      content: "    The Lord declares this;\u201CWhere is the certificate of divorceBy
        which I have sent your mother away, [O Israel]?Or to which one of My creditors
        did I sell you [as slaves]?In fact, You were sold for your wickedness [your
        sin, your injustice, your wrongdoing],And for your transgressions your mother
        was sent away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why, when I came, was there no man [to greet Me]?When I called, why
        was there no one to answer?Is My hand really so short that it cannot redeem
        [My servants]?Or have I no power to rescue?Listen carefully, with My rebuke
        I dry up the sea,I make the rivers into a desert;Their fish stink because
        there is no waterAnd die of thirst.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "I clothe the heavens with the blackness [of storm clouds]And make
        sackcloth [of mourning] their clothing.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The Lord God has given Me [His Servant] the tongue of disciples [as
        One who is taught],That I may know how to sustain the weary with a word.He
        awakens Me morning by morning,He awakens My ear to listen as a disciple [as
        One who is taught].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord God has opened My ear,And I have not been rebelliousNor
        have I turned back.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'I turned My back to those who strike Me,And My cheeks to those who
        pluck out the beard;I did not hide My face from insults and spitting.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the Lord God helps Me,Therefore, I have not been ashamed or humiliated.Therefore,
        I have made My face like flint,And I know that I shall not be put to shame.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'He who declares Me in the right is near;Who will [dare to] contend
        with Me?Let us stand up to each other;Who is My adversary?Let him approach
        Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In fact, the Lord God helps Me;Who is he who condemns Me [as guilty]?Indeed,
        they will all wear out like a garment;The moth will eat them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Who is among you who fears the Lord,Who obeys the voice of His Servant,Yet
        who walks in darkness and has no light?Let him trust and be confident in
        the name of the Lord and let him rely on his God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: Listen carefully, all you who kindle your own fire [devising your
        own man-made plan of salvation],Who surround yourselves with torches,Walk
        by the light of your [self-made] fireAnd among the torches that you have
        set ablaze.But this you will have from My hand:You will lie down in [a place
        of] torment.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Israel Exhorted'
      title: Israel Exhorted
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CListen to Me, you who pursue righteousness (right standing
        with God),Who seek and inquire of the Lord:Look to the rock from which you
        were cutAnd to the excavation of the quarry from which you were dug.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Look to Abraham your fatherAnd to Sarah who gave birth to you in
        pain;For I called him when he was but one,Then I blessed him and made him
        many.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For the Lord will comfort Zion [in her captivity];He will comfort
        all her ruins.And He will make her wilderness like Eden,And her desert like
        the garden of the Lord;Joy and gladness will be found in her,Thanksgiving
        and the voice of a melody.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CListen carefully to Me [says the Lord], O My people,And hear
        Me, O My nation;For a [divine] law will go forth from Me,And I will quickly
        establish My justice as a light to the peoples.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'My righteousness (justice) is near, My salvation has gone forth,And
        My arms will judge the peoples;The islands and coastlands will wait for Me,And
        they will wait with hope and confident expectation for My arm.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Lift up your eyes to the heavens,Then look to the earth beneath;For
        the heavens will be torn to pieces and vanish like smoke,And the earth will
        wear out like a garmentAnd its inhabitants will die in like manner.But My
        salvation will be forever,And My righteousness (justice) [and faithfully
        fulfilled promise] will not be broken.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Listen to Me, you who know righteousness (right standing with God),The
        people in whose heart is My law and instruction;Do not fear the reproach
        and taunting of man,Nor be distressed at their reviling.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For the moth will eat them like a garment,And the worm will eat them
        like wool.But My righteousness and justice [faithfully promised] will exist
        forever,And My salvation to all generations.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Awake, awake, put on strength and might, O arm of the Lord;Awake
        as in the ancient days, as in the generations of long ago.Was it not You
        who cut Rahab (Egypt) in pieces,Who pierced the dragon [of Egypt]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Was it not You who dried up the [Red] Sea,The waters of the great
        deep,Who made the depths of the sea a pathwayFor the redeemed to cross over?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So the redeemed of the Lord will returnAnd come with joyful shouting
        to Zion;Everlasting joy will be on their heads.They will obtain gladness
        and joy,And sorrow and sighing will flee away.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CI, even I, am He who comforts you.Who are you that you are
        afraid of man who diesAnd of a son of man who is made [as destructible] as
        grass,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'That you have forgotten the Lord your Maker,Who stretched out the
        heavensAnd laid the foundations of the earth,That you continually tremble
        with fear all day long because of the rage of the oppressor,As he takes aim
        to destroy?And where is the rage of the oppressor?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The [captive] exile will soon be set free, and will not die in the
        dungeon, nor will his food be lacking. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For I am the Lord your God, who stirs up the sea so that its waves
        roar\u2014the Lord of hosts is His name. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "I have put My words in your mouth and have covered you with the shadow
        of My hand, to establish the [renewed] heavens and lay the foundations of
        the [renewed] earth, and to say to Zion (Jerusalem), \u2018You are My people.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Wake yourself up! Wake yourself up! Stand up, O Jerusalem,You who
        have drunk at the hand of the Lord the cup of His wrath,You who have drunk
        the cup of staggering and intoxication to the dregs [leaving only sediment].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'There is no one to guide her among all the sons she has borne,Nor
        is there anyone to take her by the hand among all the sons she has reared.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'These two tragedies have befallen you;Who will show sympathy for
        you and mourn with you?The desolation and destruction [on the land and city],
        famine and sword [on the inhabitants];How shall I comfort you?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Your sons have fainted;They lie helpless at the head of every street,Like
        an antelope in a net,Full [from drinking] of the wrath of the Lord,The rebuke
        of your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Therefore, now hear this, you who are afflicted,Who are drunk, but
        not with wine [but overwhelmed by the wrath of God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "So says your Lord, the Lord, who is also your GodWho pleads the cause
        of His people,\u201CListen carefully, I have taken from your hand the cup
        of staggering and intoxication,The cup of My wrath;You shall never drink
        it again.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "I will put it into the hands of your tormentors,Who have said to
        you, \u2018Lie down so that we may walk over you.\u2019You have even made
        your back like the groundAnd like the street for those who walk over it.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Cheer for Downtrodden Zion'
      title: Cheer for Downtrodden Zion
      number: 1
      content: '  Awake, awake,Put on your strength, O Zion;Put on your beautiful
        garments,O Jerusalem, the holy city;For the uncircumcised and the uncleanWill
        no longer come into you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Shake yourself from the dust, arise,O captive Jerusalem;Rid yourself
        of the chains around your neck,O captive Daughter of Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "For the Lord says this, \u201CYou were sold for nothing and you will
        be redeemed, but not with money.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For the Lord God says this, \u201CMy people went down at the first
        into Egypt to live there; and [many years later Sennacherib] the Assyrian
        oppressed them without cause. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But now, what do I have here,\u201D declares the Lord, \u201Cseeing
        that My people have been taken away without reason? Those who rule over them
        howl [with taunting and mockery of salvation],\u201D declares the Lord, \u201Cand
        My name is continually blasphemed all day long. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Therefore My people shall know My Name and what it means. Therefore
        in that day I am the One who is speaking, \u2018Here I am.\u2019\u2009\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "How beautiful and delightful on the mountainsAre the feet of him
        who brings good news,Who announces peace,Who brings good news of good [things],Who
        announces salvation,Who says to Zion, \u201CYour God reigns!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Listen! Your watchmen lift up their voices,Together they shout for
        joy;For they will see face to faceThe return of the Lord to Zion.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Break forth, shout joyfully together,You ruins of Jerusalem;For the
        Lord has comforted His people,He has redeemed Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The Lord has bared His holy arm (His infinite power)Before the eyes
        of all the nations [revealing Himself as the One by Whom Israel is redeemed
        from captivity],That all the ends of the earth may seeThe salvation of our
        God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Depart, depart, go out from there (the lands of exile),Touch no unclean
        thing;Go out of the midst of her (Babylon), purify yourselves,You who carry
        the articles of the Lord [on your journey from there].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Exalted Servant'
      title: The Exalted Servant
      number: 12
      content: 'For you will not go out in a hurry [as when you left Egypt],Nor will
        you go in flight [fleeing, as you did from the Egyptians];For the Lord will
        go before you,And the God of Israel will be your rear guard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Indeed, My Servant (the Messiah) will act wisely and prosper;He will
        be raised and lifted up and greatly exalted.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Just as many were astonished and appalled at you, My people,So His
        appearance was marred more than any manAnd His form [marred] more than the
        sons of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: So He will sprinkle many nations [with His blood, providing salvation],Kings
        will shut their mouths because of Him;For what they had not been told they
        will see,And what they had not heard they will understand.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Suffering Servant'
      title: The Suffering Servant
      number: 1
      content: '  Who has believed [confidently trusted in, relied on, and adhered
        to] our message [of salvation]?And to whom [if not us] has the arm and infinite
        power of the Lord been revealed?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For He [the Servant of God] grew up before Him like a tender shoot
        (plant),And like a root out of dry ground;He has no stately form or majestic
        splendorThat we would look at Him,Nor [handsome] appearance that we would
        be attracted to Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He was despised and rejected by men,A Man of sorrows and pain and
        acquainted with grief;And like One from whom men hide their facesHe was despised,
        and we did not appreciate His worth or esteem Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But [in fact] He has borne our griefs,And He has carried our sorrows
        and pains;Yet we [ignorantly] assumed that He was stricken,Struck down by
        God and degraded and humiliated [by Him].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'But He was wounded for our transgressions,He was crushed for our
        wickedness [our sin, our injustice, our wrongdoing];The punishment [required]
        for our well-being fell on Him,And by His stripes (wounds) we are healed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'All of us like sheep have gone astray,We have turned, each one, to
        his own way;But the Lord has caused the wickedness of us all [our sin, our
        injustice, our wrongdoing]To fall on Him [instead of us].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He was oppressed and He was afflicted,Yet He did not open His mouth
        [to complain or defend Himself];Like a lamb that is led to the slaughter,And
        like a sheep that is silent before her shearers,So He did not open His mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: '  After oppression and judgment He was taken away;And as for His
        generation [His contemporaries], who [among them] concerned himself with
        the factThat He was cut off from the land of the living [by His death]For
        the transgression of my people, to whom the stroke [of death] was due?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'His grave was assigned with the wicked,But He was with a rich man
        in His death,Because He had done no violence,Nor was there any deceit in
        His mouth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Yet the Lord was willingTo crush Him, causing Him to suffer;If He
        would give Himself as a guilt offering [an atonement for sin],He shall see
        His [spiritual] offspring,He shall prolong His days,And the will (good pleasure)
        of the Lord shall succeed and prosper in His hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "As a result of the anguish of His soul,He shall see it and be satisfied;By
        His knowledge [of what He has accomplished] the Righteous One,My Servant,
        shall justify the many [making them righteous\u2014upright before God, in
        right standing with Him],For He shall bear [the responsibility for] their
        sins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Therefore, I will divide and give Him a portion with the great [kings
        and rulers],And He shall divide the spoils with the mighty,Because He [willingly]
        poured out His life to death,And was counted among the transgressors;Yet
        He Himself bore and took away the sin of many,And interceded [with the Father]
        for the transgressors.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Fertility of Zion'
      title: The Fertility of Zion
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CShout for joy, O barren one, she who has not given birth;Break
        forth into joyful shouting and rejoice, she who has not gone into labor [with
        child]!For the [spiritual] sons of the desolate one will be more numerousThan
        the sons of the married woman,\u201D says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CEnlarge the site of your tent [to make room for more children];Stretch
        out the curtains of your dwellings, do not spare them;Lengthen your tent
        ropesAnd make your pegs (stakes) firm [in the ground].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For you will spread out to the right and to the left;And your descendants
        will take possession of nationsAnd will inhabit deserted cities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CDo not fear, for you will not be put to shame,And do not feel
        humiliated or ashamed, for you will not be disgraced.For you will forget
        the shame of your youth,And you will no longer remember the disgrace of your
        widowhood.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For your husband is your Maker,The Lord of hosts is His name;And
        your Redeemer is the Holy One of Israel,Who is called the God of the whole
        earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For the Lord has called you,Like a wife who has been abandoned, grieved
        in spirit,And like a wife [married] in her youth when she is [later] rejected
        and scorned,\u201DSays your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CFor a brief moment I abandoned you,But with great compassion
        and mercy I will gather you [to Myself again].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "In an outburst of wrathI hid My face from you for a moment,But with
        everlasting kindness I will have compassion on you,\u201DSays the Lord your
        Redeemer.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor this is like the waters of Noah to Me,As I swore [an oath]
        that the waters of NoahWould not flood the earth again;In the same way I
        have sworn that I will not be angry with youNor will I rebuke you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "For the mountains may be removed and the hills may shake,But My lovingkindness
        will not be removed from you,Nor will My covenant of peace be shaken,\u201DSays
        the Lord who has compassion on you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CO you afflicted [city], storm-tossed, and not comforted,Listen
        carefully, I will set your [precious] stones in mortar,And lay your foundations
        with sapphires.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And I will make your battlements of rubies,And your gates of [shining]
        beryl stones,And all your [barrier] walls of precious stones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And all your [spiritual] sons will be disciples [of the Lord],And
        great will be the well-being of your sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'You will be firmly established in righteousness:You will be far from
        [even the thought of] oppression, for you will not fear,And from terror,
        for it will not come near you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'If anyone fiercely attacks you it will not be from Me.Whoever attacks
        you will fall because of you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Listen carefully, I have created the smith who blows on the fire
        of coalsAnd who produces a weapon for its purpose;And I have created the
        destroyer to inflict ruin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "No weapon that is formed against you will succeed;And every tongue
        that rises against you in judgment you will condemn.This [peace, righteousness,
        security, and triumph over opposition] is the heritage of the servants of
        the Lord,And this is their vindication from Me,\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Free Offer of Mercy'
      title: The Free Offer of Mercy
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CEveryone who thirsts, come to the waters;And you who have
        no money come, buy grain and eat.Come, buy wine and milkWithout money and
        without cost [simply accept it as a gift from God].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why do you spend money for that which is not bread,And your earnings
        for what does not satisfy?Listen carefully to Me, and eat what is good,And
        let your soul delight in abundance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Incline your ear [to listen] and come to Me;Hear, so that your soul
        may live;And I will make an everlasting covenant with you,  According to
        the faithful mercies [promised and] shown to David.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Listen carefully, I have appointed him [David, representing the Messiah]
        to be a witness to the nations [regarding salvation],A leader and commander
        to the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "In fact, you [Israel] will call a nation that you do not know,And
        a nation that does not know you will run to you,Because of the Lord your
        God, even the Holy One of Israel;For He has glorified you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Seek the Lord while He may be found;Call on Him [for salvation] while
        He is near.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Let the wicked leave (behind) his wayAnd the unrighteous man his
        thoughts;And let him return to the Lord,And He will have compassion (mercy)
        on him,And to our God,For He will abundantly pardon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "\u201CFor My thoughts are not your thoughts,Nor are your ways My
        ways,\u201D declares the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CFor as the heavens are higher than the earth,So are My ways
        higher than your waysAnd My thoughts higher than your thoughts.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'For as the rain and snow come down from heaven,And do not return
        there without watering the earth,Making it bear and sprout,And providing
        seed to the sower and bread to the eater,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'So will My word be which goes out of My mouth;It will not return
        to Me void (useless, without result),Without accomplishing what I desire,And
        without succeeding in the matter for which I sent it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For you will go out [from exile] with joyAnd be led forth [by the
        Lord Himself] with peace;The mountains and the hills will break forth into
        shouts of joy before you,And all the trees of the field will clap their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Instead of the thorn bush the cypress tree will grow,And instead
        of the nettle the myrtle tree will grow;And it will be a memorial to the
        Lord,For an everlasting sign [of His mercy] which will not be cut off.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Rewards for Obedience to God'
      title: Rewards for Obedience to God
      number: 1
      content: "  This is what the Lord says,\u201CMaintain justice and do righteousness,For
        My salvation is soon to come,And My righteousness and justice is soon to
        be revealed.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Blessed (happy, fortunate) is the man who does this,And the son of
        man who takes hold of it,Who keeps the Sabbath without profaning it,And keeps
        his hand from doing any evil.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Do not let the foreigner who has joined himself to the Lord say,\u201CThe
        Lord will most certainly separate me from His people.\u201DAnd do not let
        the eunuch say, \u201CLook, I am a dry tree.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "This is what the Lord says,\u201CTo the eunuchs who keep My SabbathsAnd
        choose what pleases Me,And hold firmly to My covenant,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'To them I will give in My house and within My walls a memorial,And
        a name better than that of sons and daughters;I will give them an everlasting
        name which will not be cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "\u201CAlso the foreigners who join themselves to the Lord,To minister
        to Him, and to love the name of the Lord,To be His servants, everyone who
        keeps the Sabbath without profaning itAnd holds fast to My covenant [by conscientious
        obedience];  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "All these I will bring to My holy mountainAnd make them joyful in
        My house of prayer.Their burnt offerings and their sacrifices will be accepted
        on My altar;For My house will be called a house of prayer for all the peoples.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord God, who gathers the dispersed of Israel, declares:\u201CI
        will gather yet others to them (Israel), to those [already] gathered.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All you beasts of the field,All you beasts (hostile nations) in the
        forest,Come to eat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Israel\u2019s watchmen are blind,They are all without knowledge.They
        are all mute dogs, they cannot bark;Panting, lying down, they love to slumber.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the dogs are greedy; they never have enough.They are shepherds
        who have no understanding;They have all turned to their own way,Each one
        to his unlawful gain, without exception.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CCome,\u201D [they say,] \u201Clet us get wine, and let us fill
        ourselves with strong drink;And tomorrow will be like today, very great indeed.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Evil Leaders Rebuked'
      title: Evil Leaders Rebuked
      number: 1
      content: '  The righteous man perishes [at the hand of evil], and no one takes
        it to heart;Faithful and devout men are taken away, while no one understandsThat
        the righteous person is taken away [to be spared] from disaster and evil.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He enters into peace [through death];They rest in their beds (graves), 
        Each one who walked uprightly [following God\u2019s will, living with integrity].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CBut come here, you sons of a sorceress [raised in deception
        and superstition],Offspring of an adulterer and a prostitute.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Of whom do you make fun?Against whom do you open wide your mouthAnd
        stick out your tongue?Are you not children of rebellion (sin),Offspring of
        deceit,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Who inflame yourselves [with lust in pagan rites] among the oaks
        (terebinth trees),Under every green and leafy tree,Who slaughter the children
        [in sacrifice] in the ravinesUnder the clefts of the rocks?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Among the smooth stones of the ravineIs your portion, they (the idols)
        are your lot;Even to them you have poured out a drink offering,You have offered
        a grain offering.Should I be quiet concerning these things [leaving them
        unpunished\u2014bearing them with patience]?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Upon a high and lofty mountainYou have [openly and shamelessly] made
        your [idolatrous and adulterous] bed;Even there you went up to offer sacrifice
        [to idols, in spiritual unfaithfulness to Me].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Behind the door and the doorpostYou have set up your [pagan] symbol;Indeed,
        far removed from Me, you have uncovered yourself,And have gone up and made
        your bed wide.And you have made a [new] agreement for yourself with the adulterers,You
        have loved their bed,You have looked [with passion] on their manhood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'You have gone to the king [of a pagan land] with oilAnd increased
        your perfumes;You have sent your messengers a great distanceAnd made them
        go down to Sheol (the realm of the dead).  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "You were wearied by the length of your road,  Yet you did not say,
        \u2018It is no use.\u2019You found renewed strength,Therefore you did not
        grow weak.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "\u201CAbout whom were you worried and fearfulThat you lied and did
        not remember Me,Nor give Me a thought?Was I not silent even for a long timeAnd
        [as a result] you do not fear Me?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'I will declare your [hypocritical] righteousness and your deeds,But
        they will not benefit you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "When you cry out [for help], let your [ridiculous] collection of
        idols save you.But the wind will carry them all away,A [mere] breath will
        take them.But he who takes refuge in Me will possess the land [Judea]And
        will inherit My holy mountain.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And it will be said,\u201CBuild up, build up, clear the way.Remove
        the stumbling block out of the way [of the spiritual return] of My people.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "For the high and exalted OneHe who inhabits eternity, Whose name
        is Holy says this,\u201CI dwell on the high and holy place,But also with
        the contrite and humble in spiritIn order to revive the spirit of the humbleAnd
        to revive the heart of the contrite [overcome with sorrow for sin].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For I will not contend forever,Nor will I always be angry;For [if
        I did stay angry] the spirit [of man] would grow weak before Me,And the breath
        of those whom I have created.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Because of the wickedness of his unjust gain I was angry and struck
        him;I hid My face and was angry,And he went on turning away and backsliding,
        in the way of his [own willful] heart.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'I have seen his [willful] ways, but I will heal him;I will lead him
        [also] and will restore comfort to him and to those who mourn for him,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "As I create the praise of his lips,Peace, peace, to him who is far
        away [both Jew and Gentile] and to him who is near!\u201DSays the Lord;\u201CAnd
        I will heal him [making his lips blossom anew with thankful praise].\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'But the wicked are like the tossing sea,For it cannot be quiet,And
        its waters toss up mire and mud.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CThere is no peace,\u201D says my God, \u201Cfor the wicked.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Observances of Fasts'
      title: Observances of Fasts
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CCry aloud, do not hold back;Lift up your voice like a trumpet,And
        declare to My people their transgressionAnd to the house of Jacob their sins.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Yet they seek Me day by day and delight [superficially] to know My
        ways,As [if they were in reality] a nation that has done righteousnessAnd
        has not abandoned (turned away from) the ordinance of their God.They ask
        of Me righteous judgments,They delight in the nearness of God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Why have we fasted,\u2019 they say, \u2018and You do not see
        it?Why have we humbled ourselves and You do not notice?\u2019Hear this [O
        Israel], on the day of your fast [when you should be grieving for your sins]
        you find something you desire [to do],And you force your hired servants to
        work [instead of stopping all work, as the law teaches].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The facts are that you fast only for strife and brawling and to strike
        with the fist of wickedness.You do not fast as you do today to make your
        voice heard on high.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Is a fast such as this what I have chosen, a day for a man to humble
        himself [with sorrow in his soul]?Is it only to bow down his head like a
        reedAnd to make sackcloth and ashes as a bed [pretending to have a repentant
        heart]?Do you call this a fast and a day pleasing to the Lord?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: '[Rather] is this not the fast which I choose,To undo the bonds of
        wickedness,To tear to pieces the ropes of the yoke,To let the oppressed go
        freeAnd break apart every [enslaving] yoke?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Is it not to divide your bread with the hungryAnd bring the homeless
        poor into the house;When you see the naked, that you cover him,And not to
        hide yourself from [the needs of] your own flesh and blood?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then your light will break out like the dawn,And your healing (restoration,
        new life) will quickly spring forth;Your righteousness will go before you
        [leading you to peace and prosperity],The glory of the Lord will be your
        rear guard.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then you will call, and the Lord will answer;You will cry for help,
        and He will say, \u2018Here I am.\u2019If you take away from your midst the
        yoke [of oppression],The finger pointed in scorn [toward the oppressed or
        the godly], and [every form of] wicked (sinful, unjust) speech,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And if you offer yourself to [assist] the hungryAnd satisfy the need
        of the afflicted,Then your light will rise in darknessAnd your gloom will
        become like midday.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the Lord will continually guide you,And satisfy your soul in
        scorched and dry places,And give strength to your bones;And you will be like
        a watered garden,And like a spring of water whose waters do not fail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Keeping the Sabbath'
      title: Keeping the Sabbath
      number: 12
      content: 'And your people will rebuild the ancient ruins;You will raise up
        and restore the age-old foundations [of buildings that have been laid waste];You
        will be called Repairer of the Breach,Restorer of Streets with Dwellings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "\u201CIf you turn back your foot from [unnecessary travel on] the
        Sabbath,From doing your own pleasure on My holy day,And call the Sabbath
        a [spiritual] delight, and the holy day of the Lord honorable,And honor it,
        not going your own wayOr engaging in your own pleasureOr speaking your own
        [idle] words,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then you will take pleasure in the Lord,And I will make you ride
        on the high places of the earth,And I will feed you with the [promised] heritage
        of Jacob your father;For the mouth of the Lord has spoken.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Separation from God'
      title: Separation from God
      number: 1
      content: "  Behold, the Lord\u2019s hand is not so shortThat it cannot save,Nor
        His ear so impairedThat it cannot hear.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But your wickedness has separated you from your God,And your sins
        have hidden His face from you so that He does not hear.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'For your hands are defiled with bloodAnd your fingers with wickedness
        [with sin, with injustice, with wrongdoing];Your lips have spoken lies,Your
        tongue mutters wickedness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "No one sues righteously [but for the sake of doing injury to others\u2014to
        take some undue advantage], and no one pleads [his case] in truth; [but rather]They
        trust in empty arguments and speak lies;They conceive trouble and bring forth
        injustice.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "They hatch vipers\u2019 eggs and weave the spider\u2019s webs;He
        who eats of their eggs dies,And from an egg which is crushed a viper breaks
        out.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Their webs will not serve as clothing,Nor will they cover themselves
        with what they make;Their works are works of wickedness [of sin, of injustice,
        of wrongdoing],And the act of violence is in their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Their feet run to evil,And they rush to shed innocent blood.Their
        thoughts are thoughts of wickedness [of sin, of injustice, of wrongdoing];Devastation
        and destruction are in their highways.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: A Confession of Wickedness'
      title: A Confession of Wickedness
      number: 8
      content: 'They do not know the way of peace,And there is no justice in their
        tracks.They have made them into crooked paths;Whoever walks on them does
        not know peace.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Therefore justice is far from us,And righteousness does not overtake
        us.We [expectantly] hope for light, but only see darkness;  We hope for gleam
        of light, but we walk in darkness and gloom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'We grope for a wall like the blind,We grope like those who have no
        eyes.We stumble at midday as in the twilight;Among those who are healthy
        we are like dead men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'We all groan and growl like bears,And coo sadly like doves;We hope
        for justice, but there is none,For salvation, but it is far from us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For our transgressions are multiplied before You [O Lord],And our
        sins testify against us;For our transgressions are with us,And we know and
        recognize our wickedness [our sin, our injustice, our wrongdoing]:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Rebelling against and denying the Lord,Turning away from [following]
        our God,Speaking oppression and revolt,Conceiving and muttering from the
        heart lying words.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Justice is pushed back,And righteous behavior stands far away;For
        truth has fallen in the city square,And integrity cannot enter.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Yes, truth is missing;And he who turns away from evil makes himself
        a prey.  Now the Lord saw it,And it displeased Him that there was no justice.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He saw that there was no man,And was amazed that there was no one
        to intercede [on behalf of truth and right];Therefore His own arm brought
        salvation to Him,And His own righteousness sustained Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For He [the Lord] put on righteousness like a coat of armor,And salvation
        like a helmet on His head;He put on garments of vengeance for clothingAnd
        covered Himself with zeal [and great love for His people] as a cloak.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'As their deeds deserve, so He will repay:Wrath to His adversaries,
        retribution to His enemies;To the islands and coastlands He will repay.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So they will fear the name of the Lord from the westAnd His glory
        from the rising of the sun.For He will come in like a narrow, rushing streamWhich
        the breath of the Lord drives [overwhelming the enemy].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "\u201CA Redeemer (Messiah) will come to Zion,And to those in Jacob
        (Israel) who turn from transgression (sin),\u201D declares the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "\u201CAs for Me, this is My covenant with them,\u201D says the Lord:
        \u201CMy Spirit which is upon you [writing the law of God on the heart],
        and My words which I have put in your mouth shall not depart from your mouth,
        nor from the mouths of your [true, spiritual] children, nor from the mouth
        of your children\u2019s children,\u201D says the Lord, \u201Cfrom now and
        forever.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Glorified Zion'
      title: A Glorified Zion
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CArise [from spiritual depression to a new life], shine [be
        radiant with the glory and brilliance of the Lord]; for your light has come,And
        the glory and brilliance of the Lord has risen upon you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'For in fact, darkness will cover the earthAnd deep darkness will
        cover the peoples;But the Lord will rise upon you [Jerusalem]And His glory
        and brilliance will be seen on you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Nations will come to your light,And kings to the brightness of your
        rising.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CLift up your eyes around you and see;They all gather together,
        they come to you.Your sons will come from far away,And your daughters will
        be looked after at their side.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Then you will see and be radiant,And your heart will tremble [with
        joy] and rejoiceBecause the abundant wealth of the seas will be brought to
        you,The wealth of the nations will come to you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'A multitude of camels [from the eastern trading tribes] will cover
        you [Jerusalem],The young camels of Midian and Ephah;All those from Sheba
        [who once came to trade] will comeBringing gold and frankincenseAnd proclaiming
        the praises of the Lord.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'All the flocks of Kedar will be gathered to you [as the eastern pastoral
        tribes join the trading tribes],The rams of Nebaioth will serve you;They
        will go up with acceptance [as sacrifices] on My altar,And I will glorify
        the house of My honor and splendor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who are these who fly like a cloudAnd like doves to their windows?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'The islands and coastlands will confidently wait for Me;And the ships
        of Tarshish will come first,To bring your sons from far away,Their silver
        and gold with them,For the name of the Lord your God,For the Holy One of
        Israel because He has glorified you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CForeigners will build up your walls,And their kings will serve
        you;For in My [righteous] wrath I struck you,But in My favor and grace I
        have had compassion on you.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Your gates will be open continually;They shall not be shut day or
        night,So that people may bring to you the wealth of the nations\u2014With
        their kings led in procession.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'For the nation or the kingdom which will not serve you [Jerusalem]
        shall perish,And the nations [that refuse to serve] shall be utterly ruined.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'The glory of Lebanon will come to you,The cypress, the juniper, and
        the cedar together,To beautify the place of My sanctuary;And I will honor
        and make the place of My feet glorious.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The sons of those who oppressed you will come bowing down to you
        [in submission],And all those who despised you and treated you disrespectfully
        will bow down at the soles of your feet,And they will call you the City of
        the Lord,The Zion of the Holy One of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "\u201CWhereas you [Jerusalem] have been abandoned and hatedWith no
        one passing through,I will make you an object of pride forever,A joy from
        generation to generation.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'You will suck the milk of the [Gentile] nationsAnd suck the breast
        (abundance) of kings;Then you will recognize and know that I, the Lord, am
        your SaviorAnd your Redeemer, the Mighty One of Jacob.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Instead of bronze I will bring gold,And instead of iron I will bring
        silver,And instead of wood, bronze,And instead of stones, iron.And [instead
        of the tyranny of the present] I will appoint peace as your officers,And
        righteousness your rulers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Violence will not be heard again in your land,Nor devastation or
        destruction within your borders;But you will call your walls Salvation, and
        your gates Praise [to God].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The sun will no longer be your light by day,Nor shall the bright
        glow of the moon give light to you,But the Lord will be an everlasting light
        for you;And your God will be your glory and splendor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Your sun will no longer set,Nor will your moon wane;For the Lord
        will be your everlasting light,And the days of your mourning will be over.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then all your people will be [uncompromisingly and consistently]
        righteous;They will possess the land forever,The branch of My planting,The
        work of My hands,That I may be glorified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "The smallest one will become a thousand (a clan),And the least one
        a mighty nation.I, the Lord, will quicken it in its [appointed] time.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Exaltation of the Afflicted'
      title: Exaltation of the Afflicted
      number: 1
      content: '  The Spirit of the Lord God is upon me,Because the Lord has anointed
        and commissioned meTo bring good news to the humble and afflicted;He has
        sent me to bind up [the wounds of] the brokenhearted,To proclaim release
        [from confinement and condemnation] to the [physical and spiritual] captivesAnd
        freedom to prisoners,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'To proclaim the favorable year of the Lord,  And the day of vengeance
        and retribution of our God,To comfort all who mourn,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'To grant to those who mourn in Zion the following:To give them a
        turban instead of dust [on their heads, a sign of mourning],The oil of joy
        instead of mourning,The garment [expressive] of praise instead of a disheartened
        spirit.So they will be called the trees of righteousness [strong and magnificent,
        distinguished for integrity, justice, and right standing with God],The planting
        of the Lord, that He may be glorified.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Then they will rebuild the ancient ruins,They will raise up and restore
        the former desolations;And they will renew the ruined cities,The desolations
        (deserted settlements) of many generations.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Strangers will stand and feed your flocks,And foreigners will be
        your farmers and your vinedressers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But you shall be called the priests of the Lord;People will speak
        of you as the ministers of our God.You will eat the wealth of nations,And
        you will boast of their riches.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Instead of your [former] shame you will have a double portion;And
        instead of humiliation your people will shout for joy over their portion.Therefore
        in their land they will possess double [what they had forfeited];Everlasting
        joy will be theirs.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'For I, the Lord, love justice;I hate robbery with a burnt offering.And
        I will faithfully reward them,And make an everlasting covenant with them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Then their offspring will be known among the nations,And their descendants
        among the peoples.All who see them [in their prosperity] will recognize and
        acknowledge themThat they are the people whom the Lord has blessed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'I will rejoice greatly in the Lord,My soul will exult in my God;For
        He has clothed me with garments of salvation,He has covered me with a robe
        of righteousness,As a bridegroom puts on a turban,And as a bride adorns herself
        with her jewels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: For as the earth brings forth its sprouts,And as a garden causes what
        is sown in it to spring up,So the Lord God will [most certainly] cause righteousness
        and justice and praiseTo spring up before all the nations [through the power
        of His word].
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Zion\u2019s Glory and New Name"
      title: "Zion\u2019s Glory and New Name"
      number: 1
      content: "  For Zion\u2019s sake I (Isaiah) will not be silent,And for Jerusalem\u2019s
        sake I will not keep quiet,Until her righteousness and vindication go forth
        as brightness,And her salvation goes forth like a burning torch.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The nations will see your righteousness and vindication [by God],And
        all kings [will see] your glory;And you will be called by a new nameWhich
        the mouth of the Lord will designate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'You will also be [considered] a crown of glory and splendor in the
        hand of the Lord,And a royal diadem [exceedingly beautiful] in the hand of
        your God.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "It will no longer be said of you [Judah], \u201CAzubah (Abandoned),\u201DNor
        will it any longer be said of your land, \u201CShemamah (Desolate)\u201D;But
        you will be called, \u201CHephzibah (My Delight is in Her),\u201DAnd your
        land, \u201CMarried\u201D;For the Lord delights in you,And to Him your land
        will be married [owned and protected by the Lord].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For as a young man marries a virgin [O Jerusalem],  So your sons
        will marry you;And as the bridegroom rejoices over the bride,So your God
        will rejoice over you.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'On your walls, O Jerusalem, I have appointed and stationed watchmen
        (prophets),Who will never keep silent day or night;You who profess the Lord,
        take no rest for yourselves,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And give Him no rest [from your prayers] until He establishes JerusalemAnd
        makes her a praise on the earth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "The Lord has sworn [an oath] by His right hand and by His mighty
        arm,\u201CI will never again give your grain as food for your enemies,Nor
        will [the invading] foreigners drink your new wine for which you have labored.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But they who have harvested it will eat it and praise the Lord,And
        they who have gathered it will drink it [at the feasts celebrated] in the
        courtyards of My sanctuary.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Go through, go through the gates,Clear the way for the people;Build
        up, build up the highway,Remove the stones, lift up a banner over the peoples.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Listen carefully, the Lord has proclaimed to the end of the earth,Say
        to the Daughter of Zion, \u201CLook now, your salvation is coming [in the
        Lord];Indeed, His reward is with Him, and His restitution accompanies Him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And they will call them \u201CThe Holy People,The Redeemed of the
        Lord\u201D;And you will be called \u201CSought Out, A City Not Deserted.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: God\u2019s Vengeance on the Nations"
      title: "God\u2019s Vengeance on the Nations"
      number: 1
      content: "  Who is this who comes from Edom,With crimson-stained garments from
        Bozrah [in Edom],This One (the Messiah) who is majestic in His apparel,Marching
        in the greatness of His might?\u201CIt is I, [the One] who speaks in righteousness
        [proclaiming vindication], mighty to save.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Why is Your apparel red,And Your garments like the one who treads
        in the wine press?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CI have trodden the wine trough alone,And of the peoples there
        was no one with Me.I also trod them in My angerAnd trampled them in My wrath;And
        their lifeblood is sprinkled on My garments,And I stained all My clothes.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "For the day of vengeance [against ungodliness] was in My heart,And
        My year of redemption [of those who put their trust in Me\u2014the year of
        My redeemed] has come.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'I looked, but there was no one to help,And I was amazed and appalled
        that there was no one to uphold [truth and right].So My own arm brought salvation
        to Me,And My wrath sustained Me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "6: God\u2019s Ancient Mercies Recalled"
      title: "God\u2019s Ancient Mercies Recalled"
      number: 6
      content: "I trampled the peoples in My angerAnd made them drunk with [the cup
        of] My wrath,And I spilled their lifeblood on the earth.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'I will tell of the lovingkindnesses of the Lord, and the praiseworthy
        deeds of the Lord,According to all that the Lord has done for us,And His
        great goodness toward the house of Israel,Which He has shown them according
        to His compassionAnd according to the abundance of His lovingkindnesses.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "For He said, \u201CBe assured, they are My people,Sons who will not
        be faithless.\u201DSo He became their Savior [in all their distresses].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In all their distress He was distressed,And the angel of His presence
        saved them,In His love and in His compassion He redeemed them;And He lifted
        them up and carried them all the days of old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'But they rebelledAnd grieved His Holy Spirit;Therefore He changed
        into their enemy,And He fought against them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Then His people remembered the days of old, of Moses [and they said],Where
        is He who brought our fathers up out of the [Red] Sea, with the shepherds
        of His flock [Moses and Aaron]?Where is He who put His Holy Spirit in their
        midst,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Who caused His glorious arm and infinite power to go at the right
        hand of Moses,Dividing the waters before them to make for Himself an everlasting
        name,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Who led them through the depths [of the Red Sea],Like a horse in
        the wilderness, [so that] they did not stumble?  '
      comments: []
    - name: "14: \u201CYou Are Our Father\u201D"
      title: "\u201CYou Are Our Father\u201D"
      number: 14
      content: 'Like the cattle that go down into the valley [to find better pasture
        and rest],The Spirit of the Lord gave them rest.So You led Your people [O
        Lord]To make for Yourself a beautiful and glorious name [preparing the way
        for the acknowledgment of Your name by all nations].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Look down from heaven and see from Your lofty dwelling place, holy
        and glorious.Where are Your zeal and Your mighty acts [Your miracles which
        you did for Your people]?The stirring of Your heart and Your compassion are
        restrained and withheld from me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For [most certainly] You are our Father, even though Abraham [our
        ancestor] does not know usAnd Israel does not acknowledge us.You, O Lord,
        are [still] our Father,Our Redeemer from everlasting is Your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "O Lord, why do You cause us to stray from Your waysAnd harden our
        heart from fearing You [with reverence and awe]?Return for Your servants\u2019
        sake, the tribes of Your heritage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Your holy people possessed Your sanctuary for [only] a little while;Our
        adversaries have trampled it down.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: We have become like those over whom You have never ruled,  Like those
        who were not called by Your name.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prayer for Mercy and Help'
      title: Prayer for Mercy and Help
      number: 1
      content: "  Oh, that You would tear open the heavens and come down,That the
        mountains might quake at Your presence\u2014  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "As [sure as] fire kindles the brushwood, as fire causes water to
        boil\u2014To make Your name known to Your adversaries,That the nations may
        tremble at Your presence!  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'When You did awesome and amazing things which we did not expect,You
        came down [at Sinai]; the mountains quaked at Your presence.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For from days of old no one has heard, nor has ear perceived,Nor
        has the eye seen a God besides You,Who works and acts in behalf of the one
        who [gladly] waits for Him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'You meet him who rejoices in doing that which is morally right,Who
        remembers You in Your ways.Indeed, You were angry, for we sinned;  We have
        long continued in our sins [prolonging Your anger].And shall we be saved
        [under such circumstances]?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "For we all have become like one who is [ceremonially] unclean [like
        a leper],And all our deeds of righteousness are like filthy rags;We all wither
        and decay like a leaf,And our wickedness [our sin, our injustice, our wrongdoing],
        like the wind, takes us away [carrying us far from God\u2019s favor, toward
        destruction].  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'There is no one who calls on Your name,Who awakens and causes himself
        to take hold of You;For You have hidden Your face from usAnd have handed
        us over to the [consuming and destructive] power of our wickedness [our sin,
        our injustice, our wrongdoing].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Yet, O Lord, You are our Father;We are the clay, and You our Potter,And
        we all are the work of Your hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Do not be angry beyond measure, O Lord,Do not remember our wickedness
        [our sin, our injustice, our wrongdoing] forever.Now look, consider, for
        we are all Your people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Your holy cities have become a wilderness,Zion has become a wilderness,Jerusalem
        a desolation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Our holy and beautiful house [the temple built by Solomon],Where
        our fathers praised You,Has been burned by fire;And all our precious objects
        are in ruins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: Considering these [tragedies], will You restrain Yourself, O Lord
        [and not help us]?Will You keep silent and humiliate and oppress us beyond
        measure?
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Rebellious People'
      title: A Rebellious People
      number: 1
      content: "  \u201CI let Myself be sought by those who did not ask for Me;I
        let Myself be found by those who did not seek Me.I said, \u2018Here am I,
        here am I,\u2019To the nation [Israel] which did not call on My Name.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'I have spread out My hands all the day long to a rebellious and stubborn
        people,Who walk in the way that is not good, [following] after their own
        thoughts and intentions,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The people who continually provoke Me to My face,Sacrificing [to
        idols] in gardens and making offerings with incense on bricks [instead of
        at the designated altar];  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Who sit among the graves [trying to conjure up evil spirits] and
        spend the night in the secret places [where spirits are thought to dwell];Who
        eat swine\u2019s flesh,And their pots hold the broth of unclean meat;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Who say, \u2018Keep to yourself, do not come near me,For I am too
        holy for you [and you might defile me]!\u2019These [people] are smoke in
        My nostrils,A fire that burns all the day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Indeed, it is written before Me,I will not keep silent, but I will
        repay;I will even repay it [directly] into their arms,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Both your own wickedness and the wickedness of your fathers,\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201CSince they too have made offerings with incense on the
        mountainsAnd scorned and taunted Me on the hills,I therefore will measure
        [punishment for] their former work [directly] into their arms.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "This is what the Lord says,\u201CAs the new wine is found in the
        cluster,And one says, \u2018Do not destroy it, for there is a blessing and
        benefit in it,\u2019So I will do for the sake of My servantsIn order not
        to destroy all of them.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'I will bring forth descendants from Jacob,And an heir of My mountains
        from Judah;Even My chosen ones shall inherit it,And My servants will live
        there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And [the plain of] Sharon will be a place for flocks to graze,And
        the Valley of Achor a resting place for herds,For My people who seek Me [who
        long for Me and require My presence in their lives].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'But you who abandon (turn away from) the Lord,Who forget and ignore
        My holy mountain (Zion),Who set a table for Gad [the Babylonian god of fortune],And
        who fill a jug of mixed wine for Meni [the god of fate],  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "I will destine you for the sword, [says the Lord],And all of you
        will bow down to the slaughter,Because when I called, you did not answer;When
        I spoke, you did not listen or obey.But you did [what was] evil in My sightAnd
        chose that in which I did not delight.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore, the Lord God says this,\u201CListen carefully, My servants
        will eat, but you will be hungry;Indeed, My servants will drink, but you
        will be thirsty;Indeed, My servants will rejoice, but you will be put to
        shame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Indeed, My servants will shout for joy from a happy heart,But you
        will cry out with a heavy heart,And you shall wail and howl from a broken
        spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And you will leave your name behind to My chosen ones [who will use
        it] as a curse,And the Lord God will put you to death,But He will call His
        servants by another name [a much greater name, just as the name Israel was
        greater than the name Jacob].  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: New Heavens and a New Earth'
      title: New Heavens and a New Earth
      number: 16
      content: 'Because he who blesses himself on the earthWill bless himself by
        the God of truth and faithfulness;And he who swears [an oath] on the earthWill
        swear by the God of truth and faithfulness;Because the former troubles are
        forgotten,And because they are hidden from My sight.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CBehold, I am creating new heavens and a new earth;And the former
        things [of life] will not be remembered or come to mind.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'But be glad and rejoice forever over what I create;Behold, I am creating
        Jerusalem to be a source of rejoicingAnd her people a joy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will also rejoice in Jerusalem and be glad in My people;And there
        will no longer be heard in herThe voice of weeping and the sound of crying.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'No longer shall there be in it an infant who lives only a few days,Or
        an old man who does not finish his days;For the youth who dies at the age
        of a hundred,And the one who does not reach the age of a hundredWill be thought
        of as accursed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They will build houses and live in them;They will plant vineyards
        and eat the fruit.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'They will not build and another occupy;They will not plant and another
        eat [the fruit].For as the lifetime of a tree, so will be the days of My
        people,And My chosen [people] will fully enjoy [and long make use of] the
        work of their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'They will not labor in vain,Or bear children for disaster;For they
        are the descendants of those blessed by the Lord,And their offspring with
        them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'It shall also come to pass that before they call, I will answer;
        and while they are still speaking, I will hear. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "The wolf and the lamb will graze together, and the lion will eat
        straw like the ox [there will no longer be predator and prey]; and dust will
        be the serpent\u2019s food. They will do no evil or harm in all My holy mountain
        (Zion),\u201D says the Lord."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Heaven Is God\u2019s Throne"
      title: "Heaven Is God\u2019s Throne"
      number: 1
      content: "  This is what the Lord says,\u201CHeaven is My throne and the earth
        is My footstool.Where, then, is a house that you could build for Me?And where
        will My resting place be?  "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: Hypocrisy Rebuked'
      title: Hypocrisy Rebuked
      number: 2
      content: "For all these things My hand has made,So all these things came into
        being [by and for Me],\u201D declares the Lord.\u201CBut to this one I will
        look [graciously],To him who is humble and contrite in spirit, and who [reverently]
        trembles at My word and honors My commands.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CHe who kills an ox [for pagan sacrifice] is [as guilty] as
        one who kills a man;He who sacrifices a lamb, as one who breaks a dog\u2019s
        neck;He who offers a grain offering, as one who offers swine\u2019s blood;He
        who offers incense, as one who blesses an idol.Such people have chosen their
        own ways,And their soul delights in their repulsive acts;  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "So I will choose their punishments,And will bring the things they
        dread upon themBecause I called, but no one answered;I spoke, but they did
        not listen or obey.But they did evil in My sightAnd chose that in which I
        did not delight.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Hear the word of the Lord, you who tremble [with awe-filled reverence]
        at His word:\u201CYour brothers who hate you, who exclude you for My Name\u2019s
        sake,Have said, \u2018Let the Lord be glorified, that we may see your joy.\u2019But
        they will be put to shame.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The sound of an uproar from the city! A voice from the temple!The
        voice of the Lord, providing retribution to His enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "\u201CBefore she (Zion) was in labor, she gave birth;Before her labor
        pain came, she gave birth to a boy.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Who has heard of such a thing? Who has seen such things?Can a land
        be born in one day?Or can a nation be brought forth in a moment?As soon as
        Zion was in labor, she also brought forth her sons.  '
      comments: []
    - name: "9: Joy in Jerusalem\u2019s Future"
      title: "Joy in Jerusalem\u2019s Future"
      number: 9
      content: "Shall I bring to the moment of birth and not give delivery?\u201D
        says the Lord.\u201COr shall I who gives delivery shut the womb?\u201D says
        your God.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "\u201CRejoice with Jerusalem and be glad for her, all you who love
        her;Rejoice greatly with her, all you who mourn over her,  "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "That you may nurse and be satisfied with her comforting breasts,That
        you may drink deeply and be delighted with her bountiful bosom.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "For the Lord says this, \u201CBehold, I extend peace to her (Jerusalem)
        like a river,And the glory of the nations like an overflowing stream;And
        you will be nursed, you will be carried on her hip and [playfully] rocked
        on her knees.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "As one whom his mother comforts, so I will comfort you;And you will
        be comforted in Jerusalem.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'When you see this, your heart will rejoice;Your bones will flourish
        like new grass.And the [powerful] hand of the Lord will be revealed to His
        servants,But His indignation will be toward His enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For indeed, the Lord will come in fireAnd His chariots will be like
        the stormy wind,To render His anger with rage,And His rebuke with flames
        of fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For the Lord will execute judgment by fireAnd by His sword on all
        mankind,And those slain by the Lord will be many.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "\u201CThose who [vainly attempt to] sanctify and cleanse themselves
        to go to the gardens [to sacrifice to idols],Following after one in the center,Who
        eat swine\u2019s flesh, detestable things and mice,Will come to an end together,\u201D
        says the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CFor I know their works and their thoughts. The time is coming
        to gather all nations and languages, and they will come and see My glory. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I will set up a [miraculous] sign among them, and from them I will
        send survivors to the nations: Tarshish, Pul (Put), Lud, Meshech, Tubal and
        Javan, to the distant islands and coastlands that have not heard of My fame
        nor seen My glory. And they will declare and proclaim My glory among the
        nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then they shall bring all your countrymen (children of Israel) from
        all the nations as a grain offering to the Lord\u2014on horses, in chariots,
        in litters, on mules and on camels\u2014to My holy mountain Jerusalem,\u201D
        says the Lord, \u201Cjust as the sons of Israel bring their grain offering
        in a clean vessel to the house of the Lord. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "I will also take some of them as priests and Levites,\u201D says
        the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "\u201CFor just as the new heavens and the new earthWhich I make will
        remain and endure before Me,\u201D declares the Lord,\u201CSo your offspring
        and your name will remain and endure.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And it shall be that from New Moon to New MoonAnd from Sabbath to
        Sabbath,All mankind will come to bow down and worship before Me,\u201D says
        the Lord.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "\u201CThen they will go forth and lookUpon the dead bodies of the
        [rebellious] menWho have transgressed against Me;For their worm (maggot)
        will not die,And their fire will not go out;And they will be an abhorrence
        to all mankind.\u201D"
      comments: []
